{"title_page": "Vikram (actor)", "text_new": "{{Use Indian English|date=October 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Good article}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Vikram\n| image              = Vikram.jpg\n| caption            = Vikram in 2009\n| birth_name         = Kennedy John Victor\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=y|1966|04|17}}<ref>[http://www.sify.com/movies/surprise-b-day-cake-for-vikram-on-sketch-set-news-tamil-rerkcviaiejij.html Surprise b`day cake for Vikram on `Sketch` set]. Sify.com (17 April 2017). Retrieved on 17 September 2018.</ref><ref>Vasudevan, K.V. (23 April 2016) [http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/actor-vikram-turned-50-last-wee/article8513713.ece Actor vikram turned 50 last week]. The Hindu. Retrieved on 17 September 2018.</ref>\n| birth_place        = <!--Must be sourced-->\n| residence          = <!--Must be sourced-->\n| nationality        = Indian\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Film actor|film producer|[[playback singer]]|voice actor}}\n| years_active       = 1990\u2013present\n| spouse             = Shailaja Balakrishnan (m.1992)\n| children           = 2 (inc. [[Dhruv Vikram]])\n| awards             = [[National Film Award for Best Actor|National Best Actor]] (2003)<br />[[Tamil Nadu State Film Award for Best Actor|State Best Actor]] (1999, 2003,2010) <br />[[Kalaimamani]] (2004)\n| website            = \n| alma_mater     = [[Loyola College, Chennai]]\n}}\n\n'''Kennedy John Victor''' (born 17 April 1966), better known by his stage name '''Vikram''' or '''Chiyaan Vikram''', is an Indian actor and singer who predominantly appears in [[Tamil cinema|Tamil language]] films. He has won seven [[Filmfare Awards South|Filmfare Awards]] as well as one [[National Film Awards|National Film Award]] and [[Tamil Nadu State Film Awards|Tamil Nadu State Film Award]] amongst other recognitions and was awarded an [[Honorary Doctorate]] by the [[University of Milan]] in May 2011.\n\nHe made his debut in the 1990 film ''[[En Kadhal Kanmani]]'', which was followed by a series of small-budget Tamil, [[Malayalam cinema|Malayalam]] and [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]] films in the 1990s, many of which went unnoticed. However, the success of [[Bala (director)|Bala]]'s tragedy film ''[[Sethu (film)|Sethu]]'' (1999), in which Vikram appeared as a rogue turned lover, started Vikram's successful career as an actor. In the early 2000s, Vikram appeared in a series of [[Masala (film genre)|masala films]], with ''[[Dhill]]'' (2001), ''[[Gemini (2002 Tamil film)|Gemini]]'' (2002), ''[[Dhool]]'' (2003) and ''[[Saamy]]'' (2003) becoming commercially successful ventures. During the period, Vikram also appeared in diverse roles and received critical acclaim for his performance as a blind villager in ''[[Kasi (film)|Kasi]]'' and a [[Robin Hood]]-esque figure in ''[[Samurai (2002 film)|Samurai]]''. In 2003, Vikram's performance as a gravedigger with autism spectrum disorders in Bala's ''[[Pithamagan]]'' saw him win the [[National Film Award for Best Actor]], with his character only speaking a couple of lines of dialogue in the entire film.<ref name=\"pithwin\">{{cite web|author=Kumar, Ashok |date=20 August 2004 |title=Vikram, the Victor |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2004/08/20/stories/2004082001760100.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201091647/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2004/08/20/stories/2004082001760100.htm |archivedate= 1 February 2015 |df= }}</ref> \n\nHis appearance as an idealistic lawyer with [[Dissociative identity disorder|multiple personality disorder]] in [[S. Shankar|Shankar]]'s blockbuster ''[[Anniyan]]'' (2005) also won critical acclaim, as did his appearance as a superhero in ''[[Kanthaswamy]]'' (2009). Vikram's portrayal of Veeraiya, a tribal leader inspired by the [[Ramayana]] character [[Ravana]], in [[Mani Ratnam]]'s ''[[Raavanan]]'' saw him secure further accolades, as did his appearance as a mentally challenged adult with the maturity of a six-year-old boy in ''[[Deiva Thirumagal]]'' (2011). He consequently appeared in multiple get-ups as a bodybuilder and a crippled hunchback, losing up to 35 kilograms for sequences, during the making of Shankar's romantic thriller ''[[I (film)|I]]'' (2015) and won rave reviews from critics for his performance. It is currently the [[List of highest-grossing Tamil films|sixth highest-grossing Tamil film]] of all time.<ref>{{cite web|date=4 March 2015 |title=Vikram's 'I' Box Office: Shankar's Film Completes 50-Day Milestone in Theatres |work=International Business Times |url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/vikrams-i-box-office-shankars-film-completes-50-day-milestone-theatres-625176 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402130922/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/vikrams-i-box-office-shankars-film-completes-50-day-milestone-theatres-625176 |archivedate= 2 April 2015 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"ihindu\">{{cite web|author=Rangan, Baradwaj |date=14 January 2015 |title=I: A terrific performance let down by an uninspired, exhausting movie |work=The Hindu |accessdate=18 January 2015 |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-reviews/i-movie-review-by-baradwaj-rangan/article6789179.ece |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201141639/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-reviews/i-movie-review-by-baradwaj-rangan/article6789179.ece |archivedate= 1 February 2015 |df= }}</ref>\n\nVikram has promoted various social causes and appeared as the Youth Envoy for the [[United Nations Human Settlements Programme]] in 2011. He has been a brand ambassador of Sanjeevani Trust and a school for special children, Vidya Sudha, which he stayed at during the making of ''Deiva Thirumagal'' as well as having long-term associations with the Kasi Eye Care and running his own welfare association through the Vikram Foundation.<ref name=\"vikramun\">{{cite web|date=23 April 2010 |title=Vikram happy at being chosen UN Youth envoy |work=[[Deccan Herald]] |accessdate=7 January 2011 |url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/155996/vikram-happy-being-chosen-un.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110515134019/http://www.deccanherald.com/content/155996/vikram-happy-being-chosen-un.html |archivedate=15 May 2011 |df= }}</ref> In 2016, he produced and directed the video to the flood relief anthem, [[Spirit of Chennai]], as a tribute to the city's volunteers following the [[2015 South Indian floods]].\n\n==Early life==\nVikram was born as Kennedy to a Christian father and a Hindu mother in [[Madras]], [[Tamil Nadu]].<ref name=\"flopactor\"/> His father, John Victor (alias [[Vinod Raj (Tamil actor)|Vinod Raj]]) was a native of Paramakudi and ran away from home to start a career in films. His father, however, did not fare successfully, and only managed to act in supporting roles in Tamil films and television serials and this inspired Vikram to take part in theatre lessons and become professionally trained in classical and cinema dance forms to ensure he became a leading actor.<ref name=\"flopactor\">{{cite web|author=Sreedhar, Sridevi |date=4 June 2006 |title=Southern spice |work=[[The Telegraph (Calcutta)|The Telegraph]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1060604/asp/look/story_6303930.asp |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121102154911/http://www.telegraphindia.com/1060604/asp/look/story_6303930.asp |archivedate= 2 November 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"fatheractor\">{{cite web |author=Narasimham, N. L |date=4 March 2005 |title=Still the regular guy |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2005/03/04/stories/2005030401210200.htm}}</ref> Rajeshwari, Vikram's mother, was a sub-collector and her brother, [[Thiagarajan]] is an established director-actor in the Tamil film industry; with his son, actor [[Prashanth (actor)|Prashanth]], being Vikram's first cousin.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/did-you-know-/Vikram-and-Prashanth-are-cousins/articleshow/39683316.cms|title= Prasand and Vikram are cousins|publisher=[[The Times of India]] |date=5 August 2014 |accessdate=16 August 2014}}</ref>\n\nVikram is used as a screen name as he disliked his original name, Kennedy; the name Vikram was composed by taking \"Vi\" from his father's name, \"K\" from Kennedy, \"Ra\" from his mother's name and \"ram\" from his sun sign, [[Aries (astrology)|Aries]].<ref name=\"caravan\">{{cite web|author=Rangan, Baradwaj |date=1 December 2013 |title=Man of Steel |work=The Caravan Magazine |accessdate=8 April 2014 |url=http://www.caravanmagazine.in/arts/man-steel |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150918094317/http://www.caravanmagazine.in/arts/man-steel |archivedate=18 September 2015 |df= }}</ref>\n\nVikram was educated at [[Montfort School, Yercaud]], a boarding school in a hill station near [[Salem, Tamil Nadu|Salem]] and graduated in 1983. He has mentioned that he used his opportunities at school well by taking part in karate, horseback riding and swimming and noted that such early exposure to activities gave him confidence as a youngster. Vikram lurked in the fringes of the school's theatre club for a long period and often took part in backstage work before being handed the lead role in a school adaptation of [[Moli\u00e8re]]'s ''[[Le M\u00e9decin malgr\u00e9 lui|The Doctor in Spite of Himself]]'' after the original lead had contracted chicken pox.<ref name=\"caravan\"/> Despite expressing his interest to join films after school, his father forced him to go through education with Vikram subsequently graduated from [[Loyola College, Chennai]] with a degree in English Literature and worked halfway towards an MBA programme.<ref name=\"redwin\"/> Through the prolific dramatics club, Vikram appeared in stage productions including college adaptations of ''[[The Caine Mutiny Court-Martial]]'' and [[Peter Shaffer]]'s ''[[Black Comedy (play)|Black Comedy]]'', receiving best actor awards for his performances.<ref name=\"caravan\"/> After winning a Best Actor Award at a function held at [[Indian Institute of Technology Madras|IIT Madras]], Vikram was hit by a truck during a ride on his motorbike on the way home and suffered a serious leg injury. He remained hospital-ridden for three years during college and subsequently went through twenty-three surgeries to prevent his leg from being amputated.<ref name=\"redwin\">{{cite web|author=Warrier, Shobha |date=17 August 2004 |title=Vikram's obsession gets its reward |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2004/aug/17vikram.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110718203136/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2004/aug/17vikram.htm |archivedate=18 July 2011 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"mint\">{{cite web|author=Sukumaran, Shradha |date=17 June 2010 |title=\u2018My blood group is B+ and that's my motto\u2019 |work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.livemint.com/2010/06/17200701/8216My-blood-group-is-B-an.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100621065336/http://www.livemint.com/2010/06/17200701/8216My-blood-group-is-B-an.html |archivedate=21 June 2010 |df= }}</ref> Vikram then returned to finish the final year of his degree after his accident and secured permission to finish his dissertation at home, as he was only able to walk on crutches for a short period.<ref name=\"vikacc\">{{cite web|author=Muthiah, Wani |date=28 July 2011 |title=Long, winding path to success for Vikram |work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2011/7/28/nation/9176084&sec=nation |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121019105521/http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=%2F2011%2F7%2F28%2Fnation%2F9176084&sec=nation |url-status=dead |archive-date=19 October 2012 |df= }}</ref>\n\n==Film career==\n===1990\u20131998===\nVikram began his professional career by modelling in advert films for brands including Chola Tea, TVS Excel and Alwyn watches as well as appearing in a six episode television serial titled ''Galatta Kudumbam'', which aired between November and December 1988. During the final year of his [[M.B.A]] programme at [[Loyola College, Chennai|Loyola College]], he was recognised by the film industry, with veteran director [[C. V. Sridhar]] approaching him for a lead role in a film.<ref name=\"hindrel\">{{cite web|author=Narasimhan, N. L.|date=4 March 2005|title=Still the regular guy|work=The Hindu|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2005/03/04/stories/2005030401210200.htm}}</ref> Vikram made his film debut in 1990 by appearing in ''[[En Kadhal Kanmani]]'', a small budget love story featuring him alongside [[Rekha (Tamil actress)|Rekha Nambiar]], with Sridhar's ''[[Thanthu Vitten Ennai]]'', opposite [[Rohini (actress)|Rohini]] being his next release. He then signed on to be a part of cinematographer [[P. C. Sriram]]'s college love story ''[[Meera (1992 film)|Meera]]'', with high expectations, however, the three films failed to launch his career.<ref name=\"redset\">{{cite web|author=Warrier, Shobha |date=27 March 2000 |title=All that matters is a hit |publisher=[[Rediff.com]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2000/mar/27vikram.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120429174044/http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2000/mar/27vikram.htm |archivedate=29 April 2012 |df= }}</ref> His appearances in ''Meera'' and in ''[[Kaaval Geetham]]'', with another veteran director [[S. P. Muthuraman]], helped him secure film offers from the [[Malayalam]] and [[Telugu language|Telugu]] film industries.<ref name=\"hindrel\"/> In 1993, he almost signed on to appear in [[Mani Ratnam]]'s ''[[Bombay (film)|Bombay]]'' and featured in the initial photo shoot alongside [[Manisha Koirala]]. However, Mani Ratnam wanted Vikram to remove his beard for the role, and Vikram could not do so due to continuity problems with another film he had signed and hence was dropped from the project.<ref name=\"vikramkerala\">{{cite web|author=Nair, Ranjith|year=2005|title=Vikram Interview|publisher=Deepika|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=http://www.bollywhat-forum.com/index.php?topic=6757.0}}</ref>\n\nBetween 1993 and 1994, Vikram appeared in a series of films where he portrayed supporting roles. He appeared in three successful [[Malayalam]] films by appearing with [[Mammooty]], [[Suresh Gopi]] and [[Jayaram]] in [[Joshi (director)|Joshi]]'s successful action film ''[[Dhruvam]]'', before teaming up with Gopi again for [[Shaji Kailas]]'s ''[[Mafia (1993 film)|Mafia]]'', which explored Bangalore's criminal underworld. Furthermore, Joshi cast him again alongside Mammooty in the action drama ''[[Sainyam]]'' in the role of an [[Combined Cadet Force|air cadet]].<ref name=\"malay\">{{cite web|author=Nair, Unni|date=13 August 2010|title=Vikram to act in a Malayalam film|work=[[The Indian Express]]|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/Vikram-to-act-in-a-Malayalam-film/659056/}}</ref> During the period, Vikram also appeared in the small budget Telugu film ''[[Chirunavvula Varamistava]]'' in the lead role and as [[Akkineni Nageswara Rao]]'s eldest son in the family drama ''[[Bangaru Kutumbam]]'', with both films failing commercially. A brief return to Tamil films also proved unsuccessful, with his role in [[Vikraman]]'s multi-starrer ''[[Pudhiya Mannargal]]'', with music composed by [[A. R. Rahman]] turning out to be a commercial failure.<ref name=\"pmflop\">{{cite web|title=Actor&nbsp;\u2013 Important too. |publisher=Behindwoods |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-articles/movies-04/ar-rahman-3.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121021013016/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-articles/movies-04/ar-rahman-3.html |archivedate=21 October 2012 |df= }}</ref>\n\nThroughout 1995 and 1996, Vikram appeared in further Telugu and Malayalam films to receive income, being kept away from Tamil films due to a lack of offers.<ref name=\"redset\"/> He played the lead role in the Malayalam film ''Mayoora Nritam'' directed by [[Vijayakrishnan]]'s and even played villain in ''Street'' opposite [[Babu Antony]] and lead roles in the small budget Telugu films ''[[Aadaalla Majaka|Adalla Majaka]]'' and [[Sriraj Ginne]]'s ''[[Akka! Bagunnava?]]''. He collaborated again with Mammooty in ''[[Indraprastham (film)|Indraprastham]]'' and Suresh Gopi in ''Rajaputhran'', before appearing in his first lead role in Malayalam with ''[[Itha Oru Snehagatha]]'' opposite [[Laila Mehdin|Laila]].<ref name=\"malay\"/> Vikram signed [[Amitabh Bachchan]]'s first Tamil language film production, ''[[Ullaasam]]'', which also featured [[Ajith Kumar]] and [[Maheswari]]. The big budget film created anticipation prior to release, but was ultimately panned and fared poorly at the box office.<ref name=\"ulla\">{{cite web|author=Warrier, Shobha |date=6 July 1999 |title='Thanks to my relationship, I've stopped trusting people' |publisher=[[Rediff.com]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/1999/jul/06ajit.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110510080114/http://www.rediff.com/movies/1999/jul/06ajit.htm |archivedate=10 May 2011 |df= }}</ref> However, Vikram acknowledged the film for expanding his female fan base as a result of the soft-personality of his character.<ref name=\"redset\"/> He followed it up with appearances in the unsuccessful films ''Kurralla Rajyam'' in Telugu and then in the [[Ilaiyaraaja]] musical ''[[Kangalin Vaarthaigal]]'', before playing a short role in [[R. Parthiban|Parthiban]]'s critically acclaimed film ''[[Housefull (1999 film)|Housefull]]''.\n\nDuring his struggling phase, Vikram dubbed for other heroes in films including voices for [[Prabhu Deva]] in ''[[Kaadhalan]]'', [[Ajith Kumar]] in ''[[Amaravathi (1993 film)|Amaravathi]]'' and [[Abbas (actor)|Abbas]] in ''[[Kandukondain Kandukondain]]'' respectively. Vikram has mentioned that he did not look down on dubbing and saw it as a \"dignity of labour\".<ref name=\"mint\"/> During the period, he also attended dancing classes every day, and tried acting out different scenes and different characters with his small group of friends.<ref name=\"front\">{{cite web|date=19 September 2004 |title=`I am a director's actor' |publisher=[[The Hindu|Frontline (The Hindu)]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.frontlineonnet.com/fl2119/stories/20040924003910700.htm |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100507035929/http://www.frontlineonnet.com/fl2119/stories/20040924003910700.htm |archivedate=7 May 2010 }}</ref> He began to turn down chances to play supporting roles in films and was intent on making a breakthrough as a lead actor and notably turned down the role of Swarnamalya's fianc\u00e9e in Mani Ratnam's ''[[Alaipayuthey (film)|Alaipayuthey]]''.<ref name=\"caravan\"/> Vikram also rejected approaches from television serial producers, citing that working in television would reduce his chances of becoming a mainstream actor.<ref name=\"net\">{{cite web|author=Balakrishnan, Ravi |date=3 July 2010 |title=What drives Raavan's actor Vikram to do unusual roles |work=[[The Economic Times]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/features/business-of-bollywood/what-drives-raavans-actor-vikram-to-do-unusual-roles/articleshow/6121881.cms |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121019234236/http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/features/business-of-bollywood/what-drives-raavans-actor-vikram-to-do-unusual-roles/articleshow/6121881.cms |archivedate=19 October 2012 |df= }}</ref> He also refused opportunities to take part in film events as a backing dancer, with actor [[Sriman (actor)|Sriman]] revealing that Vikram was \"one amongst not many\" who was not interested in travelling to Canada to participate in such shows.<ref name=\"caravan\"/>\n\n===1999\u20132001===\nIn 1997, debutant director [[Bala (director)|Bala]] offered him the role of the rogue Sethu (Chiyaan), in the film ''[[Sethu (film)|Sethu]]''. To prepare for the character, Vikram shaved his head, lost twenty-one kilograms and grew his nails long for the role.<ref name=\"redwin\"/><ref name=\"front\"/>  After beginning production in April 1997, the film went through [[development hell]] after industry strikes and lack of funds hampered progress. During this phase, he did not accept other acting offers in order to maintain the continuity of his looks. The film then struggled to find a distributor, who shunned it due to the tragic climax and the film remained unreleased.<ref>{{cite news|title=Making films for the real world |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/lf/2003/01/02/stories/2003010206620200.htm |accessdate=7 November 2011 |newspaper=The Hindu |date=2 January 2003 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130607041653/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/lf/2003/01/02/stories/2003010206620200.htm |archivedate= 7 June 2013 |df= }}</ref> Vikram described the period of production as \"the worst phase of his career\" as he was financially strapped and \"his fire was in danger of dying down\".<ref name=\"front\"/> He turned down an opportunity from a friend to take up a job in technology and attempted to stay in the industry by directing a serial titled ''Mounam Pesiyadhey'', with [[Ameer (director)|Ameer]] as his assistant director.<ref name=\"caravan\"/> ''Sethu'' finally released in December 1999 and initially began running at a single noon show at a suburban theater, but gradually gained an audience through word-of-mouth publicity. Eventually, it ran for over one hundred days at several cinema halls across [[Chennai]]. Vikram was constantly being mobbed by people on the streets as a result of the film's success.<ref name=\"redwin\"/><ref name=\"redset\"/> Critics praised Vikram's performance with a reviewer referring to Vikram as \"a revelation\" and that \"he is very natural and his acting in last few scenes are just too good and could even be compared with the best we have seen\".<ref name=\"indolinksethu\">{{cite web |author=Hariharan, Easwaran |date=December 1999 |title=Sethu |publisher=Indolink.com |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.indolink.com/tamil/cinema/Reviews/articles/Sethu_191236.html |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110806185746/http://www.indolink.com/tamil/cinema/Reviews/articles/Sethu_191236.html |archivedate=6 August 2011  }}</ref> Similarly, a critic from the [[Malaysia]]n daily [[New Straits Times]], described the film as an \"unforgettable experience\" and described Vikram's performance as \"praise-worthy\".<ref name=\"nst\">{{cite web|author=Vijayan, K. N.|date=12 February 2000|title=Laughs and tears galore in 'Sethu'|work=[[New Straits Times]]|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=9lRIAAAAIBAJ&sjid=lRQEAAAAIBAJ&pg=3969,1961135&dq=vikram+sethu&hl=en}}</ref> The performance drew accolades with Vikram winning the [[Filmfare Special Award&nbsp;\u2013 South]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Nuvvu Nenu wins 4 Filmfare awards |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2002-04-06/hyderabad/27122602_1_filmfare-film-award-actor-award |accessdate=5 January 2012 |newspaper=The Times of India |date=6 April 2002 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201075354/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/hyderabad/Nuvvu-Nenu-wins-4-Filmfare-awards/articleshow/6011249.cms?referral=PM |archivedate= 1 February 2015 |df= }}</ref> and the [[Tamil Nadu State Film Award Special Prize]] for his portrayal of the title character, while reports emerged that he missed out on the [[National Film Award for Best Actor]] by a single vote to [[Mohanlal]].<ref name=\"missedsethu\">{{cite web|author=Rajitha |date=21 July 2000 |title=Ajit backs off Nanda |publisher=[[Rediff.com]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2000/jul/21spice.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121026145436/http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2000/jul/21spice.htm |archivedate=26 October 2012 |df= }}</ref> Post-''Sethu'', Vikram has said that the film would have been close to him regardless of its commercial success and that it put him on the \"right path\", with Vikram choosing to adapt the prefix of Chiyaan to his screen name.<ref name=\"front\"/>\n\nVikram did not sign up to a film for sixty five days after the release of ''Sethu'', to ensure that he made the right career move.<ref name=\"redwin\"/> Vikram spent time completing projects he had agreed to feature in before the release of ''Sethu'' and hence made a couple of appearances in the Malayalam films ''[[Red Indians (film)|Red Indians]]'' and the horror film ''[[Indriyam]]''.<ref name=\"iondr\">{{cite web|year=2000 |title=Indriyam |publisher=Bizhat |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://movies.bizhat.com/review_indriyam.php |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040813120915/http://movies.bizhat.com/review_indriyam.php |archivedate=13 August 2004 |df= }}</ref> He also played a leading role in ''[[Siragugal]]'', a rare Tamil telefilm produced and featuring [[Raadhika]], which was shot entirely in the suburbs of [[London]].<ref>{{cite web|title=SIRAGUGAL|url=http://www.radaan.tv/siragugal.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120419151726/http://www.radaan.tv/siragugal.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=19 April 2012|work=Radaan Mediaworks|publisher=Radaan Mediaworks India Limited|accessdate=7 November 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Grand aunt of the small screen |url=http://hindu.com/2001/07/05/stories/09050464.htm |accessdate=7 November 2011 |newspaper=The Hindu |date=5 July 2001 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019072746/http://hindu.com/2001/07/05/stories/09050464.htm |archivedate=19 October 2013 |df= }}</ref> Furthermore, he also completed two Telugu films during the period; ''[[9 Nelalu]]'' and ''Youth''. ''9 Nelalu'' featured Vikram as the husband of the character played by [[Soundarya]], who faces the challenges of being a surrogate mother. The film won positive reviews, with a critic mentioning that Vikram gave a \"controlled performance\"<ref name=\"ninenel\">{{cite web|first=Christopher|last=Domingo|year=2000|title=9 Nelalu Movie Review|publisher=FullHyderabad.com|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=http://www.fullhyderabad.com/profile/movies/1904/2/9-nelalu-movie-review}}</ref> while Vikram's newfound popularity in Tamil films saw the film dubbed into Tamil soon after as ''Kandane Seethayai'', with an inserted comedy track by comedian [[Vivek (actor)|Vivek]].<ref name=\"kandense\">{{cite web|author=Balsubramaniam, Balaji |year=2000 |title=Kandane Seethayai |publisher=Thiraipadam.com |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.thiraipadam.com/cgi-bin/movie_review.pl?id=136&user_name=bbalaji&review_lang=english&lang=english |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111004175649/http://www.thiraipadam.com/cgi-bin/movie_review.pl?id=136&user_name=bbalaji&review_lang=english&lang=english |archivedate= 4 October 2011 |df= }}</ref> His next release was Rajakumaran's ''[[Vinnukum Mannukum]]'', alongside [[Sarath Kumar]], [[Kushboo]] and [[Devayani (actress)|Devayani]], which revolved around an ordinary boy falling in love with an actress. Vikram has since mentioned his displeasure at being a part of the film, claiming that he had arguments with the director for every single shot and that \"everything in that film, right from the first shot was wrong\"; the film became a failure commercially.<ref name=\"whyihate\">{{cite web|author=Kamath, Sudhish |date=15 February 2008 |title=Why I hate... Vinnukkum Mannukkum |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/cp/2008/02/15/stories/2008021550170400.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111201184929/http://www.hindu.com/cp/2008/02/15/stories/2008021550170400.htm |archivedate= 1 December 2011 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"balance\">{{cite web|author=Mahesh, Chitra |date=31 May 2002 |title=`I want to strike a balance' |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/05/31/stories/2002053100170100.htm |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140607062058/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/05/31/stories/2002053100170100.htm |archivedate= 7 June 2014 |df= }}</ref> His next film was ''[[Dhill]]'', where he played an aspiring police officer, Kanagavel, who tackles a corrupt policeman. To appear trim in the role of the aspiring police officer, Vikram went on a strict diet eating only fruits and drinking juice.<ref name=\"starint\">{{cite web|author=Selva, T |date=10 January 2005 |title=Vikram's star rises |work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://ecentral.my/news/story.asp?file=/2005/1/10/movies/9803468&sec=movies |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120609122941/http://ecentral.my/news/story.asp?file=%2F2005%2F1%2F10%2Fmovies%2F9803468&sec=movies |archivedate= 9 June 2012 |df= }}</ref> The film opened to positive reviews, with a critic from ''[[The Hindu]]'' claiming that \"Vikram has the ability and potential\" and that \"Vikram has once again proved that his success in ''[[Sethu (film)|Sethu]]'' was not a fluke\".<ref name=\"dhillhindu\">{{cite web|author=Kumar, Ashok |date=27 July 2001 |title=Film Review: Dhil |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/2001/07/27/stories/09270222.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101128022905/http://hindu.com/thehindu/2001/07/27/stories/09270222.htm |archivedate=28 November 2010 |df= }}</ref> ''Dhill'' subsequently went on to become Vikram's first success in the [[masala (film genre)|masala film genre]] and led the way for more such films in the same genre for him.<ref name=\"dhillhit\">{{cite web|author=Kumar, Ashok |date=9 August 2002 |title=Raising expectations |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/08/09/stories/2002080901030200.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120211210400/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/08/09/stories/2002080901030200.htm |archivedate=11 February 2012 |df= }}</ref> Vikram's portrayal of a blind folk singer in [[Vinayan]]'s ''[[Kasi (film)|Kasi]]'' won him the [[Filmfare Best Actor Award (Tamil)|Filmfare Best Tamil Actor Award]] and the film also did well commercially.<ref name=\"balance\"/> For the movie, he sunbathed on the terrace of his beachside home in Chennai for a sunburnt look and got dizzying headaches while practising to look blind.<ref name=\"starint\"/> Again, Vikram's performance won positive reviews from critics, with a reviewer describing it as an \"extraordinarily detailed performance\" and that \"as the blind singer, he brings laughter, tears and a lump in one's throat\".<ref name=\"kasisify\">{{cite web|date=17 December 2001 |title=Kasi |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/kasi-review-tamil-9080157.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131031095013/http://www.sify.com/movies/kasi-review-tamil-9080157.html |archivedate=31 October 2013 |df= }}</ref>\n\n===2002\u20132003===\nThe following year, Vikram went on to play the title role in [[Saran (director)|Saran]]'s ''[[Gemini (2002 Tamil film)|Gemini]]'', produced by [[AVM Productions]], his first big-budget film in the Tamil industry, which featured him in the role of a local rowdy.<ref name=\"sifyvikramone\">{{cite web|year=2002 |title=Vikram |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/interview.php?id=7584766&cid=2408 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022055817/http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/interview.php?id=7584766&cid=2408 |archivedate=22 October 2012 |df= }}</ref> The action film won good reviews, with a critic citing that Vikram \"delivers a convincing performance\" and consequently became a \"box office triumph\".<ref name=\"balance\"/><ref name=\"geminired\">{{cite web|author=Pearl |date=26 April 2002 |title=Vikram chews paan, excels |publisher=[[Rediff.com]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2002/apr/26gem.htm |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140607063050/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2002/apr/26gem.htm |archivedate= 7 June 2014 |df= }}</ref> Similarly, the film's soundtrack composed by [[Bharathwaj]] had become popular prior to release, with Vikram also singing a version of the hit song \"O Podu!\" for the album.<ref name=\"geminimusic\">{{cite web|author=Kamath, Sudhish |date=31 March 2002 |title='Gemini' already a hit |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/lf/2002/03/31/stories/2002033100270200.htm |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140606162017/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/lf/2002/03/31/stories/2002033100270200.htm |archivedate= 6 June 2014 |df= }}</ref> [[Balaji Sakthivel]]'s ''[[Samurai (2002 film)|Samurai]]'' was his next release, featuring him as a vigilante [[Robin Hood]]-esque figure who kidnapped corrupt politicians. Vikram had signed the film in early 2000 and the film was on hold during production, leading to a two-year delay and the film finally opened to average reviews and collections. The critic from ''[[The Hindu]]'' gave praise for Vikram's \"admirably well-maintained physique and powerful eyes\", whilst another labelled that the film's single major positive was Vikram's convincing portrayal.<ref name=\"samred\">{{cite web|author=Pearl |date=5 August 2002 |title=Sigh! |publisher=[[Rediff.com]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2002/aug/05sam.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121026145625/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2002/aug/05sam.htm |archivedate=26 October 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"hinsamu\">{{cite web|author=Rangarajan, Malathi |date=19 July 2002 |title=Samurai |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/07/19/stories/2002071900910201.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120212013813/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/07/19/stories/2002071900910201.htm |archivedate=12 February 2012 |df= }}</ref> His final release of the year was [[Prabhu Solomon]]'s ''[[King (2002 film)|King]]'', a drama film which featured him alongside [[Sneha (actress)|Sneha]] and [[Nassar (actor)|Nassar]]. Vikram played Raja, a magician, who is unaware that he has been diagnosed with [[multiple sclerosis]], with his family trying to keep the truth away from him. The film also met with an unfavorable response commercially, but won positive acclaim from critics.<ref name=\"hinking\">{{cite web|author=Rangarajan, Malathi |date=13 September 2002 |title=King |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/09/13/stories/2002091300970300.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120211234625/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/09/13/stories/2002091300970300.htm |archivedate=11 February 2012 |df= }}</ref>\n\nThe success of [[Dharani (director)|Dharani]]'s ''Dhill'' resulted in the film's team collaborating to make a film in a similar genre; ''[[Dhool]]'', which also featured [[Jyothika]], [[Reemma Sen]] and [[Vivek (actor)|Vivek]].<ref name=\"dhillhit\"/> The film saw Vikram play Aarumugham, a villager, who comes to the city seeking help in regard to a water crisis back home, but subsequently ends up tackling the corrupt politicians who are behind the water scam. In regard to his performance, the [[Rediff.com]] review praised his enactment, citing that \"Vikram is at his peak\" and that \"he seems as much at home with comedy as with action, in romance as in emotional sequences\", while the critic from ''The Hindu'' also praised his performance.<ref name=\"rediffdhool\">{{cite web|author=Aarkhay |date=23 January 2003 |title=Vikram turns up trumps with Dhool |publisher=[[Rediff.com]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2003/jan/23dhool.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110203112042/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2003/jan/23dhool.htm |archivedate= 3 February 2011 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"dhoolreview\">{{cite web|author=Rangarajan, Malathi |date=24 January 2003 |title=Dhool |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/24/stories/2003012401130200.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120211210913/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/24/stories/2003012401130200.htm |archivedate=11 February 2012 |df= }}</ref> The film became a blockbuster and his fifth success in two and a half years, with Vikram being dubbed as \"the matinee idol of our times\" by a leading Indian newspaper.<ref>{{cite news|title=track record |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-cinemaplus/article2602198.ece |accessdate=7 November 2011 |newspaper=The Hindu |date=6 November 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160115234452/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-cinemaplus/article2602198.ece |archivedate=15 January 2016 |df= }}</ref> He also featured in the romantic film ''[[Kadhal Sadugudu]]'', with [[Priyanka Upendra|Priyanka Trivedi]] which was a critical and commercial failure, with reviewers claiming that \"there are times you wish Vikram were a little more brisk and dynamic\" in regard to his performance.<ref name=\"ksgreview\">{{cite web|author=Rangarajan, Malathi |date=18 April 2003 |title=Kadhal Sadugudu |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/04/18/stories/2003041800950202.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120211093956/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/04/18/stories/2003041800950202.htm |archivedate=11 February 2012 |df= }}</ref> After release, Vikram was critical of the film's failure, confessing that the story \"underwent a lot of changes after the initial narration\", lamenting that he was \"taken for a royal ride\" by the producers.<ref name=\"sifyvikramtwo\">{{cite web|year=2003 |title=I Am Happy To Be A Saleable Hero: Vikram |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/interview.php?id=13150128&cid=2408 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022055846/http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/interview.php?id=13150128&cid=2408 |archivedate=22 October 2012 |df= }}</ref>\n\nVikram was then signed on by [[K. Balachander]] to appear in his banner's biggest production till date, ''[[Saamy]]'', directed by [[Hari (director)|Hari]].<ref name=\"kbsaamy\">{{cite web|author=Warrier, Shobha |date=13 March 2003 |title='Sami is Vikram's film' |publisher=[[Rediff.com]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2003/mar/13sami.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120109102551/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2003/mar/13sami.htm |archivedate= 9 January 2012 |df= }}</ref> Vikram played Aarusaamy, an honest cop working in [[Tirunelveli]], who solves the region's communal problems with his down-to-earth approach. Vikram worked on his body for the film, sporting a thick waist to show notable differences from his other police film, ''Dhill'' and also put on eight kilograms.<ref name=\"front\"/> The film took a large opening, grossing over Rs. 7 crores in 10 days in Tamil Nadu, while also taking the largest opening of the new millennium in [[Kerala]], with the Telugu remake rights also sold for a record price. Due to the good opening, the film has proved to be profitable just 10 days after its release and consequently went on to become a blockbuster.<ref name=\"saamybox\">{{cite web|author=Pillai, Sreedhar |date=18 April 2003 |title=Numero Uno |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/mp/2003/05/26/stories/2003052600030201.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101111112657/http://hindu.com/thehindu/mp/2003/05/26/stories/2003052600030201.htm |archivedate=11 November 2010 |df= }}</ref> Vikram's performance also was lapped up by critics earning him a nomination for [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor - Tamil|Filmfare Best Tamil Actor Award]], with the critic from [[Sify]] claiming that Vikram had \"succumbed to the superstar image trap\", but is the \"mainstay of the picture\".<ref name=\"sifysaamy\">{{cite web|year=2003 |title=Review:Saamy |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/saamy-review-tamil-13049384.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141007035217/http://www.sify.com/movies/saamy-review-tamil-13049384.html |archivedate= 7 October 2014 |df= }}</ref>\n\n===2003\u20132009===\nLater that year, he starred in [[Bala (director)|Bala]]'s ''[[Pithamagan]]'', along with [[Suriya (actor)|Suriya]], [[Sangeetha Krish|Sangeetha]] and [[Laila Mehdin|Laila]], playing the role of Chitthan, a gravedigger with autism spectrum disorders. He did not have any dialogue in the film and the actor's acting muscles were stretched as he had to use body language and facial expressions to convey his feelings and thoughts, with Vikram also applying the make-up for the character himself.<ref name=\"front\"/><ref name=\"starint\"/> The film won positive reviews with the critic from ''[[The Hindu]]'' calling it a \"symphony on celluloid\", while noting that it will be a \"milestone in Vikram's career\" and \"he carves a niche for himself in the viewer's mind with his expressions and excellent body language\".<ref name=\"pithth\">{{cite web|author=Rangarajan, Malathi |date=31 October 2003 |title=Pithamagan |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/10/31/stories/2003103101210200.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120211124803/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/10/31/stories/2003103101210200.htm |archivedate=11 February 2012 |df= }}</ref> His portrayal won him both the [[Filmfare Best Actor Award (Tamil)|Filmfare Best Tamil Actor Award]] and the [[National Film Award for Best Actor]], with the latter accolade making him only the third Tamil actor to win the award.<ref name=\"pithwin\"/><ref name=\"redwin\"/> His next release, the revenge drama ''[[Arul]]'', directed by [[Hari (director)|Hari]], garnered poor reviews and box office collections.<ref name=\"arul\">{{cite web|date=17 August 2004 |title=Vikram : A close look at the award winner |publisher=IndiaGlitz |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/10230.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121024045937/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/10230.html |archivedate=24 October 2012 |df= }}</ref>\n\nVikram signed on to feature in the action thriller ''[[Anniyan]]'', directed by prominent director [[S. Shankar|Shankar]] in March 2004.<ref name=\"anniyan\">{{cite web|date=4 March 2004 |title=First look: Shankar's `Anniyan` |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/first-look-shankars-anniyan-news-tamil-kkfvMHaaefa.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022060041/http://www.sify.com/movies/first-look-shankars-anniyan-news-tamil-kkfvMHaaefa.html |archivedate=22 October 2012 |df= }}</ref> Vikram agreed to shoot for the film for 140 days, which was revealed to be amongst the longest contracts signed by an actor in a Tamil film.<ref name=\"anniyanoneforty\">{{cite web|date=16 June 2005 |title=History made, history waits |publisher=IndiaGlitz |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/15221.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121024045949/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/15221.html |archivedate=24 October 2012 |df= }}</ref> The film featured him as a character suffering from [[dissociative identity disorder]] with three distinct personae: a meek lawyer, a suave fashion model and a psychotic serial killer. Prior to release, the film was touted as the most expensive South Indian film ever, costing Rs 26.38 crores, and was released across India with 400 prints.<ref name=\"anniyanbig\">{{cite web|author=Pillai, Sreedhar |date=18 June 2005 |title=The mother of all biggies |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/mp/2005/06/18/stories/2005061803170200.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019072806/http://www.hindu.com/mp/2005/06/18/stories/2005061803170200.htm |archivedate=19 October 2013 |df= }}</ref> ''Anniyan'' took an \"extraordinary opening\",<ref name=\"anniyanopening\">{{cite web|date=18 June 2005 |title=Extraordinary opening! |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/extraordinary-opening-news-tamil-kkfv3rcigha.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022060145/http://www.sify.com/movies/extraordinary-opening-news-tamil-kkfv3rcigha.html |archivedate=22 October 2012 |df= }}</ref> and went on to become a blockbuster grossing more than Rs.100 crores through the original and two dubbed versions.<ref name=\"aparachitbb\">{{cite web|author=Us Salam, Ziya |date=19 May 2006 |title=`Aparichit' no more |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2006/05/19/stories/2006051901290100.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121110120026/http://www.hindu.com/fr/2006/05/19/stories/2006051901290100.htm |archivedate=10 November 2012 |df= }}</ref> Vikram's performance was unanimously praised, with a reviewer from [[Sify]] citing that \"Anniyan truly belongs to Vikram and the film is unthinkable without him\" and \"it is a role that could have been reduced to a caricature by a lesser actor\".<ref name=\"anniyarv\">{{cite web|date=18 June 2005 |title=Anniyan |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/anniyan-review-tamil-13873632.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141030045503/http://www.sify.com/movies/anniyan-review-tamil-13873632.html |archivedate=30 October 2014 |df= }}</ref> The film won 8 out of the 15 awards possible at the 2005 [[Filmfare Awards South]], with Vikram adjudged [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor - Tamil|Best Actor]].<ref name=\"anniyanaward\">{{cite web|date=10 September 2006 |title=`Anniyan` sweeps Filmfare Awards! |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/anniyan-sweeps-filmfare-awards-news-tamil-kkfvinigibe.html |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140926074039/http://www.sify.com/movies/anniyan-sweeps-filmfare-awards-news-tamil-kkfvinigibe.html |archivedate=26 September 2014  }}</ref> Later in the year, he signed and completed [[Shafi (director)|Shafi]]'s comedy film with [[Asin]], ''[[Majaa]]'', in less than five months. The film which also featured [[Pasupathy]] as his brother, saw Vikram work as the assistant director under Shafi.<ref name=\"admajaa\">{{cite web|date=9 January 2006 |title=I've struggled a lot to reach this level: Vikram |publisher=IndiaGlitz |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/malayalam/interview/6525.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201121527/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/malayalam/interview/6525.html |archivedate= 1 February 2015 |df= }}</ref> ''Majaa'' faced a poor response at the box office and fetched average reviews, with a reviewer citing that \"you will surely find something missing\".<ref name=\"majaaindure\">{{cite web|author=Kumar, Ashok |date=4 November 2005 |title=Where is the entertainment? |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2005/11/04/stories/2005110402340200.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120211234401/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2005/11/04/stories/2005110402340200.htm |archivedate=11 February 2012 |df= }}</ref>\n\nVikram then signed up for ''[[Bheema]]'' in October 2005, with the film facing severe delays and only releasing in January 2008.<ref name=\"bheemasign\">{{cite web|date=15 October 2005 |title=Vikram is Bheema! |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/vikram-is-bheema-news-tamil-kkfvzjegbdd.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022060506/http://www.sify.com/movies/vikram-is-bheema-news-tamil-kkfvzjegbdd.html |archivedate=22 October 2012 |df= }}</ref> The film saw him portray Sekhar, who grows up idolizing the gangster played by [[Prakash Raj]], and Vikram revealed that he approached the film like an actor, even though the film's script was written \"for a star\".<ref name=\"bheemahindu\">{{cite web|author=Kamath, Sudhish |date=7 September 2007 |title=Vikram versus Kenny |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/cp/2007/09/07/stories/2007090750050100.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100626101624/http://www.hindu.com/cp/2007/09/07/stories/2007090750050100.htm |archivedate=26 June 2010 |df= }}</ref> Upon release, the film gained mixed reviews though reviewers praised Vikram's performance, with a critic claiming that \"Vikram breathes life into the film\", \"he looks sensational with his toned body, killer looks unarguably delivers yet another outstanding performance of his career\" and to \"see the film only for him\".<ref name=\"sifyhindure\">{{cite web|date=15 January 2008 |title=Bheema |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/bheema-review-tamil-14589515.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131218212433/http://www.sify.com/movies/bheema-review-tamil-14589515.html |archivedate=18 December 2013 |df= }}</ref> Similarly, the review from ''The Hindu'' was critical of the excessive violence and mentioned that \"as narration gives way after a point, Vikram can only appear helpless\".<ref name=\"bheemahindure\">{{cite web|author=Rangarajan, Malathi |date=15 January 2008 |title=A bloodbath almost&nbsp;\u2013 Bheema |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2008/01/18/stories/2008011850720200.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121110120105/http://www.hindu.com/fr/2008/01/18/stories/2008011850720200.htm |archivedate=10 November 2012 |df= }}</ref> His next release, ''[[Kanthaswamy (film)|Kanthaswamy]]'', directed by [[Susi Ganesan]] and also featuring [[Shriya Saran]], became the first [[superhero]] film in Tamil cinema, with Vikram being featured as a vigilante dressed as an anthropomorphic rooster, Kokorako and a CBI Officer.<ref name=\"toikantha\">{{cite web|author=Pillai, Sreedhar|date=10 April 2009|title=Gung-ho about 'Kandasamy'|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-04-10/news-interviews/28024076_1_susi-ganesan-kandasamy-film}}</ref> ''Kanthaswamy'' became Vikram's most expensive production beating ''Anniyan'', with the film boasting of high production values of having an innovative pre-launch trailer and with scenes shot in [[Italy]] and [[Mexico]].<ref name=\"trailere\">{{cite web|author=Ashok Kumar, S.R |date=19 September 2007 |title=Invitation for launch of \u2018Kandasamy\u2019 not commonplace |work=The Hindu |accessdate=19 September 2007 |url=http://www.hinduonnet.com/2007/09/19/stories/2007091959110200.htm |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090110182415/http://www.hinduonnet.com/2007/09/19/stories/2007091959110200.htm |archivedate=10 January 2009 }}</ref><ref name=\"kantexp\">{{cite web|author=Ganesan, Sharmilla |date=25 August 2009 |title=Superhero with style |work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]] |accessdate=16 July 2011 |url=http://ecentral.my/news/story.asp?file=/2009/8/25/movies/4566714&sec=movies |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120609123835/http://ecentral.my/news/story.asp?file=%2F2009%2F8%2F25%2Fmovies%2F4566714&sec=movies |archivedate= 9 June 2012 |df= }}</ref> The film earned a mixed response from critics, with the reviewer from [[Sify]] claiming that the film \"strikes a fine balance between style and substance\" and proceeding to state that \"Vikram is mesmerizing and has given an extra dimension to the characters he plays in the film and steers it to the winning post\", suggesting that \"there are very few people in Indian cinema who can do the larger-than-life fantasy characters as easily as Vikram\". Sudhish Kamath of ''The Hindu'' labelled the film as \"slow death\", claiming that \"as an actor, Vikram has nothing to do\". The film took a strong opening, with a collection of Rs. 37 crore, including Rs. 16 crore in Tamil Nadu, at the box office in the opening week of its international release. The film subsequently went on to become one of the most profitable films of the year and ran in theaters for over one hundred days.<ref name=\"hitkantha\">{{cite web|date=2 September 2009 |title=The rooster rocks the box office |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article13770.ece |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121102120011/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article13770.ece |archivedate= 2 November 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"hundredkantha\">{{cite web|date=24 December 2009 |title=Big celebration for Kanthaswamy |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/big-celebration-for-kanthaswamy-news-tamil-kkfrhdfhdea.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022060604/http://www.sify.com/movies/big-celebration-for-kanthaswamy-news-tamil-kkfrhdfhdea.html |archivedate=22 October 2012 |df= }}</ref>\n\n===2010\u20132014===\nVikram then featured in [[Mani Ratnam]]'s bilingual films ''[[Raavanan]]'' and ''[[Raavan]]'', inspired by the ancient [[Sanskrit]] epic [[Ramayana]], with Vikram featuring as the tribal leader, Veeraiya, in the Tamil version and the cop, Dev Pratap Sharma, in the Hindi version of the films, which were shot simultaneously.<ref name=\"ravsifint\">{{cite web |author=Sreedhar, Sridevi |date=10 June 2010 |title=I am flying, thrilled and intoxicated: Vikram |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/i-am-flying-thrilled-and-intoxicated-vikram-news-tamil-kkfq0xhegdc.html |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110724144159/http://www.sify.com/movies/i-am-flying-thrilled-and-intoxicated-vikram-news-tamil-kkfq0xhegdc.html |archivedate=24 July 2011 |df= }}</ref> Vikram revealed that changes between the two characters during filming took up to 45 minutes, with [[Abhishek Bachchan]] playing the tribal leader in the Hindi version, whilst [[Prithviraj Sukumaran|Prithviraj]] played the cop in the Tamil version, with [[Aishwarya Rai]] also in the cast.<ref name=\"mint\"/> Vikram was initially apprehensive, because both roles were to be shot almost simultaneously, but revealed that he succeeded by showing differences in his body language and expressions.<ref name=\"diffs\">{{cite web|author=Rangarajan, Malathi |date=6 May 2010 |title=\u2018Raavanan\u2019, a re-incarnation |work=The Hindu |accessdate=7 January 2011 |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article423184.ece |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100903110236/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article423184.ece |archivedate= 3 September 2010 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"diffstwo\">{{cite web|date=13 June 2010|title=I had the arrogance for it: Vikram|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=7 August 2011|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-06-13/news-interviews/28285463_1_vikram-mani-ratnam-anti-hero}}</ref> Vikram revealed that he and Abhishek Bachchan played the roles in the respective versions without inspiration from one another. Despite being a non-speaker and making his debut in Hindi, he dubbed his lines in the language, remarking jovially that it was the \"most difficult thing in the world\".<ref name=\"ubb\">{{cite web|author=Ramsubramaniam, Nikhil|date=9 June 2010|title=\"Abhishek has been the best co-star I have ever worked with till date\"&nbsp;\u2013 Vikram|publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|accessdate=7 August 2011|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/features/2010/06/09/6336/}}{{dead link|date=October 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"rediffraavnan\">{{cite web|author=N, Patcy |date=17 June 2010 |title=When Vikram picked up Abhishek and threw him! |publisher=[[Rediff.com]] |accessdate=7 August 2011 |url=http://movies.rediff.com/slide-show/2010/jun/17/slide-show-1-vikram-on-raavan.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110410043255/http://movies.rediff.com/slide-show/2010/jun/17/slide-show-1-vikram-on-raavan.htm |archivedate=10 April 2011 |df= }}</ref> After promotions at the [[Cannes Film Festival]] and a premiere at [[Leicester Square]] in [[London]], the two versions and the dubbed Telugu version released simultaneously in 2,200 screens worldwide and took a big opening on day one, earning 20 crores.<ref name=\"raavanpremiere\">{{cite web|date=18 June 2010 |title=Raavan has a star-studded premiere in London |work=The Hindu |accessdate=7 August 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/2010/06/18/stories/2010061855652200.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100721215342/http://www.hindu.com/2010/06/18/stories/2010061855652200.htm |archivedate=21 July 2010 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"raavanopening\">{{cite web|date=19 June 2010 |title=\u2018Raavan\u2019 earns Rs 20 crore worldwide on opening day |work=[[Deccan Herald]] |accessdate=7 August 2011 |url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/76426/raavan-earns-rs-20-crore.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110630151022/http://www.deccanherald.com/content/76426/raavan-earns-rs-20-crore.html |archivedate=30 June 2011 |df= }}</ref> The Tamil version, ''Raavanan'' won rave reviews from critics, with ''[[The Hindu]]'' calling it a \"master stroke\" and claiming that Vikram \"raises the bar higher with every venture\". The critic cited that \"emotions of love, animus, anguish and joy dance on his face in quick succession\", concluding that \"Vikram lifts the role to an admirable level\".<ref name=\"raavananhin\">{{cite web|author=Rangarajan, Malathi |date=25 June 2010 |title=A masterstroke yet again&nbsp;\u2013 Raavanan |work=The Hindu |accessdate=7 August 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2010/06/25/stories/2010062550400201.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100701032556/http://www.hindu.com/fr/2010/06/25/stories/2010062550400201.htm |archivedate= 1 July 2010 |df= }}</ref> The critic from Sify labelled it as an \"astonishing portrayal\", while the critic from the ''[[Hindustan Times]]'' praised Vikram's \"ability to get into Veeraiya's skin and emote with conviction\".<ref name=\"raavanantimes\">{{cite web|author=Bhaskaran, Gauthaman |date=19 June 2010 |title=Gautaman Bhaskaran's Review: Raavanan |work=[[Hindustan Times]] |accessdate=7 August 2011 |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Gautaman-Bhaskaran-s-Review-Raavanan/Article1-560002.aspx |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100627152149/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Gautaman-Bhaskaran-s-Review-Raavanan/Article1-560002.aspx |archivedate=27 June 2010 |df= }}</ref> The Tamil version consequently went on to become a commercial success, with Vikram's performance leading to him winning the [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor - Tamil|Filmfare Award for Best Tamil Actor]] among other accolades.<ref name=\"raavananhhit\">{{cite web|author=Reddy, Krithika |date=2 July 2010 |title=Rock and role |work=The Hindu |accessdate=7 August 2011 |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article496828.ece |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100814123146/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article496828.ece |archivedate=14 August 2010 |df= }}</ref> In contrast, the Hindi version fetched mixed reviews, with critics agreeing that Vikram's performance as the tribal leader was more convincing than Bachchan's. [[Baradwaj Rangan]], writing for ''[[The New Indian Express]]'' rated the film 4/5 and said: \"Raavan falls for Sita (and vice versa) in an intriguingly idiosyncratic take on the Ramayana&nbsp;\u2013 if you can get past the lead performances, that is\".<ref>{{cite web|first=Baradwaj |last=Rangan |title='Raavan' Review |work=[[The New Indian Express]] |url=http://baradwajrangan.wordpress.com/2010/06/19/review-raavan/ |accessdate=19 June 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100621082438/http://baradwajrangan.wordpress.com/2010/06/19/review-raavan/ |archivedate=21 June 2010 |df= }}</ref> Whereas, [[Taran Adarsh]], writing for [[Bollywood Hungama]] rated it 1.5/5 and said: \"On the whole, ''Raavan'' is a king-sized disappointment, in terms of content\" though mentioning that Vikram was \"first-rate, although the role isn't substantial enough\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Adarsh |first=Taran |title=Raavan: Movie Review |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/14148/index.html |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=18 June 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100623075355/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/14148/index.html |archivedate=23 June 2010 |df= }}</ref> ''Raavan'' subsequently went on to become a surprise flop at the Indian box office.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hits continue to evade Bollywood as ''Raavan'' flops |url=http://movies.rediff.com/report/2010/jun/28/box-office-raavan-flops.htm |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=8 July 2010 |date=28 June 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100701042457/http://movies.rediff.com/report/2010/jun/28/box-office-raavan-flops.htm |archivedate= 1 July 2010 |df= }}</ref> The film was also screened at the [[Venice Film Festival]] and the [[Busan International Film Festival]], with Vikram in attendance.<ref name=\"venice\">{{cite web|author=Sangeetha|date=11 September 2010|title=Vikram: I was never so excited|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=7 August 2011|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-09-11/news-interviews/28215529_1_vikram-chiyaan-suhasini}}</ref>\n[[File:Tamil actor & UN Habitat Youth Envoy Vikram.jpg|thumb|Vikram in 2011 ]]\nAfter two years of discussions, Vikram began a film under the direction of [[Selvaraghavan]] in a project dubbed by the media as ''Sindubad''. The film began shoot and completed a schedule by early 2010 in the [[Himalayas]] with [[Swati Reddy]] appearing as the female lead. However, the film was reported to be momentarily shelved and subsequently never took off again after the producer Singanamala Ramesh walked out.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/nov-12-02/selvaraghavan-vikram-10-11-12.html |title=Why Did Selvaraghavan And Vikram's Association Break? |publisher=Behindwoods |date=10 November 2012 |accessdate=12 June 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130907204401/http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/nov-12-02/selvaraghavan-vikram-10-11-12.html |archivedate= 7 September 2013 |df= }}</ref> Vikram then agreed terms to feature in [[Vikram Kumar]]'s ''24'', produced by Mohan Natarajan, with [[Ileana D'Cruz]] signed on to play the female lead role. The film progressed briefly with shots being canned in caves, before the director was ousted from the project, cancelling the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/dec-09-04/vikram-vikram-kumar-ileana-21-12-09.html |title=Vikram & Vikram get busy! |publisher=Behindwoods |date=21 December 2009 |accessdate=12 June 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131002113828/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/dec-09-04/vikram-vikram-kumar-ileana-21-12-09.html |archivedate= 2 October 2013 |df= }}</ref> Vikram then also shot briefly for a third successive shelved project directed by [[Boopathy Pandian]] for the same producer, featuring him in the role of an investigative cop; however the film failed to progress and instead Natarajan financed Vikram's next film.<ref>{{cite web|author=V Lakshmi |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-02-09/news-interviews/31040985_1_ileana-producer-mohan-natarajan-telugu-film-industry |title=Ileana refuses to return advance? |work=The Times of India |date=9 February 2012 |accessdate=12 June 2013}}</ref> His 2011 release ''[[Deiva Thirumagal]]'', directed by [[A. L. Vijay]], saw Vikram portray a father with a [[developmental disability]] having the mental maturity of a seven-year-old. To prepare for the role, Vikram visited homes for the mentally challenged such as Vidya Sagar and Vidya Sudha for a month, watching their body language and taking notes.<ref name=\"dtmbestfather\">{{cite web|author=Subramanian, Anupama |date=11 July 2011 |title=I\u2019m the best father: Chiyaan Vikram |work=[[Deccan Chronicle]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/channels/showbiz/kollywood/i%E2%80%99m-best-father-chiyaan-vikram-092 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110817101018/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/channels/showbiz/kollywood/i%E2%80%99m-best-father-chiyaan-vikram-092 |archivedate=17 August 2011 }}</ref> He also communicated with the patients, to pick up the nuances of people with impaired speech. Vikram has since gone on to describe his role as Krishna as the best character he has ever portrayed.<ref name=\"dtmbest\">{{cite web|author=Jeshi, K |date=28 August 2010 |title=Sitting pretty |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article600074.ece |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100902145635/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article600074.ece |archivedate= 2 September 2010 |df= }}</ref> The film, which also featured [[Sara Arjun]], [[Anushka Shetty]] and [[Amala Paul]] in supporting roles, opened to predominantly positive reviews from critics and enjoyed commercial success at the box office.<ref name=\"dtmsuccess\">{{cite web|date=19 July 2011|title=Deiva Thiirumagal comes in for praise|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-07-19/news-interviews/29790374_1_chiyaan-vikram-deiva-thiirumagal-film}}</ref> The reviewer from [[The Deccan Chronicle]] described that the film was \"Vikram's show all the way\" and that \"his rendition of a mentally-challenged man trying to cope with the everyday realities of raising a child is a work of art\", praising his \"fiery, complex performance as one of the more viciously honest depictions of mental illness cinema has seen\".<ref name=\"dtmdc\">{{cite web | url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/channels/showbiz/kollywood/deivathirumagal-it-vikram-all-way-008 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121011205328/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/channels/showbiz/kollywood/deivathirumagal-it-vikram-all-way-008 | archivedate=11 October 2012 | title=Deivathirumagal: It is Vikram all the way | work=[[Deccan Chronicle]] | date=16 July 2011 | accessdate=31 July 2011 | author=Subramanian, Anupama}}</ref> Similarly, another critic described that the on-screen chemistry between Vikram and his daughter, played by Sara Arjun, is \"magic\" and their performances \"are sure to leave a lump in your throat\".<ref name=\"dtmtoi\">{{cite web|author=Narayanan, Venkateswaren |date=17 July 2011 |title=Deiva Thirumagal |work=[[The Times of India]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/tamil/movie-reviews/Deiva-Thirumagal/movie-review/9256649.cms |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121106035815/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/tamil/movie-reviews/Deiva-Thirumagal/movie-review/9256649.cms |archivedate= 6 November 2012 |df= }}</ref> The critic from ''The Hindu'' praised the film and Vikram's performance, but analysed that \"a problem arises only when you stop looking at Krishna as a character, and begin to see him as Vikram, the hero\" and that Vikram should have \"underplayed a little here and there and it would have worked better\".<ref name=\"dtmhind\">{{cite web|author=Rangarajan, Malathi |date=16 July 2011 |title=Deiva Thirumagal: a sensitive poem on celluloid |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article2233163.ece |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110720135157/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article2233163.ece |archivedate=20 July 2011 |df= }}</ref> However, Vikram once again completed a sweep of the top acting awards that year, with further recognition at the Vijay and [[Filmfare Awards South|Filmfare Awards]].<ref>{{cite news| url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-07-08/news-interviews/32588512_1_aadukalam-video-pranayam | title=The 59th Idea Filmfare Awards 2011(South)| date=8 July 2012}}</ref>\n\nVikram next featured in ''[[Rajapattai]]'' (2011), alongside [[Deeksha Seth]], under the direction of [[Suseenthiran]], where he played a [[henchman]] trying to get a break in the [[Tamil cinema|Tamil film]] industry.<ref name=\"rajap\">{{cite web|date=26 July 2011 |title=Vikram's role in Raja Pattai |publisher=Behindwoods |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/jul-11-04/vikram-raja-pattai-26-07-11.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110926094022/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/jul-11-04/vikram-raja-pattai-26-07-11.html |archivedate=26 September 2011 |df= }}</ref> The film opened to mixed reviews from critics in December 2011 and performed below expectations at the box office. Vikram also completed half of a fantasy period film during 2011, ''Karikalan'', in which he played [[Karikala Chola]], a Tamil king who ruled in 270 BC, opposite [[Zarine Khan]], under the direction of graphics director Kannan, but the film was later shelved owing to production troubles.<ref name=\"karikalan\">{{cite web|date=13 May 2011 |title=Vikram & Zarine in Karikalan |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/vikram-zarine-in-karikalan-news-tamil-lfnlLCijcdb.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110819072713/http://www.sify.com/movies/vikram-zarine-in-karikalan-news-tamil-lfnlLCijcdb.html |archivedate=19 August 2011 |df= }}</ref> He then appeared in his second project with director [[A. L. Vijay|Vijay]], portraying the lead role of a blinded [[Research and Analysis Wing|RAW agent]] in the action-thriller, ''[[Thaandavam]]''. The film, which also featured [[Anushka Shetty]], [[Amy Jackson]] and [[Lakshmi Rai]] in pivotal roles, opened to mixed reviews in September 2012.<ref name=\"vijayamy\">{{cite web|author=Ramanujam, Srinivasa|date=10 July 2011|title=Amy in Vikram's next?|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-07-10/news-interviews/29757850_1_amy-jackson-hindi-version-vikram-vijay}}</ref> For his role of a blind man, Vikram trained under noted [[human echolocation]] specialist [[Daniel Kish]], with the latter also playing a cameo in the film.<ref>{{cite news|agency=TNN |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-09-10/news-interviews/33736244_1_vikram-thaandavam-daniel-kish |title=Vikram gets trained by Daniel Kish |work=The Times of India |date=10 September 2012 |accessdate=12 June 2013}}</ref> A critic from Sify.com noted that it was \"Vikram and him alone who diverts your attention from the film's little logical script flaws and spellbinds you with an endearing act that is Thaandavam's biggest strength\";<ref>{{cite web|title=Thaandavam |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/thaandavam-review-tamil-15008711.html |publisher=Sify |accessdate=28 September 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131218212437/http://www.sify.com/movies/thaandavam-review-tamil-15008711.html |archivedate=18 December 2013 |df= }}</ref> subsequently, the film did average business commercially. The actor was next seen portraying the title role in [[Bejoy Nambiar]]'s bilingual ''[[David (2013 Hindi film)|David]]'', which released with different cast members in Hindi and Tamil. Vikram remained the only common lead actor in the versions, with his segment playing out a love story between a careless drunkard fisherman and a mute girl played by [[Isha Sherwani]]. While the Tamil version opened to predominantly positive review,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/south-review-tamil-david/20130201.htm |title=Review: David is a masterpiece |publisher=Rediff |date=1 February 2013 |accessdate=12 June 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130517035734/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/south-review-tamil-david/20130201.htm |archivedate=17 May 2013 |df= }}</ref> the Hindi film also won mixed reviews, with both films performing average business at the box office.\n\n===2015\u2013present===\nVikram signed on to collaborate again with [[S. Shankar|Shankar]] for ''[[I (film)|I]]'', a romantic thriller opposite [[Amy Jackson]], in early 2012.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-07-10/news-interviews/32605619_1_amy-jackson-aascar-ravichandran-vikram |title=Amy Jackson to romance Vikram in I |work=The Times of India |date=10 July 2012 |accessdate=15 July 2012}}</ref> Following hushed production developments, it was revealed that the actor would sport four significantly different looks in the film: a body builder, a beast, a model and a hunchback. He put on weight to portray the bodybuilder, sticking to a diet of protein and coffee, to ensure his muscles are defined on screen. Vikram subsequently lost weight to portray a model, before shaving his head and reducing his weight to 56 kilograms to portray the crippled hunchback.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/vikram-betting-on-i/article6782719.ece |title=Vikram betting on I's success with Pongal release |work=The Hindu |date=13 January 2015 |accessdate=18 January 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160115234452/http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/vikram-betting-on-i/article6782719.ece |archivedate=15 January 2016 |df= }}</ref> He changed his physique by eating small meals of egg whites and apples instead of regular food intakes, while engaging in an intensive weight loss regime to become thin. The cast and crew of the film reportedly struggled to recognise the actor at times, while he also stayed away from the media for close to a year when sporting the look.<ref>{{cite web|author=Subhash K. Jha |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/interview/vikram-i-was-really-tough/20150114.htm |title=Vikram: I was looking pathetic during the shooting of I |publisher=Rediff |date=14 January 2015 |accessdate=18 January 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150118194829/http://www.rediff.com/movies/interview/vikram-i-was-really-tough/20150114.htm |archivedate=18 January 2015 |df= }}</ref> Taking almost three years for production, Vikram described the film \"as the toughest he has ever done\" and regularly suffered [[folliculitis]] as a result of the prosthetic make-up he had to wear.<ref name=\"caravan\"/> The film opened amidst much expectation in January 2015 to mixed reviews, though critics gave Vikram's portrayal of Lingesan, unanimously positive reviews. A critic from Times of India noted: \"Vikram bowls you over with a heart-wrenching performance whether he is handsome or disfigured\", while The Hindu added his transformation was \"laudable\", and that \"Vikram wins hearts as the earnest-to-boot gym rat and as the strapping new model on the block, he floors the audience with his performance as Koonan, the deformed hunchback\".<ref>{{cite news|author=Iyer, Meena |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-review/I/movie-review/45888402.cms |title=Movie Review:I |work=The Times of India |date=14 January 2015 |accessdate=18 January 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150117173150/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-review/I/movie-review/45888402.cms |archivedate=17 January 2015 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Rajendra, Ranjani |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/review-of-i-predictable-beauty-and-the-beast-tale/article6789004.ece |title=Predictable beauty and the beast tale |work=The Hindu |date=14 January 2015 |accessdate=18 January 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201091213/http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/review-of-i-predictable-beauty-and-the-beast-tale/article6789004.ece |archivedate= 1 February 2015 |df= }}</ref> Similarly, Rediff.com noted the actor \"is truly impressive and deserves much applause\", while Sify.com added he \"lived the role\".<ref>{{cite web|author=Saraswathi, S |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-vikram-i-is-definitely-a-pongal-treat/20150114.htm |title=Vikram's I is definitely a Pongal treat |publisher=Rediff.com |date=14 January 2015 |accessdate=18 January 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150117175541/http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-vikram-i-is-definitely-a-pongal-treat/20150114.htm |archivedate=17 January 2015 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/i-review-tamil-15058840.html |title=Movie Review:I |publisher=Sify.com |date=14 January 2015 |accessdate=18 January 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150117174107/http://www.sify.com/movies/i-review-tamil-15058840.html |archivedate=17 January 2015 |df= }}</ref> Despite mixed reviews, ''I'' performed well at the box office, as well as becoming the most successful Tamil film of all time in Kerala.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/vikram-on-10-enradhukulla-movie/article7774642.ece|title=Vikram on 10 Enradhukulla movie|author=sudhir srinivasan|work=The Hindu|accessdate=2 May 2016}}</ref> He then worked on [[Vijay Milton]]'s road-thriller, ''[[10 Enradhukulla]]'' (2015), which featured him as an unnamed race driver who goes on a road trip through [[India]]. Paired opposite [[Samantha Ruth Prabhu|Samantha]], the film opened to mixed reviews and did not perform well at the box office. A critic from Sify.com however, noted that Vikram \"breathes life to his role and his energy level is highly infectious\", adding that \"the way he smiles, dances and fights is a treat for his fans\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/10-enradhukulla-review--pkvqS2bcfcaid.html |title=Review : 10 Enradhukulla |work=Sify |accessdate=2 May 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160129085457/http://www.sify.com/movies/10-enradhukulla-review--pkvqS2bcfcaid.html |archivedate=29 January 2016 |df= }}</ref> Likewise, a critic from The Hindu criticised the film's script, adding that \"it's hard to see Vikram in this fluff\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-reviews/10-enradhukulla-a-slipshod-road-movie/article7790285.ece |title=10 Enradhukulla: A slipshod road movie |author=Baradwaj Rangan |work=The Hindu |accessdate=2 May 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160505013158/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-reviews/10-enradhukulla-a-slipshod-road-movie/article7790285.ece |archivedate= 5 May 2016 |df= }}</ref> Vikram later appeared in ''[[Iru Mugan]]'', a science fiction action film directed by [[Anand Shankar]], featuring him alongside [[Nayanthara]] and [[Nithya Menen]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Im-crazy-when-it-comes-to-acting-Vikram/articleshow/49701028.cms |title=I\u2019m crazy when it comes to acting: Vikram |work=The Times of India |accessdate=2 May 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151110085501/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Im-crazy-when-it-comes-to-acting-Vikram/articleshow/49701028.cms |archivedate=10 November 2015 |df= }}</ref>\n\nHis forthcoming films are [[Gautham Menon]]'s ''[[Dhruva Natchathiram]]'', followed by a sequel to ''Saamy'' directed by Hari,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/saamy-2-vikram-sequel-irumugan-garuda-upcoming/1/733634.html |title=Saamy 2: Vikram's film to go on floors after he completes Garuda |work=India Today |date=6 August 2016 |accessdate=13 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160822061519/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/saamy-2-vikram-sequel-irumugan-garuda-upcoming/1/733634.html |archivedate=22 August 2016 |df= }}</ref> and ''Sketch'', to be directed by Vijay Chander.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/Vikram%E2%80%99s-next-film-to-roll-from-December/article16668274.ece |title=Vikram's next film to roll from December |work=The Hindu |accessdate=23 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161123210513/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/Vikram%E2%80%99s-next-film-to-roll-from-December/article16668274.ece |archivedate=23 November 2016 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.top10cinema.com/article/42106/vikrams-sketch-with-vijay-announced |title=Vikram\u2019s \u2018Sketch\u2019 with Vijay announced |date=8 April 2017 |work=Top 10 Cinema |access-date=9 April 2017 |language=en-US |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170410214146/https://www.top10cinema.com/article/42106/vikrams-sketch-with-vijay-announced |archivedate=10 April 2017 |df= }}</ref>\n\n==Other work==\n\n===Film and television work===\nApart from acting, Vikram has also been a part of other film-making processes with credits as a playback singer and as an assistant director. In 2000, Vikram and actress [[Meena Durairaj|Meena]] launched a pop album titled ''Kadhalism'', which the pair would sing and appear in music videos for, although the project was completed without much promotion.<ref name=\"kadhalism\">{{cite web\n |year=2000 \n |title=Tamil cinema 2000 \n |publisher=CinemaToday2.com \n |accessdate=31 July 2011 \n |url=http://cinematoday2.itgo.com/44Hot%20News%20Just%20for%20U.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120324015314/http://cinematoday2.itgo.com/44Hot%20News%20Just%20for%20U.htm \n |archivedate=24 March 2012 \n |df= \n}}</ref> Following the success of [[Bharathwaj]]'s music for Vikram's 2002 film ''[[Gemini (2002 Tamil film)|Gemini]]'', Vikram sang a version of the hit song \"O Podu!\" for the extended version of the album.<ref name=\"geminimusic\"/> During the making of ''[[Kanthaswamy]]'' in 2009, the music composer [[Devi Sri Prasad]] had asked Vikram to sing a few rough tracks during the film's song composition in [[Malaysia]]. The producers were impressed with his voice and Vikram ended up singing four songs in the film.<ref name=\"singer\">{{cite web|author=Kumar, Ashok |date=14 February 2009 |title=Vikram, now a playback singer too |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/2009/02/14/stories/2009021458610200.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121110120148/http://www.hindu.com/2009/02/14/stories/2009021458610200.htm |archivedate=10 November 2012 |df= }}</ref> Furthermore, Vikram also recorded all four tracks in the Telugu version of the album titled ''Mallana''.<ref name=\"singermallana\">{{cite web\n |date=6 February 2009 \n |title=Vikram shows singers the door \n |publisher=Behindwoods \n |accessdate=31 July 2011 \n |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/feb-09-01/vikram-06-02-09.html \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715081820/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/feb-09-01/vikram-06-02-09.html \n |archivedate=15 July 2011 \n |df= \n}}</ref> He then went on to sing for a film he was unrelated to, by lending five different voices in \"Meghame\" for [[G. V. Prakash Kumar]]'s album in ''[[Madrasapattinam]]''.<ref name=\"madras\">{{cite web\n |date=6 March 2010 \n |title=Vikram's five different voices \n |publisher=Behindwoods \n |accessdate=31 July 2011 \n |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/mar-10-02/vikram-madrasapattinam-09-03-10.html \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100819132337/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/mar-10-02/vikram-madrasapattinam-09-03-10.html \n |archivedate=19 August 2010 \n |df= \n}}</ref> He sang two further songs under Prakash Kumar for his ''[[Deiva Thirumagal]]'', singing in the voice of his character, an adult with the maturity of a six-year-old.<ref name=\"vijayvikram\">{{cite web|date=7 February 2011|title=Vikram sings for his next|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-02-07/news-interviews/28546173_1_vikram-voice-song}}</ref> In 2011, he sang the song \"Laddu Laddu\" for his film ''[[Rajapattai]]'', under composer [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]'s direction.<ref>{{cite web|title=Top 10 songs |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-slide-shows/movie-4/top-ten-songs-dec-16/rajapattai.html |publisher=Behindwoods |accessdate=19 December 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120107191935/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-slide-shows/movie-4/top-ten-songs-dec-16/rajapattai.html |archivedate= 7 January 2012 |df= }}</ref> Vikram announced his own production company Reel Life Entertainment in July 2009 and announced that [[M. Sasikumar|Sasikumar]] would direct his first film, the action thriller ''[[Easan]]'', featuring [[Samudrakani]], [[Vaibhav]], [[Abhinaya (actress)|Abhinaya]] and [[Aparnaa Bajpai]].<ref name=\"sasivikram\">{{cite web|date=19 November 2009 |title=Vikram starts his Sasikumar film! |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/vikram-starts-his-sasikumar-film-news-tamil-kkfro8jcjab.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110724144411/http://www.sify.com/movies/vikram-starts-his-sasikumar-film-news-tamil-kkfro8jcjab.html |archivedate=24 July 2011 |df= }}</ref> However, after 90% of the shoot had been completed, Vikram pulled out of the venture, citing that Sasikumar had overshot his budget and the director eventually bought and released the film.<ref name=\"parteways\">{{cite web\n |date=6 September 2010 \n |title=Sasikumar and Vikram part ways \n |publisher=Behindwoods \n |accessdate=31 July 2011 \n |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/sep-10-02/sasi-kumar-vikram-samudrakani-06-09-10.html \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111206014208/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/sep-10-02/sasi-kumar-vikram-samudrakani-06-09-10.html \n |archivedate= 6 December 2011 \n |df= \n}}</ref> The actor, however, was later listed as one of the three producers for his 2013 bilingual film, ''David'', thereby making his debut in film financing. Vikram has also worked as the assistant director under [[Shafi (director)|Shafi]] in ''[[Majaa]]'', and has mentioned that he would like to direct a film in the future.<ref name=\"admajaa\"/>\n\n===Philanthropy===\nVikram has promoted various social causes with several of his charity works being linked to characters he had portrayed in his films. He has been a brand ambassador of Sanjeevani Trust and a school for special children Vidya Sudha, which he stayed at during the making of ''Deiva Thirumagal''.<ref name=\"dtmbest\"/> Moreover, he has had a long-term association since the making of his film ''[[Kasi (film)|Kasi]]'' with the Kasi Eye Care, which does free eye surgeries for the poor.<ref name=\"vikrampoverty\">{{cite news|date=12 April 2011|title=Vikram wants a poverty free world|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=21 February 2011|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-04-12/news-interviews/29409638_1_chiyaan-vikram-envoys-brand-ambassador}}</ref> Vikram has also set up The Vikram Foundation through his fan club to provide heart operations for the poor, educate poor children and rehabilitate victims from natural disasters. Every year, Vikram has celebrated his birthday doing charity work across [[Tamil Nadu]] and in 2008, he organised a camp where a thousand of his fans pledged their eyes in an eye donation appeal.<ref name=\"vikramnet\">{{cite web|title=The Vikram Foundation |url=http://www.chiyaanvikram.net:80/socialview.php?cid=3&ct |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080513222141/http://www.chiyaanvikram.net/socialview.php?cid=3&ct |archivedate=13 May 2008 |publisher=chiyaanvikram.net |accessdate=7 November 2011 |url-status=dead  }}</ref>\n\nHe has lent his support for the Chennai-based charity ''The Banyan'', and appeared in the charity musical [[Netru, Indru, Naalai]] directed by Mani Ratnam for the cause.<ref name=\"ninbanyan\">{{cite web|title=Mani Ratnam to direct Star Vijay's extravaganza |url=http://inhome.rediff.com/movies/2005/jun/15mani.htm |work=Rediff Movies |publisher=Rediff |accessdate=7 November 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715165248/http://inhome.rediff.com/movies/2005/jun/15mani.htm |archivedate=15 July 2011 |df= }}</ref> The actor also starred in the 2010 \"[[Mile Sur Mera Tumhara]]\" music video on national integration alongside a bevy of Indian actors and musicians, describing the experience as \"phenomenal\".<ref name=\"phil\">{{cite web|author=Suresh, Taranya|date=25 February 2010|title=Calling Raavan|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-02-25/news-interviews/28123869_1_raavan-mani-ratnam-films}}</ref> In 2011, Vikram was selected as a Youth Envoy for the [[United Nations Human Settlements Programme]] with his aim being to spread awareness about the statutes of U.N. Habitat which include urban stabilisation and to help formulate plans for effective water management, slum eradication and women and youth empowerment.<ref name=\"nienvoy\">{{cite web|title=Vikram is the youth envoy of UN Habitat |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-south-vikram-is-the-youth-envoy-of-un-habitat/20110413.htm |work=Rediff Movies |publisher=Rediff |accessdate=7 November 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111125054404/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-south-vikram-is-the-youth-envoy-of-un-habitat/20110413.htm |archivedate=25 November 2011 |df= }}</ref> Soon after, he announced two further social projects, \"Karka Kasadara\" and \"Patchai Puratchi\", with the former being to identify school and college dropouts and help them to stand on their own feet, while the latter was about planting trees with an aim to make [[Chennai]] go green.<ref name=\"vikramun\"/> In 2016, he produced and directed the video to the flood relief anthem [[Spirit of Chennai]], as a tribute to the city's volunteers following the [[2015 South Indian floods]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/celebrating-the-spirit-of-chennai/article8083351.ece |title=Celebrating the spirit of Chennai |author=Ranjani Rajendra |work=The Hindu |accessdate=2 May 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160322103414/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/celebrating-the-spirit-of-chennai/article8083351.ece |archivedate=22 March 2016 |df= }}</ref>\n\n==In the media==\n\nVikram is a prolific [[method actor]], being often compared akin to Hollywood's [[Christian Bale]]. Since the success of ''[[Sethu (film)|Sethu]]'', Vikram's intense performances and variety of roles have received critical acclaim.<ref name=\"intense\">{{cite web|author=Reddy, Krithika |date=9 July 2011 |title=Step By Step |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=7 January 2011 |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article2214157.ece |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714061449/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article2214157.ece |archivedate=14 July 2011 |df= }}</ref> His performances as a rogue turned mentally ill patient in ''[[Sethu (film)|Sethu]]'', a gravedigger with autism spectrum disorder in Bala's ''[[Pithamagan]]'', a [[Brahmin]] lawyer with multiple personality disorder in ''[[Anniyan]]'' and a mentally challenged adult with the maturity of a six-year-old boy in ''[[Deiva Thirumagal]]'' are all roles in which he played a mentally affected man, with Vikram mentioning that he does such roles to reinvent himself on screen.<ref name=\"sonvikram\">{{cite web|author=Nagarajan, Saraswathy |date=27 March 2006 |title=V for Vikram |work=The Hindu |accessdate=7 January 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/mp/2006/03/27/stories/2006032700220500.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110713144035/http://www.hindu.com/mp/2006/03/27/stories/2006032700220500.htm |archivedate=13 July 2011 |df= }}</ref> Furthermore, Vikram has enjoyed a large fan following in [[Andhra Pradesh]] as a result of a series of successful dubbed [[Telugu language|Telugu]] films with ''Aparichitudu'', dubbed from his Tamil film ''Anniyan'', being among the most successful Telugu films of 2005. All his films are thus released in Telugu soon after their original release in Tamil, while ''Anniyan'' was also dubbed in Hindi as ''Aparichit''.<ref name=\"mint\"/> He has also enjoyed success in [[Kerala]], where his films have demanded large box office openings akin to Malayalam film stars.<ref name=\"caravan\"/> In 2004, Vikram participated in a live stadium stage event organised by producer [[P. L. Thenappan]] titled \"Vikram Mega Nite\". The event, held in [[Singapore]], attracted several hundreds of his South East Asian fans and was held in the form of a stage musical.<ref name=\"starnite\">{{cite web|author=Pillai, Sreedhar |date=9 February 2004 |title=Valentine's Day Special |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=8 April 2014 |url=http://www.hindu.com/mp/2004/02/09/stories/2004020900030200.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110514071438/http://www.hindu.com/mp/2004/02/09/stories/2004020900030200.htm |archivedate=14 May 2011 |df= }}</ref>\n\nHis pan-Indian popularity has also prompted him to be regularly considered for brand endorsements. In 2005, Vikram was signed as [[Coca-Cola]]'s brand ambassador in [[Tamil Nadu]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/todays-paper/tp-marketing/actor-vikram-is-new-coke-brand-ambassador/article2174957.ece |title=Actor Vikram is new Coke brand ambassador |work=Business Line |date=19 April 2005 |accessdate=13 July 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160115234452/http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/todays-paper/tp-marketing/actor-vikram-is-new-coke-brand-ambassador/article2174957.ece |archivedate=15 January 2016 |df= }}</ref> He has been the ambassador for [[Brooke Bond|Brooke Bond 3 Roses]], [[Manappuram General Finance and Leasing|Manappuram General Finance and Leasing Ltd]] and Josco Jewellers since 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.webindia123.com/news/articles/India/20100928/1596592.html |title=Vikram and Trisha brand ambassadors for Brooke Bond |publisher=News Web India123.com |date=27 September 2010 |accessdate=13 July 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160115234452/http://news.webindia123.com/news/articles/India/20100928/1596592.html |archivedate=15 January 2016 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chiyaanvikramfans.in/2010/05/vikram-brand-ambassador-for-manappuram.html |title=Vikram Brand Ambassador for Manappuram General Finance and Leasing Ltd |publisher=Chiyaan Vikram Fans.in |date=6 May 2010 |accessdate=13 July 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150713180706/http://www.chiyaanvikramfans.in/2010/05/vikram-brand-ambassador-for-manappuram.html |archivedate=13 July 2015 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bpu1egteTGM |title=Chiyaan Vikram in Josco Jewellers Complete Ad 2010-HQ |publisher=YouTube |date=9 November 2010 |accessdate=18 July 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141207082702/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bpu1egteTGM |archivedate= 7 December 2014 |df= }}</ref> In 2015, Vikram has endorsed Big Deal TV, a celebrity-driven home shopping channel.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ytalkies.com/kollywood-film-news/vikram-is-the-brand-ambassador-for-big-deal-tv |title=Vikram is the Brand Ambassador for Big Deal TV |publisher=Y Talikies |date=4 June 2015 |accessdate=13 July 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160115234452/http://www.ytalkies.com/kollywood-film-news/vikram-is-the-brand-ambassador-for-big-deal-tv |archivedate=15 January 2016 |df= }}</ref>\n\nHe is amongst the most decorated actors in terms of awards in the history of [[Tamil cinema]]. He holds a [[National Film Award (India)|National Film Award]] for Best Actor; a feat only matched by four other actors in Tamil films. Moreover, Vikram holds seven [[Filmfare Awards South]], with the tally being only second to [[Kamal Haasan]] who has ten wins. In 2010 his film ''[[Raavan]]'' was promoted at the [[Cannes Film Festival]] and then screened at [[Venice Film Festival]] and the [[Busan International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"venice\"/> Within weeks of release, ''[[Deiva Thirumagal]]'' was sent to the [[Asia Pacific Screen Awards]] after it was nominated by the [[Film Federation of India]] and the National Film Development Corporation.<ref name=\"dtasa\">{{cite web|author=Lakshmi, V|date=1 August 2011|title=DT makes it to international film fest|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-08-01/news-interviews/29838201_1_international-film-tamil-film-national-film-development-corporation}}</ref> Vikram is also a recipient of the [[Kalaimamani|Kalaimamani Award]] from the [[Government of Tamil Nadu]] in 2004. Other recognitions includes a string of [[Cinema Express Awards]], [[Vijay Awards]] and [[Tamil Nadu State Film Awards]], including recognition in three different categories. In 2011, Vikram was awarded an honorary doctorate from Universit\u00e0 Popolare degli Studi di Milano (People's University of Milan) in the field of Fine Arts. Vikram accepted the title on 29 May 2011 and in his next release, ''Deiva Thirumagal'', he was credited as Dr. Chiyaan Vikram.<ref name=\"drvikram\">{{cite web|date=10 March 2011 |title=Vikram gets an honorary doctorate |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=7 January 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/vikram-gets-an-honorary-doctorate-news-tamil-ldknAujjafh.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110313023301/http://www.sify.com/movies/vikram-gets-an-honorary-doctorate-news-tamil-ldknAujjafh.html |archivedate=13 March 2011 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-06-01/news-interviews/29603366_1_honorary-doctorate-vikram-indian-cinema |title=Vikram turns Dr Vikram |work=The Times of India |author=Suresh Kavirayani |date=1 June 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cinema.pluz.in/galleries/kollywood/9451/vikram-honoured-with-doctorate.htm |title=Vikram Honoured With Doctorate |publisher=cinema.pluz.in |date=3 June 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927081021/http://cinema.pluz.in/galleries/kollywood/9451/vikram-honoured-with-doctorate.htm |archivedate=27 September 2013 |df= }}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nVikram met Shailaja Balakrishnan in the late 1980s and married her in 1992 at [[Guruvayoor]] in a mass wedding alongside dozens of couples.<ref name=\"vikramkerala\"/> The pair then had a low-key wedding ceremony conducted at the church at [[Loyola College, Chennai]].<ref name=\"caravan\"/> She hails from [[Thalassery]], [[Kerala]] and now works as a psychology teacher at a leading Chennai school.<ref name=\"teacher\">{{cite web|author=Jha, Subhash K. |date=18 May 2010 |title='Aishwarya's a hero, Abhishek a brat' |publisher=[[CNN-IBN|IBN]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/aishwaryas-a-hero-abhishek-a-brat/115603-8-66.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100521092254/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/aishwaryas-a-hero-abhishek-a-brat/115603-8-66.html |archivedate=21 May 2010 |df= }}</ref> Shailaja also worked with the team of ''[[Deiva Thirumagal]]'' by giving professional advice on how people with special needs are treated and helping develop the character played by Vikram.<ref name=\"shailajadt\">{{cite web|author=Ramanujam, Srinivasa|date=19 April 2011|title=Vikram's wife helps Deiva Thirumagan!|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-04-19/news-interviews/29446904_1_shailaja-actor-vikram-vijay}}</ref>\n\nThe couple has a daughter Akshita born in 1993 and a son Dhruv born in 1997.<ref name=\"sonvikram\"/><ref name=\"dhruv\">{{cite web |author=Vandhana |year=2014 |title=Vikram's son not debuting anytime soon |publisher=Silverscreen |accessdate=28 August 2014 |url=http://silverscreen.in/news/vikrams-son-debuting-anytime-soon/ |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140830134627/http://silverscreen.in/news/vikrams-son-debuting-anytime-soon/ |archivedate=30 August 2014 |df= }}</ref> His daughter married Manu Ranjith, the great-grandson of [[M. Karunanidhi]], on 30 October 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thenewsminute.com/article/akshita-manu-ranjith-wedding-vikram-s-daughter-gets-married-karunanidhi-s-great-grandson|title=Akshita-Manu Ranjith wedding: Vikram\u2019s daughter gets married to Karunanidhi\u2019s great grandson|date=1 November 2017|work=The News Minute|access-date=1 November 2017}}</ref> He lives near the beach in [[Besant Nagar]], Chennai and has stated that he would remain based in Chennai regardless of any offers in other regional films.<ref name=\"kanthaint\">{{cite web|author=Jyothsna |year=2009 |title=Vikram in a frank chat with behindwoods.com |publisher=Behindwoods |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.videos.behindwoods.com/videos-q1-09/actor-actress-interview/vikram.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110807045813/http://www.videos.behindwoods.com/videos-q1-09/actor-actress-interview/vikram.html |archivedate= 7 August 2011 |df= }}</ref>\n\nDhruv made his debut with ''[[Adithya Varma]]'' in the year 2019 which was the Tamil remake of the Telugu film ''[[Arjun Reddy]]''.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/dhruv-vikram-to-head-to-portugal-for-aditya-varma-song-shoot/articleshow/68749205.cms |title=Dhruv Vikram to head to Portugal for 'Aditya Varma' song shoot |date=6 April 2019 |work=[[The Times of India]] |access-date=8 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography and awards==\n\n===Filmography===\n{{Main|Vikram filmography}}\n\n===Awards and nominations===\n{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Vikram}}\n\n== Discography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20%;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:5%;\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Language\n! Song(s)\n! Composer\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Co-singer(s)\n! class=\"unsortable\" | {{Tooltip|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Shree (2002 film)|Shree]]''\n| 2002\n| Tamil\n| \"Yaamirukka Bayamein\"\n| {{sortname|T. S.|Muralidharan|nolink=1}}\n| [[Shankar Mahadevan]], [[Tippu (singer)|Tippu]]\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref name=\"DTD\">{{cite news | url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/lf/2002/02/01/stories/2002020100410200.htm | title=Dhil to Dhool | work=The Hindu | date=1 February 2002 | accessdate=1 February 2015 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201154114/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/lf/2002/02/01/stories/2002020100410200.htm | archivedate=1 February 2015 | url-status=live}}</ref> <br/> <ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-cinemaplus/sing-on/article3021611.ece | title=Sing on... | work=The Hindu | date=26 June 2009 | accessdate=1 February 2015 | last=Rangarajan | first=Malathi | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201154658/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-cinemaplus/sing-on/article3021611.ece | archivedate=1 February 2015 | url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Gemini (2002 Tamil film)|Gemini]]''\n| 2002\n| Tamil\n| \"O Podu\"\n| [[Bharathwaj]]\n| {{sortname|Anuradha|Sriram}}\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/lf/2002/03/31/stories/2002033100270200.htm | title='Gemini' already a hit! | work=The Hindu | date=31 March 2002 | accessdate=1 February 2015 | last=Kamath | first=Sudhish | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201155021/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/lf/2002/03/31/stories/2002033100270200.htm | archivedate=1 February 2015 | url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Kanthaswamy]]'' / ''Mallanna''\n| 2009\n| Tamil / Telugu\n| \"Excuse Me\" <br/>\"Ithellam Dupe\" / \"Ivannee Dupe\" <br/>\"Mambo Mamiya\" <br/>\"Meow Meow\"\n| [[Devi Sri Prasad]]\n| [[Suchitra]] <br/> Devi Sri Prasad <br/> [[Rita (Indian singer)|Rita]] <br/> [[Priya Himesh]]\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/article355048.ece | title=Vikram a singer too | work=The Hindu | date=15 February 2009 | accessdate=1 February 2015 | last=Ashok Kumar | first=S. R. | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201155228/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/article355048.ece | archivedate=1 February 2015 | url-status=live}}</ref> <br/> <ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/article648662.ece | title=Music to the ears | work=The Hindu | date=8 April 2009 | accessdate=1 February 2015 | last=Ashok Kumar | first=S. R. | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201155610/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/article648662.ece | archivedate=1 February 2015 | url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Madrasapattinam]]''\n| 2010\n| Tamil\n| \"Meghame O Meghame\"\n| {{sortname|G. V.|Prakash Kumar}}\n| {{sortname|M. S.|Viswanathan}}, [[Nassar (actor)|Nassar]]\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref>{{cite news | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news-interviews/Vikram-croons-in-five-voices/articleshow/5658772.cms | title=Vikram croons in five voices! | work=The Times of India | date=9 March 2010 | accessdate=1 February 2015 | last=Ramanujam | first=Srinivasa | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201160601/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Vikram-croons-in-five-voices/articleshow/5658772.cms | archivedate=1 February 2015 | url-status=live | df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Deiva Thirumagal]]'' / ''Nanna''\n| 2011\n| Tamil / Telugu\n| \"Kadha Solla Poren\" / \"Katha Cheputhane\" <br/>\"Pa Pa Pappa\"\n| {{sortname|G. V.|Prakash Kumar|nolink=1}}\n| Shringa <br/> Solo\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/south-review-deiva-thirumagan/20110420.htm | title=Music Review: Deiva Thirumagan music is touching | publisher=Rediff.com | date=20 April 2011 | accessdate=1 February 2015 | last=Srinivasan | first=Pavithra | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201160751/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/south-review-deiva-thirumagan/20110420.htm | archivedate=1 February 2015 | url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Rajapattai]]'' / ''Veedinthe''\n| 2011\n| Tamil / Telugu\n| \"Laddu Laddu\"\n| [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| [[Suchitra]], [[Priyadarshini (singer)|Priyadarshini]]\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref name=\"Pattai\">{{cite news | url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/music-review-rajapattai/20111216.htm | title=Music Review: Nothing new about Rajapattai's music | publisher=Rediff.com | date=16 December 2011 | accessdate=1 February 2015 | last=Srinivasan | first=Pavithra | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201161457/http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/music-review-rajapattai/20111216.htm | archivedate=1 February 2015 | url-status=live}}</ref> <br/> <ref>{{cite web | url=http://play.raaga.com/telugu/album/Veedinthe-songs-A0002842 | title=Veedinthe (2011) | publisher=[[Raaga.com]] | accessdate=1 February 2015 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201162453/http://play.raaga.com/telugu/album/Veedinthe-songs-A0002842 | archivedate=1 February 2015 | url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[David (2013 Tamil film)|David]]''\n| 2013\n| Tamil\n| \"Maria Pitache\"\n| {{sortname|Remo|Fernandes}}\n| {{sortname|Remo|Fernandes|nolink=1}}\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref>{{cite news | url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/david--tamil-music-review-the-soundtrack--boasts-of-trendsetting-music/315811-71-178.html | title=Music Review: David&nbsp;\u2014 The soundtrack boasts of trendsetting music | publisher=CNN-News18 | date=15 January 2013 | agency=IANS | accessdate=1 February 2015 | archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6W2tlOlE8?url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/david--tamil-music-review-the-soundtrack--boasts-of-trendsetting-music/315811-71-178.html | archivedate=2 February 2015 | url-status=live | df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Sketch (2018 film)|Sketch]]''\n| 2018\n| Tamil\n| \"Kanave Kanave\"\n| {{sortname|S. |Thaman}}\n| {{sortname|S.|Thaman|nolink=1}}\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref>{{cite web |url=https://itunes.apple.com/in/album/sketch-original-motion-picture-soundtrack-ep/1334069589 |title=Sketch (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack) - EP by Thaman S. on Apple Music |date=11 January 2018 |website=[[Apple Music]] |access-date=30 January 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Saamy Square]]''\n| 2018\n| Tamil\n| \"Pudhu Metro Rail\"\n| Devi Sri Prasad\n| [[Keerthy Suresh]]\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/saamy-square-original-motion-picture-soundtrack-ep/1415789917|title=Saamy Square (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack) - EP by Devi Sri Prasad on Apple Music|date=24 July 2018|website=[[Apple Music]]|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Kadaram Kondan]]''\n| 2019\n| Tamil\n| \"Theesudar Kuniyuma\"\n| [[Ghibran]]\n| {{N/A}}\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/music/kadaraam-kondan-makers-release-new-video-song-titled-theesudar-kuniyuma-from-the-chiyan-vikram-starrer/articleshow/70361991.cms|title='Kadaraam Kondan\u2019: Makers release new video song titled, \u2018'Theesudar Kuniyuma' from the Chiyan Vikram starrer|date=24 July 2019|website=[[Times of India]]|accessdate=3 August 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Vikram}}\n* {{official website|https://web.archive.org/web/20080513222141/http://www.chiyaanvikram.net:80/}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=1417314|name=Vikram}}\n\n{{NationalFilmAwardBestActor}}\n{{FilmfareTamilBestActor}}\n{{TamilNaduStateAwardForBestActor}}\n{{SIIMA Award for Best Actor}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vikram}}\n[[Category:Tamil male actors]]\n[[Category:Best Actor National Film Award winners]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Tamil cinema]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Tamil playback singers]]\n[[Category:Loyola College, Chennai alumni]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Hindi cinema]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Chennai]]\n[[Category:1966 births]]\n[[Category:Telugu male actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Telugu cinema]]\n[[Category:Indian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Malayalam cinema]]\n[[Category:Tamil Nadu State Film Awards winners]]\n[[Category:Filmfare Awards South winners]]\n[[Category:Indian male voice actors]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Kalaimamani Award]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:SIIMA Awards winners]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Indian English|date=October 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Good article}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Vikram\n| image              = Vikram.jpg\n| caption            = Vikram in 2009\n| birth_name         = Kennedy John Victor\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=y|1966|04|17}}{{age 54}}<ref>[http://www.sify.com/movies/surprise-b-day-cake-for-vikram-on-sketch-set-news-tamil-rerkcviaiejij.html Surprise b`day cake for Vikram on `Sketch` set]. Sify.com (17 April 2017). Retrieved on 17 September 2018.</ref><ref>Vasudevan, K.V. (23 April 2016) [http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/actor-vikram-turned-50-last-wee/article8513713.ece Actor vikram turned 50 last week]. The Hindu. Retrieved on 17 September 2018.</ref>\n| birth_place        = <!--Must be sourced-->\n| residence          = <!--Must be sourced-->\n| nationality        = Indian\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Film actor|film producer|[[playback singer]]|voice actor}}\n| years_active       = 1990\u2013present\n| spouse             = Shailaja Balakrishnan (m.1992)\n| children           = 2 (inc. [[Dhruv Vikram]])\n| awards             = [[National Film Award for Best Actor|National Best Actor]] (2003)<br />[[Tamil Nadu State Film Award for Best Actor|State Best Actor]] (1999, 2003,2010) <br />[[Kalaimamani]] (2004)\n| website            = \n| alma_mater     = [[Loyola College, Chennai]]\n}}\n\n'''Kennedy John Victor''' (born 17 April 1966), better known by his stage name '''Vikram''' or '''Chiyaan Vikram''', is an Indian actor and singer who predominantly appears in [[Tamil cinema|Tamil language]] films. He has won seven [[Filmfare Awards South|Filmfare Awards]] as well as one [[National Film Awards|National Film Award]] and [[Tamil Nadu State Film Awards|Tamil Nadu State Film Award]] amongst other recognitions and was awarded an [[Honorary Doctorate]] by the [[University of Milan]] in May 2011.\n\nHe made his debut in the 1990 film ''[[En Kadhal Kanmani]]'', which was followed by a series of small-budget Tamil, [[Malayalam cinema|Malayalam]] and [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]] films in the 1990s, many of which went unnoticed. However, the success of [[Bala (director)|Bala]]'s tragedy film ''[[Sethu (film)|Sethu]]'' (1999), in which Vikram appeared as a rogue turned lover, started Vikram's successful career as an actor. In the early 2000s, Vikram appeared in a series of [[Masala (film genre)|masala films]], with ''[[Dhill]]'' (2001), ''[[Gemini (2002 Tamil film)|Gemini]]'' (2002), ''[[Dhool]]'' (2003) and ''[[Saamy]]'' (2003) becoming commercially successful ventures. During the period, Vikram also appeared in diverse roles and received critical acclaim for his performance as a blind villager in ''[[Kasi (film)|Kasi]]'' and a [[Robin Hood]]-esque figure in ''[[Samurai (2002 film)|Samurai]]''. In 2003, Vikram's performance as a gravedigger with autism spectrum disorders in Bala's ''[[Pithamagan]]'' saw him win the [[National Film Award for Best Actor]], with his character only speaking a couple of lines of dialogue in the entire film.<ref name=\"pithwin\">{{cite web|author=Kumar, Ashok |date=20 August 2004 |title=Vikram, the Victor |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2004/08/20/stories/2004082001760100.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201091647/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2004/08/20/stories/2004082001760100.htm |archivedate= 1 February 2015 |df= }}</ref> \n\nHis appearance as an idealistic lawyer with [[Dissociative identity disorder|multiple personality disorder]] in [[S. Shankar|Shankar]]'s blockbuster ''[[Anniyan]]'' (2005) also won critical acclaim, as did his appearance as a superhero in ''[[Kanthaswamy]]'' (2009). Vikram's portrayal of Veeraiya, a tribal leader inspired by the [[Ramayana]] character [[Ravana]], in [[Mani Ratnam]]'s ''[[Raavanan]]'' saw him secure further accolades, as did his appearance as a mentally challenged adult with the maturity of a six-year-old boy in ''[[Deiva Thirumagal]]'' (2011). He consequently appeared in multiple get-ups as a bodybuilder and a crippled hunchback, losing up to 35 kilograms for sequences, during the making of Shankar's romantic thriller ''[[I (film)|I]]'' (2015) and won rave reviews from critics for his performance. It is currently the [[List of highest-grossing Tamil films|sixth highest-grossing Tamil film]] of all time.<ref>{{cite web|date=4 March 2015 |title=Vikram's 'I' Box Office: Shankar's Film Completes 50-Day Milestone in Theatres |work=International Business Times |url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/vikrams-i-box-office-shankars-film-completes-50-day-milestone-theatres-625176 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402130922/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/vikrams-i-box-office-shankars-film-completes-50-day-milestone-theatres-625176 |archivedate= 2 April 2015 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"ihindu\">{{cite web|author=Rangan, Baradwaj |date=14 January 2015 |title=I: A terrific performance let down by an uninspired, exhausting movie |work=The Hindu |accessdate=18 January 2015 |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-reviews/i-movie-review-by-baradwaj-rangan/article6789179.ece |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201141639/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-reviews/i-movie-review-by-baradwaj-rangan/article6789179.ece |archivedate= 1 February 2015 |df= }}</ref>\n\nVikram has promoted various social causes and appeared as the Youth Envoy for the [[United Nations Human Settlements Programme]] in 2011. He has been a brand ambassador of Sanjeevani Trust and a school for special children, Vidya Sudha, which he stayed at during the making of ''Deiva Thirumagal'' as well as having long-term associations with the Kasi Eye Care and running his own welfare association through the Vikram Foundation.<ref name=\"vikramun\">{{cite web|date=23 April 2010 |title=Vikram happy at being chosen UN Youth envoy |work=[[Deccan Herald]] |accessdate=7 January 2011 |url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/155996/vikram-happy-being-chosen-un.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110515134019/http://www.deccanherald.com/content/155996/vikram-happy-being-chosen-un.html |archivedate=15 May 2011 |df= }}</ref> In 2016, he produced and directed the video to the flood relief anthem, [[Spirit of Chennai]], as a tribute to the city's volunteers following the [[2015 South Indian floods]].\n\n==Early life==\nVikram was born as Kennedy to a Christian father and a Hindu mother in [[Madras]], [[Tamil Nadu]].<ref name=\"flopactor\"/> His father, John Victor (alias [[Vinod Raj (Tamil actor)|Vinod Raj]]) was a native of Paramakudi and ran away from home to start a career in films. His father, however, did not fare successfully, and only managed to act in supporting roles in Tamil films and television serials and this inspired Vikram to take part in theatre lessons and become professionally trained in classical and cinema dance forms to ensure he became a leading actor.<ref name=\"flopactor\">{{cite web|author=Sreedhar, Sridevi |date=4 June 2006 |title=Southern spice |work=[[The Telegraph (Calcutta)|The Telegraph]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1060604/asp/look/story_6303930.asp |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121102154911/http://www.telegraphindia.com/1060604/asp/look/story_6303930.asp |archivedate= 2 November 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"fatheractor\">{{cite web |author=Narasimham, N. L |date=4 March 2005 |title=Still the regular guy |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2005/03/04/stories/2005030401210200.htm}}</ref> Rajeshwari, Vikram's mother, was a sub-collector and her brother, [[Thiagarajan]] is an established director-actor in the Tamil film industry; with his son, actor [[Prashanth (actor)|Prashanth]], being Vikram's first cousin.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/did-you-know-/Vikram-and-Prashanth-are-cousins/articleshow/39683316.cms|title= Prasand and Vikram are cousins|publisher=[[The Times of India]] |date=5 August 2014 |accessdate=16 August 2014}}</ref>\n\nVikram is used as a screen name as he disliked his original name, Kennedy; the name Vikram was composed by taking \"Vi\" from his father's name, \"K\" from Kennedy, \"Ra\" from his mother's name and \"ram\" from his sun sign, [[Aries (astrology)|Aries]].<ref name=\"caravan\">{{cite web|author=Rangan, Baradwaj |date=1 December 2013 |title=Man of Steel |work=The Caravan Magazine |accessdate=8 April 2014 |url=http://www.caravanmagazine.in/arts/man-steel |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150918094317/http://www.caravanmagazine.in/arts/man-steel |archivedate=18 September 2015 |df= }}</ref>\n\nVikram was educated at [[Montfort School, Yercaud]], a boarding school in a hill station near [[Salem, Tamil Nadu|Salem]] and graduated in 1983. He has mentioned that he used his opportunities at school well by taking part in karate, horseback riding and swimming and noted that such early exposure to activities gave him confidence as a youngster. Vikram lurked in the fringes of the school's theatre club for a long period and often took part in backstage work before being handed the lead role in a school adaptation of [[Moli\u00e8re]]'s ''[[Le M\u00e9decin malgr\u00e9 lui|The Doctor in Spite of Himself]]'' after the original lead had contracted chicken pox.<ref name=\"caravan\"/> Despite expressing his interest to join films after school, his father forced him to go through education with Vikram subsequently graduated from [[Loyola College, Chennai]] with a degree in English Literature and worked halfway towards an MBA programme.<ref name=\"redwin\"/> Through the prolific dramatics club, Vikram appeared in stage productions including college adaptations of ''[[The Caine Mutiny Court-Martial]]'' and [[Peter Shaffer]]'s ''[[Black Comedy (play)|Black Comedy]]'', receiving best actor awards for his performances.<ref name=\"caravan\"/> After winning a Best Actor Award at a function held at [[Indian Institute of Technology Madras|IIT Madras]], Vikram was hit by a truck during a ride on his motorbike on the way home and suffered a serious leg injury. He remained hospital-ridden for three years during college and subsequently went through twenty-three surgeries to prevent his leg from being amputated.<ref name=\"redwin\">{{cite web|author=Warrier, Shobha |date=17 August 2004 |title=Vikram's obsession gets its reward |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2004/aug/17vikram.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110718203136/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2004/aug/17vikram.htm |archivedate=18 July 2011 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"mint\">{{cite web|author=Sukumaran, Shradha |date=17 June 2010 |title=\u2018My blood group is B+ and that's my motto\u2019 |work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.livemint.com/2010/06/17200701/8216My-blood-group-is-B-an.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100621065336/http://www.livemint.com/2010/06/17200701/8216My-blood-group-is-B-an.html |archivedate=21 June 2010 |df= }}</ref> Vikram then returned to finish the final year of his degree after his accident and secured permission to finish his dissertation at home, as he was only able to walk on crutches for a short period.<ref name=\"vikacc\">{{cite web|author=Muthiah, Wani |date=28 July 2011 |title=Long, winding path to success for Vikram |work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2011/7/28/nation/9176084&sec=nation |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121019105521/http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=%2F2011%2F7%2F28%2Fnation%2F9176084&sec=nation |url-status=dead |archive-date=19 October 2012 |df= }}</ref>\n\n==Film career==\n===1990\u20131998===\nVikram began his professional career by modelling in advert films for brands including Chola Tea, TVS Excel and Alwyn watches as well as appearing in a six episode television serial titled ''Galatta Kudumbam'', which aired between November and December 1988. During the final year of his [[M.B.A]] programme at [[Loyola College, Chennai|Loyola College]], he was recognised by the film industry, with veteran director [[C. V. Sridhar]] approaching him for a lead role in a film.<ref name=\"hindrel\">{{cite web|author=Narasimhan, N. L.|date=4 March 2005|title=Still the regular guy|work=The Hindu|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2005/03/04/stories/2005030401210200.htm}}</ref> Vikram made his film debut in 1990 by appearing in ''[[En Kadhal Kanmani]]'', a small budget love story featuring him alongside [[Rekha (Tamil actress)|Rekha Nambiar]], with Sridhar's ''[[Thanthu Vitten Ennai]]'', opposite [[Rohini (actress)|Rohini]] being his next release. He then signed on to be a part of cinematographer [[P. C. Sriram]]'s college love story ''[[Meera (1992 film)|Meera]]'', with high expectations, however, the three films failed to launch his career.<ref name=\"redset\">{{cite web|author=Warrier, Shobha |date=27 March 2000 |title=All that matters is a hit |publisher=[[Rediff.com]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2000/mar/27vikram.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120429174044/http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2000/mar/27vikram.htm |archivedate=29 April 2012 |df= }}</ref> His appearances in ''Meera'' and in ''[[Kaaval Geetham]]'', with another veteran director [[S. P. Muthuraman]], helped him secure film offers from the [[Malayalam]] and [[Telugu language|Telugu]] film industries.<ref name=\"hindrel\"/> In 1993, he almost signed on to appear in [[Mani Ratnam]]'s ''[[Bombay (film)|Bombay]]'' and featured in the initial photo shoot alongside [[Manisha Koirala]]. However, Mani Ratnam wanted Vikram to remove his beard for the role, and Vikram could not do so due to continuity problems with another film he had signed and hence was dropped from the project.<ref name=\"vikramkerala\">{{cite web|author=Nair, Ranjith|year=2005|title=Vikram Interview|publisher=Deepika|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=http://www.bollywhat-forum.com/index.php?topic=6757.0}}</ref>\n\nBetween 1993 and 1994, Vikram appeared in a series of films where he portrayed supporting roles. He appeared in three successful [[Malayalam]] films by appearing with [[Mammooty]], [[Suresh Gopi]] and [[Jayaram]] in [[Joshi (director)|Joshi]]'s successful action film ''[[Dhruvam]]'', before teaming up with Gopi again for [[Shaji Kailas]]'s ''[[Mafia (1993 film)|Mafia]]'', which explored Bangalore's criminal underworld. Furthermore, Joshi cast him again alongside Mammooty in the action drama ''[[Sainyam]]'' in the role of an [[Combined Cadet Force|air cadet]].<ref name=\"malay\">{{cite web|author=Nair, Unni|date=13 August 2010|title=Vikram to act in a Malayalam film|work=[[The Indian Express]]|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/Vikram-to-act-in-a-Malayalam-film/659056/}}</ref> During the period, Vikram also appeared in the small budget Telugu film ''[[Chirunavvula Varamistava]]'' in the lead role and as [[Akkineni Nageswara Rao]]'s eldest son in the family drama ''[[Bangaru Kutumbam]]'', with both films failing commercially. A brief return to Tamil films also proved unsuccessful, with his role in [[Vikraman]]'s multi-starrer ''[[Pudhiya Mannargal]]'', with music composed by [[A. R. Rahman]] turning out to be a commercial failure.<ref name=\"pmflop\">{{cite web|title=Actor&nbsp;\u2013 Important too. |publisher=Behindwoods |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-articles/movies-04/ar-rahman-3.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121021013016/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-articles/movies-04/ar-rahman-3.html |archivedate=21 October 2012 |df= }}</ref>\n\nThroughout 1995 and 1996, Vikram appeared in further Telugu and Malayalam films to receive income, being kept away from Tamil films due to a lack of offers.<ref name=\"redset\"/> He played the lead role in the Malayalam film ''Mayoora Nritam'' directed by [[Vijayakrishnan]]'s and even played villain in ''Street'' opposite [[Babu Antony]] and lead roles in the small budget Telugu films ''[[Aadaalla Majaka|Adalla Majaka]]'' and [[Sriraj Ginne]]'s ''[[Akka! Bagunnava?]]''. He collaborated again with Mammooty in ''[[Indraprastham (film)|Indraprastham]]'' and Suresh Gopi in ''Rajaputhran'', before appearing in his first lead role in Malayalam with ''[[Itha Oru Snehagatha]]'' opposite [[Laila Mehdin|Laila]].<ref name=\"malay\"/> Vikram signed [[Amitabh Bachchan]]'s first Tamil language film production, ''[[Ullaasam]]'', which also featured [[Ajith Kumar]] and [[Maheswari]]. The big budget film created anticipation prior to release, but was ultimately panned and fared poorly at the box office.<ref name=\"ulla\">{{cite web|author=Warrier, Shobha |date=6 July 1999 |title='Thanks to my relationship, I've stopped trusting people' |publisher=[[Rediff.com]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/1999/jul/06ajit.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110510080114/http://www.rediff.com/movies/1999/jul/06ajit.htm |archivedate=10 May 2011 |df= }}</ref> However, Vikram acknowledged the film for expanding his female fan base as a result of the soft-personality of his character.<ref name=\"redset\"/> He followed it up with appearances in the unsuccessful films ''Kurralla Rajyam'' in Telugu and then in the [[Ilaiyaraaja]] musical ''[[Kangalin Vaarthaigal]]'', before playing a short role in [[R. Parthiban|Parthiban]]'s critically acclaimed film ''[[Housefull (1999 film)|Housefull]]''.\n\nDuring his struggling phase, Vikram dubbed for other heroes in films including voices for [[Prabhu Deva]] in ''[[Kaadhalan]]'', [[Ajith Kumar]] in ''[[Amaravathi (1993 film)|Amaravathi]]'' and [[Abbas (actor)|Abbas]] in ''[[Kandukondain Kandukondain]]'' respectively. Vikram has mentioned that he did not look down on dubbing and saw it as a \"dignity of labour\".<ref name=\"mint\"/> During the period, he also attended dancing classes every day, and tried acting out different scenes and different characters with his small group of friends.<ref name=\"front\">{{cite web|date=19 September 2004 |title=`I am a director's actor' |publisher=[[The Hindu|Frontline (The Hindu)]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.frontlineonnet.com/fl2119/stories/20040924003910700.htm |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100507035929/http://www.frontlineonnet.com/fl2119/stories/20040924003910700.htm |archivedate=7 May 2010 }}</ref> He began to turn down chances to play supporting roles in films and was intent on making a breakthrough as a lead actor and notably turned down the role of Swarnamalya's fianc\u00e9e in Mani Ratnam's ''[[Alaipayuthey (film)|Alaipayuthey]]''.<ref name=\"caravan\"/> Vikram also rejected approaches from television serial producers, citing that working in television would reduce his chances of becoming a mainstream actor.<ref name=\"net\">{{cite web|author=Balakrishnan, Ravi |date=3 July 2010 |title=What drives Raavan's actor Vikram to do unusual roles |work=[[The Economic Times]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/features/business-of-bollywood/what-drives-raavans-actor-vikram-to-do-unusual-roles/articleshow/6121881.cms |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121019234236/http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/features/business-of-bollywood/what-drives-raavans-actor-vikram-to-do-unusual-roles/articleshow/6121881.cms |archivedate=19 October 2012 |df= }}</ref> He also refused opportunities to take part in film events as a backing dancer, with actor [[Sriman (actor)|Sriman]] revealing that Vikram was \"one amongst not many\" who was not interested in travelling to Canada to participate in such shows.<ref name=\"caravan\"/>\n\n===1999\u20132001===\nIn 1997, debutant director [[Bala (director)|Bala]] offered him the role of the rogue Sethu (Chiyaan), in the film ''[[Sethu (film)|Sethu]]''. To prepare for the character, Vikram shaved his head, lost twenty-one kilograms and grew his nails long for the role.<ref name=\"redwin\"/><ref name=\"front\"/>  After beginning production in April 1997, the film went through [[development hell]] after industry strikes and lack of funds hampered progress. During this phase, he did not accept other acting offers in order to maintain the continuity of his looks. The film then struggled to find a distributor, who shunned it due to the tragic climax and the film remained unreleased.<ref>{{cite news|title=Making films for the real world |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/lf/2003/01/02/stories/2003010206620200.htm |accessdate=7 November 2011 |newspaper=The Hindu |date=2 January 2003 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130607041653/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/lf/2003/01/02/stories/2003010206620200.htm |archivedate= 7 June 2013 |df= }}</ref> Vikram described the period of production as \"the worst phase of his career\" as he was financially strapped and \"his fire was in danger of dying down\".<ref name=\"front\"/> He turned down an opportunity from a friend to take up a job in technology and attempted to stay in the industry by directing a serial titled ''Mounam Pesiyadhey'', with [[Ameer (director)|Ameer]] as his assistant director.<ref name=\"caravan\"/> ''Sethu'' finally released in December 1999 and initially began running at a single noon show at a suburban theater, but gradually gained an audience through word-of-mouth publicity. Eventually, it ran for over one hundred days at several cinema halls across [[Chennai]]. Vikram was constantly being mobbed by people on the streets as a result of the film's success.<ref name=\"redwin\"/><ref name=\"redset\"/> Critics praised Vikram's performance with a reviewer referring to Vikram as \"a revelation\" and that \"he is very natural and his acting in last few scenes are just too good and could even be compared with the best we have seen\".<ref name=\"indolinksethu\">{{cite web |author=Hariharan, Easwaran |date=December 1999 |title=Sethu |publisher=Indolink.com |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.indolink.com/tamil/cinema/Reviews/articles/Sethu_191236.html |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110806185746/http://www.indolink.com/tamil/cinema/Reviews/articles/Sethu_191236.html |archivedate=6 August 2011  }}</ref> Similarly, a critic from the [[Malaysia]]n daily [[New Straits Times]], described the film as an \"unforgettable experience\" and described Vikram's performance as \"praise-worthy\".<ref name=\"nst\">{{cite web|author=Vijayan, K. N.|date=12 February 2000|title=Laughs and tears galore in 'Sethu'|work=[[New Straits Times]]|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=9lRIAAAAIBAJ&sjid=lRQEAAAAIBAJ&pg=3969,1961135&dq=vikram+sethu&hl=en}}</ref> The performance drew accolades with Vikram winning the [[Filmfare Special Award&nbsp;\u2013 South]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Nuvvu Nenu wins 4 Filmfare awards |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2002-04-06/hyderabad/27122602_1_filmfare-film-award-actor-award |accessdate=5 January 2012 |newspaper=The Times of India |date=6 April 2002 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201075354/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/hyderabad/Nuvvu-Nenu-wins-4-Filmfare-awards/articleshow/6011249.cms?referral=PM |archivedate= 1 February 2015 |df= }}</ref> and the [[Tamil Nadu State Film Award Special Prize]] for his portrayal of the title character, while reports emerged that he missed out on the [[National Film Award for Best Actor]] by a single vote to [[Mohanlal]].<ref name=\"missedsethu\">{{cite web|author=Rajitha |date=21 July 2000 |title=Ajit backs off Nanda |publisher=[[Rediff.com]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2000/jul/21spice.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121026145436/http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2000/jul/21spice.htm |archivedate=26 October 2012 |df= }}</ref> Post-''Sethu'', Vikram has said that the film would have been close to him regardless of its commercial success and that it put him on the \"right path\", with Vikram choosing to adapt the prefix of Chiyaan to his screen name.<ref name=\"front\"/>\n\nVikram did not sign up to a film for sixty five days after the release of ''Sethu'', to ensure that he made the right career move.<ref name=\"redwin\"/> Vikram spent time completing projects he had agreed to feature in before the release of ''Sethu'' and hence made a couple of appearances in the Malayalam films ''[[Red Indians (film)|Red Indians]]'' and the horror film ''[[Indriyam]]''.<ref name=\"iondr\">{{cite web|year=2000 |title=Indriyam |publisher=Bizhat |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://movies.bizhat.com/review_indriyam.php |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040813120915/http://movies.bizhat.com/review_indriyam.php |archivedate=13 August 2004 |df= }}</ref> He also played a leading role in ''[[Siragugal]]'', a rare Tamil telefilm produced and featuring [[Raadhika]], which was shot entirely in the suburbs of [[London]].<ref>{{cite web|title=SIRAGUGAL|url=http://www.radaan.tv/siragugal.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120419151726/http://www.radaan.tv/siragugal.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=19 April 2012|work=Radaan Mediaworks|publisher=Radaan Mediaworks India Limited|accessdate=7 November 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Grand aunt of the small screen |url=http://hindu.com/2001/07/05/stories/09050464.htm |accessdate=7 November 2011 |newspaper=The Hindu |date=5 July 2001 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019072746/http://hindu.com/2001/07/05/stories/09050464.htm |archivedate=19 October 2013 |df= }}</ref> Furthermore, he also completed two Telugu films during the period; ''[[9 Nelalu]]'' and ''Youth''. ''9 Nelalu'' featured Vikram as the husband of the character played by [[Soundarya]], who faces the challenges of being a surrogate mother. The film won positive reviews, with a critic mentioning that Vikram gave a \"controlled performance\"<ref name=\"ninenel\">{{cite web|first=Christopher|last=Domingo|year=2000|title=9 Nelalu Movie Review|publisher=FullHyderabad.com|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=http://www.fullhyderabad.com/profile/movies/1904/2/9-nelalu-movie-review}}</ref> while Vikram's newfound popularity in Tamil films saw the film dubbed into Tamil soon after as ''Kandane Seethayai'', with an inserted comedy track by comedian [[Vivek (actor)|Vivek]].<ref name=\"kandense\">{{cite web|author=Balsubramaniam, Balaji |year=2000 |title=Kandane Seethayai |publisher=Thiraipadam.com |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.thiraipadam.com/cgi-bin/movie_review.pl?id=136&user_name=bbalaji&review_lang=english&lang=english |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111004175649/http://www.thiraipadam.com/cgi-bin/movie_review.pl?id=136&user_name=bbalaji&review_lang=english&lang=english |archivedate= 4 October 2011 |df= }}</ref> His next release was Rajakumaran's ''[[Vinnukum Mannukum]]'', alongside [[Sarath Kumar]], [[Kushboo]] and [[Devayani (actress)|Devayani]], which revolved around an ordinary boy falling in love with an actress. Vikram has since mentioned his displeasure at being a part of the film, claiming that he had arguments with the director for every single shot and that \"everything in that film, right from the first shot was wrong\"; the film became a failure commercially.<ref name=\"whyihate\">{{cite web|author=Kamath, Sudhish |date=15 February 2008 |title=Why I hate... Vinnukkum Mannukkum |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/cp/2008/02/15/stories/2008021550170400.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111201184929/http://www.hindu.com/cp/2008/02/15/stories/2008021550170400.htm |archivedate= 1 December 2011 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"balance\">{{cite web|author=Mahesh, Chitra |date=31 May 2002 |title=`I want to strike a balance' |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/05/31/stories/2002053100170100.htm |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140607062058/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/05/31/stories/2002053100170100.htm |archivedate= 7 June 2014 |df= }}</ref> His next film was ''[[Dhill]]'', where he played an aspiring police officer, Kanagavel, who tackles a corrupt policeman. To appear trim in the role of the aspiring police officer, Vikram went on a strict diet eating only fruits and drinking juice.<ref name=\"starint\">{{cite web|author=Selva, T |date=10 January 2005 |title=Vikram's star rises |work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://ecentral.my/news/story.asp?file=/2005/1/10/movies/9803468&sec=movies |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120609122941/http://ecentral.my/news/story.asp?file=%2F2005%2F1%2F10%2Fmovies%2F9803468&sec=movies |archivedate= 9 June 2012 |df= }}</ref> The film opened to positive reviews, with a critic from ''[[The Hindu]]'' claiming that \"Vikram has the ability and potential\" and that \"Vikram has once again proved that his success in ''[[Sethu (film)|Sethu]]'' was not a fluke\".<ref name=\"dhillhindu\">{{cite web|author=Kumar, Ashok |date=27 July 2001 |title=Film Review: Dhil |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/2001/07/27/stories/09270222.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101128022905/http://hindu.com/thehindu/2001/07/27/stories/09270222.htm |archivedate=28 November 2010 |df= }}</ref> ''Dhill'' subsequently went on to become Vikram's first success in the [[masala (film genre)|masala film genre]] and led the way for more such films in the same genre for him.<ref name=\"dhillhit\">{{cite web|author=Kumar, Ashok |date=9 August 2002 |title=Raising expectations |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/08/09/stories/2002080901030200.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120211210400/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/08/09/stories/2002080901030200.htm |archivedate=11 February 2012 |df= }}</ref> Vikram's portrayal of a blind folk singer in [[Vinayan]]'s ''[[Kasi (film)|Kasi]]'' won him the [[Filmfare Best Actor Award (Tamil)|Filmfare Best Tamil Actor Award]] and the film also did well commercially.<ref name=\"balance\"/> For the movie, he sunbathed on the terrace of his beachside home in Chennai for a sunburnt look and got dizzying headaches while practising to look blind.<ref name=\"starint\"/> Again, Vikram's performance won positive reviews from critics, with a reviewer describing it as an \"extraordinarily detailed performance\" and that \"as the blind singer, he brings laughter, tears and a lump in one's throat\".<ref name=\"kasisify\">{{cite web|date=17 December 2001 |title=Kasi |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/kasi-review-tamil-9080157.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131031095013/http://www.sify.com/movies/kasi-review-tamil-9080157.html |archivedate=31 October 2013 |df= }}</ref>\n\n===2002\u20132003===\nThe following year, Vikram went on to play the title role in [[Saran (director)|Saran]]'s ''[[Gemini (2002 Tamil film)|Gemini]]'', produced by [[AVM Productions]], his first big-budget film in the Tamil industry, which featured him in the role of a local rowdy.<ref name=\"sifyvikramone\">{{cite web|year=2002 |title=Vikram |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/interview.php?id=7584766&cid=2408 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022055817/http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/interview.php?id=7584766&cid=2408 |archivedate=22 October 2012 |df= }}</ref> The action film won good reviews, with a critic citing that Vikram \"delivers a convincing performance\" and consequently became a \"box office triumph\".<ref name=\"balance\"/><ref name=\"geminired\">{{cite web|author=Pearl |date=26 April 2002 |title=Vikram chews paan, excels |publisher=[[Rediff.com]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2002/apr/26gem.htm |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140607063050/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2002/apr/26gem.htm |archivedate= 7 June 2014 |df= }}</ref> Similarly, the film's soundtrack composed by [[Bharathwaj]] had become popular prior to release, with Vikram also singing a version of the hit song \"O Podu!\" for the album.<ref name=\"geminimusic\">{{cite web|author=Kamath, Sudhish |date=31 March 2002 |title='Gemini' already a hit |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/lf/2002/03/31/stories/2002033100270200.htm |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140606162017/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/lf/2002/03/31/stories/2002033100270200.htm |archivedate= 6 June 2014 |df= }}</ref> [[Balaji Sakthivel]]'s ''[[Samurai (2002 film)|Samurai]]'' was his next release, featuring him as a vigilante [[Robin Hood]]-esque figure who kidnapped corrupt politicians. Vikram had signed the film in early 2000 and the film was on hold during production, leading to a two-year delay and the film finally opened to average reviews and collections. The critic from ''[[The Hindu]]'' gave praise for Vikram's \"admirably well-maintained physique and powerful eyes\", whilst another labelled that the film's single major positive was Vikram's convincing portrayal.<ref name=\"samred\">{{cite web|author=Pearl |date=5 August 2002 |title=Sigh! |publisher=[[Rediff.com]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2002/aug/05sam.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121026145625/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2002/aug/05sam.htm |archivedate=26 October 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"hinsamu\">{{cite web|author=Rangarajan, Malathi |date=19 July 2002 |title=Samurai |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/07/19/stories/2002071900910201.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120212013813/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/07/19/stories/2002071900910201.htm |archivedate=12 February 2012 |df= }}</ref> His final release of the year was [[Prabhu Solomon]]'s ''[[King (2002 film)|King]]'', a drama film which featured him alongside [[Sneha (actress)|Sneha]] and [[Nassar (actor)|Nassar]]. Vikram played Raja, a magician, who is unaware that he has been diagnosed with [[multiple sclerosis]], with his family trying to keep the truth away from him. The film also met with an unfavorable response commercially, but won positive acclaim from critics.<ref name=\"hinking\">{{cite web|author=Rangarajan, Malathi |date=13 September 2002 |title=King |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/09/13/stories/2002091300970300.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120211234625/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/09/13/stories/2002091300970300.htm |archivedate=11 February 2012 |df= }}</ref>\n\nThe success of [[Dharani (director)|Dharani]]'s ''Dhill'' resulted in the film's team collaborating to make a film in a similar genre; ''[[Dhool]]'', which also featured [[Jyothika]], [[Reemma Sen]] and [[Vivek (actor)|Vivek]].<ref name=\"dhillhit\"/> The film saw Vikram play Aarumugham, a villager, who comes to the city seeking help in regard to a water crisis back home, but subsequently ends up tackling the corrupt politicians who are behind the water scam. In regard to his performance, the [[Rediff.com]] review praised his enactment, citing that \"Vikram is at his peak\" and that \"he seems as much at home with comedy as with action, in romance as in emotional sequences\", while the critic from ''The Hindu'' also praised his performance.<ref name=\"rediffdhool\">{{cite web|author=Aarkhay |date=23 January 2003 |title=Vikram turns up trumps with Dhool |publisher=[[Rediff.com]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2003/jan/23dhool.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110203112042/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2003/jan/23dhool.htm |archivedate= 3 February 2011 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"dhoolreview\">{{cite web|author=Rangarajan, Malathi |date=24 January 2003 |title=Dhool |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/24/stories/2003012401130200.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120211210913/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/24/stories/2003012401130200.htm |archivedate=11 February 2012 |df= }}</ref> The film became a blockbuster and his fifth success in two and a half years, with Vikram being dubbed as \"the matinee idol of our times\" by a leading Indian newspaper.<ref>{{cite news|title=track record |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-cinemaplus/article2602198.ece |accessdate=7 November 2011 |newspaper=The Hindu |date=6 November 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160115234452/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-cinemaplus/article2602198.ece |archivedate=15 January 2016 |df= }}</ref> He also featured in the romantic film ''[[Kadhal Sadugudu]]'', with [[Priyanka Upendra|Priyanka Trivedi]] which was a critical and commercial failure, with reviewers claiming that \"there are times you wish Vikram were a little more brisk and dynamic\" in regard to his performance.<ref name=\"ksgreview\">{{cite web|author=Rangarajan, Malathi |date=18 April 2003 |title=Kadhal Sadugudu |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/04/18/stories/2003041800950202.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120211093956/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/04/18/stories/2003041800950202.htm |archivedate=11 February 2012 |df= }}</ref> After release, Vikram was critical of the film's failure, confessing that the story \"underwent a lot of changes after the initial narration\", lamenting that he was \"taken for a royal ride\" by the producers.<ref name=\"sifyvikramtwo\">{{cite web|year=2003 |title=I Am Happy To Be A Saleable Hero: Vikram |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/interview.php?id=13150128&cid=2408 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022055846/http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/interview.php?id=13150128&cid=2408 |archivedate=22 October 2012 |df= }}</ref>\n\nVikram was then signed on by [[K. Balachander]] to appear in his banner's biggest production till date, ''[[Saamy]]'', directed by [[Hari (director)|Hari]].<ref name=\"kbsaamy\">{{cite web|author=Warrier, Shobha |date=13 March 2003 |title='Sami is Vikram's film' |publisher=[[Rediff.com]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2003/mar/13sami.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120109102551/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2003/mar/13sami.htm |archivedate= 9 January 2012 |df= }}</ref> Vikram played Aarusaamy, an honest cop working in [[Tirunelveli]], who solves the region's communal problems with his down-to-earth approach. Vikram worked on his body for the film, sporting a thick waist to show notable differences from his other police film, ''Dhill'' and also put on eight kilograms.<ref name=\"front\"/> The film took a large opening, grossing over Rs. 7 crores in 10 days in Tamil Nadu, while also taking the largest opening of the new millennium in [[Kerala]], with the Telugu remake rights also sold for a record price. Due to the good opening, the film has proved to be profitable just 10 days after its release and consequently went on to become a blockbuster.<ref name=\"saamybox\">{{cite web|author=Pillai, Sreedhar |date=18 April 2003 |title=Numero Uno |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/mp/2003/05/26/stories/2003052600030201.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101111112657/http://hindu.com/thehindu/mp/2003/05/26/stories/2003052600030201.htm |archivedate=11 November 2010 |df= }}</ref> Vikram's performance also was lapped up by critics earning him a nomination for [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor - Tamil|Filmfare Best Tamil Actor Award]], with the critic from [[Sify]] claiming that Vikram had \"succumbed to the superstar image trap\", but is the \"mainstay of the picture\".<ref name=\"sifysaamy\">{{cite web|year=2003 |title=Review:Saamy |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/saamy-review-tamil-13049384.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141007035217/http://www.sify.com/movies/saamy-review-tamil-13049384.html |archivedate= 7 October 2014 |df= }}</ref>\n\n===2003\u20132009===\nLater that year, he starred in [[Bala (director)|Bala]]'s ''[[Pithamagan]]'', along with [[Suriya (actor)|Suriya]], [[Sangeetha Krish|Sangeetha]] and [[Laila Mehdin|Laila]], playing the role of Chitthan, a gravedigger with autism spectrum disorders. He did not have any dialogue in the film and the actor's acting muscles were stretched as he had to use body language and facial expressions to convey his feelings and thoughts, with Vikram also applying the make-up for the character himself.<ref name=\"front\"/><ref name=\"starint\"/> The film won positive reviews with the critic from ''[[The Hindu]]'' calling it a \"symphony on celluloid\", while noting that it will be a \"milestone in Vikram's career\" and \"he carves a niche for himself in the viewer's mind with his expressions and excellent body language\".<ref name=\"pithth\">{{cite web|author=Rangarajan, Malathi |date=31 October 2003 |title=Pithamagan |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/10/31/stories/2003103101210200.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120211124803/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/10/31/stories/2003103101210200.htm |archivedate=11 February 2012 |df= }}</ref> His portrayal won him both the [[Filmfare Best Actor Award (Tamil)|Filmfare Best Tamil Actor Award]] and the [[National Film Award for Best Actor]], with the latter accolade making him only the third Tamil actor to win the award.<ref name=\"pithwin\"/><ref name=\"redwin\"/> His next release, the revenge drama ''[[Arul]]'', directed by [[Hari (director)|Hari]], garnered poor reviews and box office collections.<ref name=\"arul\">{{cite web|date=17 August 2004 |title=Vikram : A close look at the award winner |publisher=IndiaGlitz |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/10230.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121024045937/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/10230.html |archivedate=24 October 2012 |df= }}</ref>\n\nVikram signed on to feature in the action thriller ''[[Anniyan]]'', directed by prominent director [[S. Shankar|Shankar]] in March 2004.<ref name=\"anniyan\">{{cite web|date=4 March 2004 |title=First look: Shankar's `Anniyan` |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/first-look-shankars-anniyan-news-tamil-kkfvMHaaefa.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022060041/http://www.sify.com/movies/first-look-shankars-anniyan-news-tamil-kkfvMHaaefa.html |archivedate=22 October 2012 |df= }}</ref> Vikram agreed to shoot for the film for 140 days, which was revealed to be amongst the longest contracts signed by an actor in a Tamil film.<ref name=\"anniyanoneforty\">{{cite web|date=16 June 2005 |title=History made, history waits |publisher=IndiaGlitz |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/15221.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121024045949/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/15221.html |archivedate=24 October 2012 |df= }}</ref> The film featured him as a character suffering from [[dissociative identity disorder]] with three distinct personae: a meek lawyer, a suave fashion model and a psychotic serial killer. Prior to release, the film was touted as the most expensive South Indian film ever, costing Rs 26.38 crores, and was released across India with 400 prints.<ref name=\"anniyanbig\">{{cite web|author=Pillai, Sreedhar |date=18 June 2005 |title=The mother of all biggies |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/mp/2005/06/18/stories/2005061803170200.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019072806/http://www.hindu.com/mp/2005/06/18/stories/2005061803170200.htm |archivedate=19 October 2013 |df= }}</ref> ''Anniyan'' took an \"extraordinary opening\",<ref name=\"anniyanopening\">{{cite web|date=18 June 2005 |title=Extraordinary opening! |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/extraordinary-opening-news-tamil-kkfv3rcigha.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022060145/http://www.sify.com/movies/extraordinary-opening-news-tamil-kkfv3rcigha.html |archivedate=22 October 2012 |df= }}</ref> and went on to become a blockbuster grossing more than Rs.100 crores through the original and two dubbed versions.<ref name=\"aparachitbb\">{{cite web|author=Us Salam, Ziya |date=19 May 2006 |title=`Aparichit' no more |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2006/05/19/stories/2006051901290100.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121110120026/http://www.hindu.com/fr/2006/05/19/stories/2006051901290100.htm |archivedate=10 November 2012 |df= }}</ref> Vikram's performance was unanimously praised, with a reviewer from [[Sify]] citing that \"Anniyan truly belongs to Vikram and the film is unthinkable without him\" and \"it is a role that could have been reduced to a caricature by a lesser actor\".<ref name=\"anniyarv\">{{cite web|date=18 June 2005 |title=Anniyan |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/anniyan-review-tamil-13873632.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141030045503/http://www.sify.com/movies/anniyan-review-tamil-13873632.html |archivedate=30 October 2014 |df= }}</ref> The film won 8 out of the 15 awards possible at the 2005 [[Filmfare Awards South]], with Vikram adjudged [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor - Tamil|Best Actor]].<ref name=\"anniyanaward\">{{cite web|date=10 September 2006 |title=`Anniyan` sweeps Filmfare Awards! |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/anniyan-sweeps-filmfare-awards-news-tamil-kkfvinigibe.html |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140926074039/http://www.sify.com/movies/anniyan-sweeps-filmfare-awards-news-tamil-kkfvinigibe.html |archivedate=26 September 2014  }}</ref> Later in the year, he signed and completed [[Shafi (director)|Shafi]]'s comedy film with [[Asin]], ''[[Majaa]]'', in less than five months. The film which also featured [[Pasupathy]] as his brother, saw Vikram work as the assistant director under Shafi.<ref name=\"admajaa\">{{cite web|date=9 January 2006 |title=I've struggled a lot to reach this level: Vikram |publisher=IndiaGlitz |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/malayalam/interview/6525.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201121527/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/malayalam/interview/6525.html |archivedate= 1 February 2015 |df= }}</ref> ''Majaa'' faced a poor response at the box office and fetched average reviews, with a reviewer citing that \"you will surely find something missing\".<ref name=\"majaaindure\">{{cite web|author=Kumar, Ashok |date=4 November 2005 |title=Where is the entertainment? |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2005/11/04/stories/2005110402340200.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120211234401/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2005/11/04/stories/2005110402340200.htm |archivedate=11 February 2012 |df= }}</ref>\n\nVikram then signed up for ''[[Bheema]]'' in October 2005, with the film facing severe delays and only releasing in January 2008.<ref name=\"bheemasign\">{{cite web|date=15 October 2005 |title=Vikram is Bheema! |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/vikram-is-bheema-news-tamil-kkfvzjegbdd.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022060506/http://www.sify.com/movies/vikram-is-bheema-news-tamil-kkfvzjegbdd.html |archivedate=22 October 2012 |df= }}</ref> The film saw him portray Sekhar, who grows up idolizing the gangster played by [[Prakash Raj]], and Vikram revealed that he approached the film like an actor, even though the film's script was written \"for a star\".<ref name=\"bheemahindu\">{{cite web|author=Kamath, Sudhish |date=7 September 2007 |title=Vikram versus Kenny |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/cp/2007/09/07/stories/2007090750050100.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100626101624/http://www.hindu.com/cp/2007/09/07/stories/2007090750050100.htm |archivedate=26 June 2010 |df= }}</ref> Upon release, the film gained mixed reviews though reviewers praised Vikram's performance, with a critic claiming that \"Vikram breathes life into the film\", \"he looks sensational with his toned body, killer looks unarguably delivers yet another outstanding performance of his career\" and to \"see the film only for him\".<ref name=\"sifyhindure\">{{cite web|date=15 January 2008 |title=Bheema |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/bheema-review-tamil-14589515.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131218212433/http://www.sify.com/movies/bheema-review-tamil-14589515.html |archivedate=18 December 2013 |df= }}</ref> Similarly, the review from ''The Hindu'' was critical of the excessive violence and mentioned that \"as narration gives way after a point, Vikram can only appear helpless\".<ref name=\"bheemahindure\">{{cite web|author=Rangarajan, Malathi |date=15 January 2008 |title=A bloodbath almost&nbsp;\u2013 Bheema |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2008/01/18/stories/2008011850720200.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121110120105/http://www.hindu.com/fr/2008/01/18/stories/2008011850720200.htm |archivedate=10 November 2012 |df= }}</ref> His next release, ''[[Kanthaswamy (film)|Kanthaswamy]]'', directed by [[Susi Ganesan]] and also featuring [[Shriya Saran]], became the first [[superhero]] film in Tamil cinema, with Vikram being featured as a vigilante dressed as an anthropomorphic rooster, Kokorako and a CBI Officer.<ref name=\"toikantha\">{{cite web|author=Pillai, Sreedhar|date=10 April 2009|title=Gung-ho about 'Kandasamy'|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-04-10/news-interviews/28024076_1_susi-ganesan-kandasamy-film}}</ref> ''Kanthaswamy'' became Vikram's most expensive production beating ''Anniyan'', with the film boasting of high production values of having an innovative pre-launch trailer and with scenes shot in [[Italy]] and [[Mexico]].<ref name=\"trailere\">{{cite web|author=Ashok Kumar, S.R |date=19 September 2007 |title=Invitation for launch of \u2018Kandasamy\u2019 not commonplace |work=The Hindu |accessdate=19 September 2007 |url=http://www.hinduonnet.com/2007/09/19/stories/2007091959110200.htm |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090110182415/http://www.hinduonnet.com/2007/09/19/stories/2007091959110200.htm |archivedate=10 January 2009 }}</ref><ref name=\"kantexp\">{{cite web|author=Ganesan, Sharmilla |date=25 August 2009 |title=Superhero with style |work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]] |accessdate=16 July 2011 |url=http://ecentral.my/news/story.asp?file=/2009/8/25/movies/4566714&sec=movies |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120609123835/http://ecentral.my/news/story.asp?file=%2F2009%2F8%2F25%2Fmovies%2F4566714&sec=movies |archivedate= 9 June 2012 |df= }}</ref> The film earned a mixed response from critics, with the reviewer from [[Sify]] claiming that the film \"strikes a fine balance between style and substance\" and proceeding to state that \"Vikram is mesmerizing and has given an extra dimension to the characters he plays in the film and steers it to the winning post\", suggesting that \"there are very few people in Indian cinema who can do the larger-than-life fantasy characters as easily as Vikram\". Sudhish Kamath of ''The Hindu'' labelled the film as \"slow death\", claiming that \"as an actor, Vikram has nothing to do\". The film took a strong opening, with a collection of Rs. 37 crore, including Rs. 16 crore in Tamil Nadu, at the box office in the opening week of its international release. The film subsequently went on to become one of the most profitable films of the year and ran in theaters for over one hundred days.<ref name=\"hitkantha\">{{cite web|date=2 September 2009 |title=The rooster rocks the box office |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article13770.ece |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121102120011/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article13770.ece |archivedate= 2 November 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"hundredkantha\">{{cite web|date=24 December 2009 |title=Big celebration for Kanthaswamy |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/big-celebration-for-kanthaswamy-news-tamil-kkfrhdfhdea.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022060604/http://www.sify.com/movies/big-celebration-for-kanthaswamy-news-tamil-kkfrhdfhdea.html |archivedate=22 October 2012 |df= }}</ref>\n\n===2010\u20132014===\nVikram then featured in [[Mani Ratnam]]'s bilingual films ''[[Raavanan]]'' and ''[[Raavan]]'', inspired by the ancient [[Sanskrit]] epic [[Ramayana]], with Vikram featuring as the tribal leader, Veeraiya, in the Tamil version and the cop, Dev Pratap Sharma, in the Hindi version of the films, which were shot simultaneously.<ref name=\"ravsifint\">{{cite web |author=Sreedhar, Sridevi |date=10 June 2010 |title=I am flying, thrilled and intoxicated: Vikram |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/i-am-flying-thrilled-and-intoxicated-vikram-news-tamil-kkfq0xhegdc.html |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110724144159/http://www.sify.com/movies/i-am-flying-thrilled-and-intoxicated-vikram-news-tamil-kkfq0xhegdc.html |archivedate=24 July 2011 |df= }}</ref> Vikram revealed that changes between the two characters during filming took up to 45 minutes, with [[Abhishek Bachchan]] playing the tribal leader in the Hindi version, whilst [[Prithviraj Sukumaran|Prithviraj]] played the cop in the Tamil version, with [[Aishwarya Rai]] also in the cast.<ref name=\"mint\"/> Vikram was initially apprehensive, because both roles were to be shot almost simultaneously, but revealed that he succeeded by showing differences in his body language and expressions.<ref name=\"diffs\">{{cite web|author=Rangarajan, Malathi |date=6 May 2010 |title=\u2018Raavanan\u2019, a re-incarnation |work=The Hindu |accessdate=7 January 2011 |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article423184.ece |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100903110236/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article423184.ece |archivedate= 3 September 2010 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"diffstwo\">{{cite web|date=13 June 2010|title=I had the arrogance for it: Vikram|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=7 August 2011|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-06-13/news-interviews/28285463_1_vikram-mani-ratnam-anti-hero}}</ref> Vikram revealed that he and Abhishek Bachchan played the roles in the respective versions without inspiration from one another. Despite being a non-speaker and making his debut in Hindi, he dubbed his lines in the language, remarking jovially that it was the \"most difficult thing in the world\".<ref name=\"ubb\">{{cite web|author=Ramsubramaniam, Nikhil|date=9 June 2010|title=\"Abhishek has been the best co-star I have ever worked with till date\"&nbsp;\u2013 Vikram|publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|accessdate=7 August 2011|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/features/2010/06/09/6336/}}{{dead link|date=October 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"rediffraavnan\">{{cite web|author=N, Patcy |date=17 June 2010 |title=When Vikram picked up Abhishek and threw him! |publisher=[[Rediff.com]] |accessdate=7 August 2011 |url=http://movies.rediff.com/slide-show/2010/jun/17/slide-show-1-vikram-on-raavan.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110410043255/http://movies.rediff.com/slide-show/2010/jun/17/slide-show-1-vikram-on-raavan.htm |archivedate=10 April 2011 |df= }}</ref> After promotions at the [[Cannes Film Festival]] and a premiere at [[Leicester Square]] in [[London]], the two versions and the dubbed Telugu version released simultaneously in 2,200 screens worldwide and took a big opening on day one, earning 20 crores.<ref name=\"raavanpremiere\">{{cite web|date=18 June 2010 |title=Raavan has a star-studded premiere in London |work=The Hindu |accessdate=7 August 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/2010/06/18/stories/2010061855652200.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100721215342/http://www.hindu.com/2010/06/18/stories/2010061855652200.htm |archivedate=21 July 2010 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"raavanopening\">{{cite web|date=19 June 2010 |title=\u2018Raavan\u2019 earns Rs 20 crore worldwide on opening day |work=[[Deccan Herald]] |accessdate=7 August 2011 |url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/76426/raavan-earns-rs-20-crore.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110630151022/http://www.deccanherald.com/content/76426/raavan-earns-rs-20-crore.html |archivedate=30 June 2011 |df= }}</ref> The Tamil version, ''Raavanan'' won rave reviews from critics, with ''[[The Hindu]]'' calling it a \"master stroke\" and claiming that Vikram \"raises the bar higher with every venture\". The critic cited that \"emotions of love, animus, anguish and joy dance on his face in quick succession\", concluding that \"Vikram lifts the role to an admirable level\".<ref name=\"raavananhin\">{{cite web|author=Rangarajan, Malathi |date=25 June 2010 |title=A masterstroke yet again&nbsp;\u2013 Raavanan |work=The Hindu |accessdate=7 August 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2010/06/25/stories/2010062550400201.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100701032556/http://www.hindu.com/fr/2010/06/25/stories/2010062550400201.htm |archivedate= 1 July 2010 |df= }}</ref> The critic from Sify labelled it as an \"astonishing portrayal\", while the critic from the ''[[Hindustan Times]]'' praised Vikram's \"ability to get into Veeraiya's skin and emote with conviction\".<ref name=\"raavanantimes\">{{cite web|author=Bhaskaran, Gauthaman |date=19 June 2010 |title=Gautaman Bhaskaran's Review: Raavanan |work=[[Hindustan Times]] |accessdate=7 August 2011 |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Gautaman-Bhaskaran-s-Review-Raavanan/Article1-560002.aspx |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100627152149/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Gautaman-Bhaskaran-s-Review-Raavanan/Article1-560002.aspx |archivedate=27 June 2010 |df= }}</ref> The Tamil version consequently went on to become a commercial success, with Vikram's performance leading to him winning the [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor - Tamil|Filmfare Award for Best Tamil Actor]] among other accolades.<ref name=\"raavananhhit\">{{cite web|author=Reddy, Krithika |date=2 July 2010 |title=Rock and role |work=The Hindu |accessdate=7 August 2011 |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article496828.ece |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100814123146/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article496828.ece |archivedate=14 August 2010 |df= }}</ref> In contrast, the Hindi version fetched mixed reviews, with critics agreeing that Vikram's performance as the tribal leader was more convincing than Bachchan's. [[Baradwaj Rangan]], writing for ''[[The New Indian Express]]'' rated the film 4/5 and said: \"Raavan falls for Sita (and vice versa) in an intriguingly idiosyncratic take on the Ramayana&nbsp;\u2013 if you can get past the lead performances, that is\".<ref>{{cite web|first=Baradwaj |last=Rangan |title='Raavan' Review |work=[[The New Indian Express]] |url=http://baradwajrangan.wordpress.com/2010/06/19/review-raavan/ |accessdate=19 June 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100621082438/http://baradwajrangan.wordpress.com/2010/06/19/review-raavan/ |archivedate=21 June 2010 |df= }}</ref> Whereas, [[Taran Adarsh]], writing for [[Bollywood Hungama]] rated it 1.5/5 and said: \"On the whole, ''Raavan'' is a king-sized disappointment, in terms of content\" though mentioning that Vikram was \"first-rate, although the role isn't substantial enough\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Adarsh |first=Taran |title=Raavan: Movie Review |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/14148/index.html |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=18 June 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100623075355/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/14148/index.html |archivedate=23 June 2010 |df= }}</ref> ''Raavan'' subsequently went on to become a surprise flop at the Indian box office.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hits continue to evade Bollywood as ''Raavan'' flops |url=http://movies.rediff.com/report/2010/jun/28/box-office-raavan-flops.htm |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=8 July 2010 |date=28 June 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100701042457/http://movies.rediff.com/report/2010/jun/28/box-office-raavan-flops.htm |archivedate= 1 July 2010 |df= }}</ref> The film was also screened at the [[Venice Film Festival]] and the [[Busan International Film Festival]], with Vikram in attendance.<ref name=\"venice\">{{cite web|author=Sangeetha|date=11 September 2010|title=Vikram: I was never so excited|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=7 August 2011|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-09-11/news-interviews/28215529_1_vikram-chiyaan-suhasini}}</ref>\n[[File:Tamil actor & UN Habitat Youth Envoy Vikram.jpg|thumb|Vikram in 2011 ]]\nAfter two years of discussions, Vikram began a film under the direction of [[Selvaraghavan]] in a project dubbed by the media as ''Sindubad''. The film began shoot and completed a schedule by early 2010 in the [[Himalayas]] with [[Swati Reddy]] appearing as the female lead. However, the film was reported to be momentarily shelved and subsequently never took off again after the producer Singanamala Ramesh walked out.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/nov-12-02/selvaraghavan-vikram-10-11-12.html |title=Why Did Selvaraghavan And Vikram's Association Break? |publisher=Behindwoods |date=10 November 2012 |accessdate=12 June 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130907204401/http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/nov-12-02/selvaraghavan-vikram-10-11-12.html |archivedate= 7 September 2013 |df= }}</ref> Vikram then agreed terms to feature in [[Vikram Kumar]]'s ''24'', produced by Mohan Natarajan, with [[Ileana D'Cruz]] signed on to play the female lead role. The film progressed briefly with shots being canned in caves, before the director was ousted from the project, cancelling the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/dec-09-04/vikram-vikram-kumar-ileana-21-12-09.html |title=Vikram & Vikram get busy! |publisher=Behindwoods |date=21 December 2009 |accessdate=12 June 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131002113828/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/dec-09-04/vikram-vikram-kumar-ileana-21-12-09.html |archivedate= 2 October 2013 |df= }}</ref> Vikram then also shot briefly for a third successive shelved project directed by [[Boopathy Pandian]] for the same producer, featuring him in the role of an investigative cop; however the film failed to progress and instead Natarajan financed Vikram's next film.<ref>{{cite web|author=V Lakshmi |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-02-09/news-interviews/31040985_1_ileana-producer-mohan-natarajan-telugu-film-industry |title=Ileana refuses to return advance? |work=The Times of India |date=9 February 2012 |accessdate=12 June 2013}}</ref> His 2011 release ''[[Deiva Thirumagal]]'', directed by [[A. L. Vijay]], saw Vikram portray a father with a [[developmental disability]] having the mental maturity of a seven-year-old. To prepare for the role, Vikram visited homes for the mentally challenged such as Vidya Sagar and Vidya Sudha for a month, watching their body language and taking notes.<ref name=\"dtmbestfather\">{{cite web|author=Subramanian, Anupama |date=11 July 2011 |title=I\u2019m the best father: Chiyaan Vikram |work=[[Deccan Chronicle]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/channels/showbiz/kollywood/i%E2%80%99m-best-father-chiyaan-vikram-092 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110817101018/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/channels/showbiz/kollywood/i%E2%80%99m-best-father-chiyaan-vikram-092 |archivedate=17 August 2011 }}</ref> He also communicated with the patients, to pick up the nuances of people with impaired speech. Vikram has since gone on to describe his role as Krishna as the best character he has ever portrayed.<ref name=\"dtmbest\">{{cite web|author=Jeshi, K |date=28 August 2010 |title=Sitting pretty |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article600074.ece |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100902145635/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article600074.ece |archivedate= 2 September 2010 |df= }}</ref> The film, which also featured [[Sara Arjun]], [[Anushka Shetty]] and [[Amala Paul]] in supporting roles, opened to predominantly positive reviews from critics and enjoyed commercial success at the box office.<ref name=\"dtmsuccess\">{{cite web|date=19 July 2011|title=Deiva Thiirumagal comes in for praise|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-07-19/news-interviews/29790374_1_chiyaan-vikram-deiva-thiirumagal-film}}</ref> The reviewer from [[The Deccan Chronicle]] described that the film was \"Vikram's show all the way\" and that \"his rendition of a mentally-challenged man trying to cope with the everyday realities of raising a child is a work of art\", praising his \"fiery, complex performance as one of the more viciously honest depictions of mental illness cinema has seen\".<ref name=\"dtmdc\">{{cite web | url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/channels/showbiz/kollywood/deivathirumagal-it-vikram-all-way-008 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121011205328/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/channels/showbiz/kollywood/deivathirumagal-it-vikram-all-way-008 | archivedate=11 October 2012 | title=Deivathirumagal: It is Vikram all the way | work=[[Deccan Chronicle]] | date=16 July 2011 | accessdate=31 July 2011 | author=Subramanian, Anupama}}</ref> Similarly, another critic described that the on-screen chemistry between Vikram and his daughter, played by Sara Arjun, is \"magic\" and their performances \"are sure to leave a lump in your throat\".<ref name=\"dtmtoi\">{{cite web|author=Narayanan, Venkateswaren |date=17 July 2011 |title=Deiva Thirumagal |work=[[The Times of India]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/tamil/movie-reviews/Deiva-Thirumagal/movie-review/9256649.cms |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121106035815/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/tamil/movie-reviews/Deiva-Thirumagal/movie-review/9256649.cms |archivedate= 6 November 2012 |df= }}</ref> The critic from ''The Hindu'' praised the film and Vikram's performance, but analysed that \"a problem arises only when you stop looking at Krishna as a character, and begin to see him as Vikram, the hero\" and that Vikram should have \"underplayed a little here and there and it would have worked better\".<ref name=\"dtmhind\">{{cite web|author=Rangarajan, Malathi |date=16 July 2011 |title=Deiva Thirumagal: a sensitive poem on celluloid |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article2233163.ece |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110720135157/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article2233163.ece |archivedate=20 July 2011 |df= }}</ref> However, Vikram once again completed a sweep of the top acting awards that year, with further recognition at the Vijay and [[Filmfare Awards South|Filmfare Awards]].<ref>{{cite news| url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-07-08/news-interviews/32588512_1_aadukalam-video-pranayam | title=The 59th Idea Filmfare Awards 2011(South)| date=8 July 2012}}</ref>\n\nVikram next featured in ''[[Rajapattai]]'' (2011), alongside [[Deeksha Seth]], under the direction of [[Suseenthiran]], where he played a [[henchman]] trying to get a break in the [[Tamil cinema|Tamil film]] industry.<ref name=\"rajap\">{{cite web|date=26 July 2011 |title=Vikram's role in Raja Pattai |publisher=Behindwoods |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/jul-11-04/vikram-raja-pattai-26-07-11.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110926094022/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/jul-11-04/vikram-raja-pattai-26-07-11.html |archivedate=26 September 2011 |df= }}</ref> The film opened to mixed reviews from critics in December 2011 and performed below expectations at the box office. Vikram also completed half of a fantasy period film during 2011, ''Karikalan'', in which he played [[Karikala Chola]], a Tamil king who ruled in 270 BC, opposite [[Zarine Khan]], under the direction of graphics director Kannan, but the film was later shelved owing to production troubles.<ref name=\"karikalan\">{{cite web|date=13 May 2011 |title=Vikram & Zarine in Karikalan |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/vikram-zarine-in-karikalan-news-tamil-lfnlLCijcdb.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110819072713/http://www.sify.com/movies/vikram-zarine-in-karikalan-news-tamil-lfnlLCijcdb.html |archivedate=19 August 2011 |df= }}</ref> He then appeared in his second project with director [[A. L. Vijay|Vijay]], portraying the lead role of a blinded [[Research and Analysis Wing|RAW agent]] in the action-thriller, ''[[Thaandavam]]''. The film, which also featured [[Anushka Shetty]], [[Amy Jackson]] and [[Lakshmi Rai]] in pivotal roles, opened to mixed reviews in September 2012.<ref name=\"vijayamy\">{{cite web|author=Ramanujam, Srinivasa|date=10 July 2011|title=Amy in Vikram's next?|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-07-10/news-interviews/29757850_1_amy-jackson-hindi-version-vikram-vijay}}</ref> For his role of a blind man, Vikram trained under noted [[human echolocation]] specialist [[Daniel Kish]], with the latter also playing a cameo in the film.<ref>{{cite news|agency=TNN |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-09-10/news-interviews/33736244_1_vikram-thaandavam-daniel-kish |title=Vikram gets trained by Daniel Kish |work=The Times of India |date=10 September 2012 |accessdate=12 June 2013}}</ref> A critic from Sify.com noted that it was \"Vikram and him alone who diverts your attention from the film's little logical script flaws and spellbinds you with an endearing act that is Thaandavam's biggest strength\";<ref>{{cite web|title=Thaandavam |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/thaandavam-review-tamil-15008711.html |publisher=Sify |accessdate=28 September 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131218212437/http://www.sify.com/movies/thaandavam-review-tamil-15008711.html |archivedate=18 December 2013 |df= }}</ref> subsequently, the film did average business commercially. The actor was next seen portraying the title role in [[Bejoy Nambiar]]'s bilingual ''[[David (2013 Hindi film)|David]]'', which released with different cast members in Hindi and Tamil. Vikram remained the only common lead actor in the versions, with his segment playing out a love story between a careless drunkard fisherman and a mute girl played by [[Isha Sherwani]]. While the Tamil version opened to predominantly positive review,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/south-review-tamil-david/20130201.htm |title=Review: David is a masterpiece |publisher=Rediff |date=1 February 2013 |accessdate=12 June 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130517035734/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/south-review-tamil-david/20130201.htm |archivedate=17 May 2013 |df= }}</ref> the Hindi film also won mixed reviews, with both films performing average business at the box office.\n\n===2015\u2013present===\nVikram signed on to collaborate again with [[S. Shankar|Shankar]] for ''[[I (film)|I]]'', a romantic thriller opposite [[Amy Jackson]], in early 2012.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-07-10/news-interviews/32605619_1_amy-jackson-aascar-ravichandran-vikram |title=Amy Jackson to romance Vikram in I |work=The Times of India |date=10 July 2012 |accessdate=15 July 2012}}</ref> Following hushed production developments, it was revealed that the actor would sport four significantly different looks in the film: a body builder, a beast, a model and a hunchback. He put on weight to portray the bodybuilder, sticking to a diet of protein and coffee, to ensure his muscles are defined on screen. Vikram subsequently lost weight to portray a model, before shaving his head and reducing his weight to 56 kilograms to portray the crippled hunchback.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/vikram-betting-on-i/article6782719.ece |title=Vikram betting on I's success with Pongal release |work=The Hindu |date=13 January 2015 |accessdate=18 January 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160115234452/http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/vikram-betting-on-i/article6782719.ece |archivedate=15 January 2016 |df= }}</ref> He changed his physique by eating small meals of egg whites and apples instead of regular food intakes, while engaging in an intensive weight loss regime to become thin. The cast and crew of the film reportedly struggled to recognise the actor at times, while he also stayed away from the media for close to a year when sporting the look.<ref>{{cite web|author=Subhash K. Jha |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/interview/vikram-i-was-really-tough/20150114.htm |title=Vikram: I was looking pathetic during the shooting of I |publisher=Rediff |date=14 January 2015 |accessdate=18 January 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150118194829/http://www.rediff.com/movies/interview/vikram-i-was-really-tough/20150114.htm |archivedate=18 January 2015 |df= }}</ref> Taking almost three years for production, Vikram described the film \"as the toughest he has ever done\" and regularly suffered [[folliculitis]] as a result of the prosthetic make-up he had to wear.<ref name=\"caravan\"/> The film opened amidst much expectation in January 2015 to mixed reviews, though critics gave Vikram's portrayal of Lingesan, unanimously positive reviews. A critic from Times of India noted: \"Vikram bowls you over with a heart-wrenching performance whether he is handsome or disfigured\", while The Hindu added his transformation was \"laudable\", and that \"Vikram wins hearts as the earnest-to-boot gym rat and as the strapping new model on the block, he floors the audience with his performance as Koonan, the deformed hunchback\".<ref>{{cite news|author=Iyer, Meena |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-review/I/movie-review/45888402.cms |title=Movie Review:I |work=The Times of India |date=14 January 2015 |accessdate=18 January 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150117173150/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-review/I/movie-review/45888402.cms |archivedate=17 January 2015 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Rajendra, Ranjani |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/review-of-i-predictable-beauty-and-the-beast-tale/article6789004.ece |title=Predictable beauty and the beast tale |work=The Hindu |date=14 January 2015 |accessdate=18 January 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201091213/http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/review-of-i-predictable-beauty-and-the-beast-tale/article6789004.ece |archivedate= 1 February 2015 |df= }}</ref> Similarly, Rediff.com noted the actor \"is truly impressive and deserves much applause\", while Sify.com added he \"lived the role\".<ref>{{cite web|author=Saraswathi, S |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-vikram-i-is-definitely-a-pongal-treat/20150114.htm |title=Vikram's I is definitely a Pongal treat |publisher=Rediff.com |date=14 January 2015 |accessdate=18 January 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150117175541/http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-vikram-i-is-definitely-a-pongal-treat/20150114.htm |archivedate=17 January 2015 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/i-review-tamil-15058840.html |title=Movie Review:I |publisher=Sify.com |date=14 January 2015 |accessdate=18 January 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150117174107/http://www.sify.com/movies/i-review-tamil-15058840.html |archivedate=17 January 2015 |df= }}</ref> Despite mixed reviews, ''I'' performed well at the box office, as well as becoming the most successful Tamil film of all time in Kerala.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/vikram-on-10-enradhukulla-movie/article7774642.ece|title=Vikram on 10 Enradhukulla movie|author=sudhir srinivasan|work=The Hindu|accessdate=2 May 2016}}</ref> He then worked on [[Vijay Milton]]'s road-thriller, ''[[10 Enradhukulla]]'' (2015), which featured him as an unnamed race driver who goes on a road trip through [[India]]. Paired opposite [[Samantha Ruth Prabhu|Samantha]], the film opened to mixed reviews and did not perform well at the box office. A critic from Sify.com however, noted that Vikram \"breathes life to his role and his energy level is highly infectious\", adding that \"the way he smiles, dances and fights is a treat for his fans\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/10-enradhukulla-review--pkvqS2bcfcaid.html |title=Review : 10 Enradhukulla |work=Sify |accessdate=2 May 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160129085457/http://www.sify.com/movies/10-enradhukulla-review--pkvqS2bcfcaid.html |archivedate=29 January 2016 |df= }}</ref> Likewise, a critic from The Hindu criticised the film's script, adding that \"it's hard to see Vikram in this fluff\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-reviews/10-enradhukulla-a-slipshod-road-movie/article7790285.ece |title=10 Enradhukulla: A slipshod road movie |author=Baradwaj Rangan |work=The Hindu |accessdate=2 May 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160505013158/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-reviews/10-enradhukulla-a-slipshod-road-movie/article7790285.ece |archivedate= 5 May 2016 |df= }}</ref> Vikram later appeared in ''[[Iru Mugan]]'', a science fiction action film directed by [[Anand Shankar]], featuring him alongside [[Nayanthara]] and [[Nithya Menen]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Im-crazy-when-it-comes-to-acting-Vikram/articleshow/49701028.cms |title=I\u2019m crazy when it comes to acting: Vikram |work=The Times of India |accessdate=2 May 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151110085501/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Im-crazy-when-it-comes-to-acting-Vikram/articleshow/49701028.cms |archivedate=10 November 2015 |df= }}</ref>\n\nHis forthcoming films are [[Gautham Menon]]'s ''[[Dhruva Natchathiram]]'', followed by a sequel to ''Saamy'' directed by Hari,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/saamy-2-vikram-sequel-irumugan-garuda-upcoming/1/733634.html |title=Saamy 2: Vikram's film to go on floors after he completes Garuda |work=India Today |date=6 August 2016 |accessdate=13 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160822061519/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/saamy-2-vikram-sequel-irumugan-garuda-upcoming/1/733634.html |archivedate=22 August 2016 |df= }}</ref> and ''Sketch'', to be directed by Vijay Chander.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/Vikram%E2%80%99s-next-film-to-roll-from-December/article16668274.ece |title=Vikram's next film to roll from December |work=The Hindu |accessdate=23 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161123210513/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/Vikram%E2%80%99s-next-film-to-roll-from-December/article16668274.ece |archivedate=23 November 2016 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.top10cinema.com/article/42106/vikrams-sketch-with-vijay-announced |title=Vikram\u2019s \u2018Sketch\u2019 with Vijay announced |date=8 April 2017 |work=Top 10 Cinema |access-date=9 April 2017 |language=en-US |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170410214146/https://www.top10cinema.com/article/42106/vikrams-sketch-with-vijay-announced |archivedate=10 April 2017 |df= }}</ref>\n\n==Other work==\n\n===Film and television work===\nApart from acting, Vikram has also been a part of other film-making processes with credits as a playback singer and as an assistant director. In 2000, Vikram and actress [[Meena Durairaj|Meena]] launched a pop album titled ''Kadhalism'', which the pair would sing and appear in music videos for, although the project was completed without much promotion.<ref name=\"kadhalism\">{{cite web\n |year=2000 \n |title=Tamil cinema 2000 \n |publisher=CinemaToday2.com \n |accessdate=31 July 2011 \n |url=http://cinematoday2.itgo.com/44Hot%20News%20Just%20for%20U.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120324015314/http://cinematoday2.itgo.com/44Hot%20News%20Just%20for%20U.htm \n |archivedate=24 March 2012 \n |df= \n}}</ref> Following the success of [[Bharathwaj]]'s music for Vikram's 2002 film ''[[Gemini (2002 Tamil film)|Gemini]]'', Vikram sang a version of the hit song \"O Podu!\" for the extended version of the album.<ref name=\"geminimusic\"/> During the making of ''[[Kanthaswamy]]'' in 2009, the music composer [[Devi Sri Prasad]] had asked Vikram to sing a few rough tracks during the film's song composition in [[Malaysia]]. The producers were impressed with his voice and Vikram ended up singing four songs in the film.<ref name=\"singer\">{{cite web|author=Kumar, Ashok |date=14 February 2009 |title=Vikram, now a playback singer too |work=The Hindu |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/2009/02/14/stories/2009021458610200.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121110120148/http://www.hindu.com/2009/02/14/stories/2009021458610200.htm |archivedate=10 November 2012 |df= }}</ref> Furthermore, Vikram also recorded all four tracks in the Telugu version of the album titled ''Mallana''.<ref name=\"singermallana\">{{cite web\n |date=6 February 2009 \n |title=Vikram shows singers the door \n |publisher=Behindwoods \n |accessdate=31 July 2011 \n |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/feb-09-01/vikram-06-02-09.html \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715081820/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/feb-09-01/vikram-06-02-09.html \n |archivedate=15 July 2011 \n |df= \n}}</ref> He then went on to sing for a film he was unrelated to, by lending five different voices in \"Meghame\" for [[G. V. Prakash Kumar]]'s album in ''[[Madrasapattinam]]''.<ref name=\"madras\">{{cite web\n |date=6 March 2010 \n |title=Vikram's five different voices \n |publisher=Behindwoods \n |accessdate=31 July 2011 \n |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/mar-10-02/vikram-madrasapattinam-09-03-10.html \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100819132337/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/mar-10-02/vikram-madrasapattinam-09-03-10.html \n |archivedate=19 August 2010 \n |df= \n}}</ref> He sang two further songs under Prakash Kumar for his ''[[Deiva Thirumagal]]'', singing in the voice of his character, an adult with the maturity of a six-year-old.<ref name=\"vijayvikram\">{{cite web|date=7 February 2011|title=Vikram sings for his next|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-02-07/news-interviews/28546173_1_vikram-voice-song}}</ref> In 2011, he sang the song \"Laddu Laddu\" for his film ''[[Rajapattai]]'', under composer [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]'s direction.<ref>{{cite web|title=Top 10 songs |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-slide-shows/movie-4/top-ten-songs-dec-16/rajapattai.html |publisher=Behindwoods |accessdate=19 December 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120107191935/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-slide-shows/movie-4/top-ten-songs-dec-16/rajapattai.html |archivedate= 7 January 2012 |df= }}</ref> Vikram announced his own production company Reel Life Entertainment in July 2009 and announced that [[M. Sasikumar|Sasikumar]] would direct his first film, the action thriller ''[[Easan]]'', featuring [[Samudrakani]], [[Vaibhav]], [[Abhinaya (actress)|Abhinaya]] and [[Aparnaa Bajpai]].<ref name=\"sasivikram\">{{cite web|date=19 November 2009 |title=Vikram starts his Sasikumar film! |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/vikram-starts-his-sasikumar-film-news-tamil-kkfro8jcjab.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110724144411/http://www.sify.com/movies/vikram-starts-his-sasikumar-film-news-tamil-kkfro8jcjab.html |archivedate=24 July 2011 |df= }}</ref> However, after 90% of the shoot had been completed, Vikram pulled out of the venture, citing that Sasikumar had overshot his budget and the director eventually bought and released the film.<ref name=\"parteways\">{{cite web\n |date=6 September 2010 \n |title=Sasikumar and Vikram part ways \n |publisher=Behindwoods \n |accessdate=31 July 2011 \n |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/sep-10-02/sasi-kumar-vikram-samudrakani-06-09-10.html \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111206014208/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/sep-10-02/sasi-kumar-vikram-samudrakani-06-09-10.html \n |archivedate= 6 December 2011 \n |df= \n}}</ref> The actor, however, was later listed as one of the three producers for his 2013 bilingual film, ''David'', thereby making his debut in film financing. Vikram has also worked as the assistant director under [[Shafi (director)|Shafi]] in ''[[Majaa]]'', and has mentioned that he would like to direct a film in the future.<ref name=\"admajaa\"/>\n\n===Philanthropy===\nVikram has promoted various social causes with several of his charity works being linked to characters he had portrayed in his films. He has been a brand ambassador of Sanjeevani Trust and a school for special children Vidya Sudha, which he stayed at during the making of ''Deiva Thirumagal''.<ref name=\"dtmbest\"/> Moreover, he has had a long-term association since the making of his film ''[[Kasi (film)|Kasi]]'' with the Kasi Eye Care, which does free eye surgeries for the poor.<ref name=\"vikrampoverty\">{{cite news|date=12 April 2011|title=Vikram wants a poverty free world|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=21 February 2011|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-04-12/news-interviews/29409638_1_chiyaan-vikram-envoys-brand-ambassador}}</ref> Vikram has also set up The Vikram Foundation through his fan club to provide heart operations for the poor, educate poor children and rehabilitate victims from natural disasters. Every year, Vikram has celebrated his birthday doing charity work across [[Tamil Nadu]] and in 2008, he organised a camp where a thousand of his fans pledged their eyes in an eye donation appeal.<ref name=\"vikramnet\">{{cite web|title=The Vikram Foundation |url=http://www.chiyaanvikram.net:80/socialview.php?cid=3&ct |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080513222141/http://www.chiyaanvikram.net/socialview.php?cid=3&ct |archivedate=13 May 2008 |publisher=chiyaanvikram.net |accessdate=7 November 2011 |url-status=dead  }}</ref>\n\nHe has lent his support for the Chennai-based charity ''The Banyan'', and appeared in the charity musical [[Netru, Indru, Naalai]] directed by Mani Ratnam for the cause.<ref name=\"ninbanyan\">{{cite web|title=Mani Ratnam to direct Star Vijay's extravaganza |url=http://inhome.rediff.com/movies/2005/jun/15mani.htm |work=Rediff Movies |publisher=Rediff |accessdate=7 November 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715165248/http://inhome.rediff.com/movies/2005/jun/15mani.htm |archivedate=15 July 2011 |df= }}</ref> The actor also starred in the 2010 \"[[Mile Sur Mera Tumhara]]\" music video on national integration alongside a bevy of Indian actors and musicians, describing the experience as \"phenomenal\".<ref name=\"phil\">{{cite web|author=Suresh, Taranya|date=25 February 2010|title=Calling Raavan|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-02-25/news-interviews/28123869_1_raavan-mani-ratnam-films}}</ref> In 2011, Vikram was selected as a Youth Envoy for the [[United Nations Human Settlements Programme]] with his aim being to spread awareness about the statutes of U.N. Habitat which include urban stabilisation and to help formulate plans for effective water management, slum eradication and women and youth empowerment.<ref name=\"nienvoy\">{{cite web|title=Vikram is the youth envoy of UN Habitat |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-south-vikram-is-the-youth-envoy-of-un-habitat/20110413.htm |work=Rediff Movies |publisher=Rediff |accessdate=7 November 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111125054404/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-south-vikram-is-the-youth-envoy-of-un-habitat/20110413.htm |archivedate=25 November 2011 |df= }}</ref> Soon after, he announced two further social projects, \"Karka Kasadara\" and \"Patchai Puratchi\", with the former being to identify school and college dropouts and help them to stand on their own feet, while the latter was about planting trees with an aim to make [[Chennai]] go green.<ref name=\"vikramun\"/> In 2016, he produced and directed the video to the flood relief anthem [[Spirit of Chennai]], as a tribute to the city's volunteers following the [[2015 South Indian floods]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/celebrating-the-spirit-of-chennai/article8083351.ece |title=Celebrating the spirit of Chennai |author=Ranjani Rajendra |work=The Hindu |accessdate=2 May 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160322103414/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/celebrating-the-spirit-of-chennai/article8083351.ece |archivedate=22 March 2016 |df= }}</ref>\n\n==In the media==\n\nVikram is a prolific [[method actor]], being often compared akin to Hollywood's [[Christian Bale]]. Since the success of ''[[Sethu (film)|Sethu]]'', Vikram's intense performances and variety of roles have received critical acclaim.<ref name=\"intense\">{{cite web|author=Reddy, Krithika |date=9 July 2011 |title=Step By Step |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=7 January 2011 |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article2214157.ece |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714061449/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article2214157.ece |archivedate=14 July 2011 |df= }}</ref> His performances as a rogue turned mentally ill patient in ''[[Sethu (film)|Sethu]]'', a gravedigger with autism spectrum disorder in Bala's ''[[Pithamagan]]'', a [[Brahmin]] lawyer with multiple personality disorder in ''[[Anniyan]]'' and a mentally challenged adult with the maturity of a six-year-old boy in ''[[Deiva Thirumagal]]'' are all roles in which he played a mentally affected man, with Vikram mentioning that he does such roles to reinvent himself on screen.<ref name=\"sonvikram\">{{cite web|author=Nagarajan, Saraswathy |date=27 March 2006 |title=V for Vikram |work=The Hindu |accessdate=7 January 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/mp/2006/03/27/stories/2006032700220500.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110713144035/http://www.hindu.com/mp/2006/03/27/stories/2006032700220500.htm |archivedate=13 July 2011 |df= }}</ref> Furthermore, Vikram has enjoyed a large fan following in [[Andhra Pradesh]] as a result of a series of successful dubbed [[Telugu language|Telugu]] films with ''Aparichitudu'', dubbed from his Tamil film ''Anniyan'', being among the most successful Telugu films of 2005. All his films are thus released in Telugu soon after their original release in Tamil, while ''Anniyan'' was also dubbed in Hindi as ''Aparichit''.<ref name=\"mint\"/> He has also enjoyed success in [[Kerala]], where his films have demanded large box office openings akin to Malayalam film stars.<ref name=\"caravan\"/> In 2004, Vikram participated in a live stadium stage event organised by producer [[P. L. Thenappan]] titled \"Vikram Mega Nite\". The event, held in [[Singapore]], attracted several hundreds of his South East Asian fans and was held in the form of a stage musical.<ref name=\"starnite\">{{cite web|author=Pillai, Sreedhar |date=9 February 2004 |title=Valentine's Day Special |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=8 April 2014 |url=http://www.hindu.com/mp/2004/02/09/stories/2004020900030200.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110514071438/http://www.hindu.com/mp/2004/02/09/stories/2004020900030200.htm |archivedate=14 May 2011 |df= }}</ref>\n\nHis pan-Indian popularity has also prompted him to be regularly considered for brand endorsements. In 2005, Vikram was signed as [[Coca-Cola]]'s brand ambassador in [[Tamil Nadu]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/todays-paper/tp-marketing/actor-vikram-is-new-coke-brand-ambassador/article2174957.ece |title=Actor Vikram is new Coke brand ambassador |work=Business Line |date=19 April 2005 |accessdate=13 July 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160115234452/http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/todays-paper/tp-marketing/actor-vikram-is-new-coke-brand-ambassador/article2174957.ece |archivedate=15 January 2016 |df= }}</ref> He has been the ambassador for [[Brooke Bond|Brooke Bond 3 Roses]], [[Manappuram General Finance and Leasing|Manappuram General Finance and Leasing Ltd]] and Josco Jewellers since 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.webindia123.com/news/articles/India/20100928/1596592.html |title=Vikram and Trisha brand ambassadors for Brooke Bond |publisher=News Web India123.com |date=27 September 2010 |accessdate=13 July 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160115234452/http://news.webindia123.com/news/articles/India/20100928/1596592.html |archivedate=15 January 2016 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chiyaanvikramfans.in/2010/05/vikram-brand-ambassador-for-manappuram.html |title=Vikram Brand Ambassador for Manappuram General Finance and Leasing Ltd |publisher=Chiyaan Vikram Fans.in |date=6 May 2010 |accessdate=13 July 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150713180706/http://www.chiyaanvikramfans.in/2010/05/vikram-brand-ambassador-for-manappuram.html |archivedate=13 July 2015 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bpu1egteTGM |title=Chiyaan Vikram in Josco Jewellers Complete Ad 2010-HQ |publisher=YouTube |date=9 November 2010 |accessdate=18 July 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141207082702/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bpu1egteTGM |archivedate= 7 December 2014 |df= }}</ref> In 2015, Vikram has endorsed Big Deal TV, a celebrity-driven home shopping channel.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ytalkies.com/kollywood-film-news/vikram-is-the-brand-ambassador-for-big-deal-tv |title=Vikram is the Brand Ambassador for Big Deal TV |publisher=Y Talikies |date=4 June 2015 |accessdate=13 July 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160115234452/http://www.ytalkies.com/kollywood-film-news/vikram-is-the-brand-ambassador-for-big-deal-tv |archivedate=15 January 2016 |df= }}</ref>\n\nHe is amongst the most decorated actors in terms of awards in the history of [[Tamil cinema]]. He holds a [[National Film Award (India)|National Film Award]] for Best Actor; a feat only matched by four other actors in Tamil films. Moreover, Vikram holds seven [[Filmfare Awards South]], with the tally being only second to [[Kamal Haasan]] who has ten wins. In 2010 his film ''[[Raavan]]'' was promoted at the [[Cannes Film Festival]] and then screened at [[Venice Film Festival]] and the [[Busan International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"venice\"/> Within weeks of release, ''[[Deiva Thirumagal]]'' was sent to the [[Asia Pacific Screen Awards]] after it was nominated by the [[Film Federation of India]] and the National Film Development Corporation.<ref name=\"dtasa\">{{cite web|author=Lakshmi, V|date=1 August 2011|title=DT makes it to international film fest|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-08-01/news-interviews/29838201_1_international-film-tamil-film-national-film-development-corporation}}</ref> Vikram is also a recipient of the [[Kalaimamani|Kalaimamani Award]] from the [[Government of Tamil Nadu]] in 2004. Other recognitions includes a string of [[Cinema Express Awards]], [[Vijay Awards]] and [[Tamil Nadu State Film Awards]], including recognition in three different categories. In 2011, Vikram was awarded an honorary doctorate from Universit\u00e0 Popolare degli Studi di Milano (People's University of Milan) in the field of Fine Arts. Vikram accepted the title on 29 May 2011 and in his next release, ''Deiva Thirumagal'', he was credited as Dr. Chiyaan Vikram.<ref name=\"drvikram\">{{cite web|date=10 March 2011 |title=Vikram gets an honorary doctorate |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=7 January 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/vikram-gets-an-honorary-doctorate-news-tamil-ldknAujjafh.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110313023301/http://www.sify.com/movies/vikram-gets-an-honorary-doctorate-news-tamil-ldknAujjafh.html |archivedate=13 March 2011 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-06-01/news-interviews/29603366_1_honorary-doctorate-vikram-indian-cinema |title=Vikram turns Dr Vikram |work=The Times of India |author=Suresh Kavirayani |date=1 June 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cinema.pluz.in/galleries/kollywood/9451/vikram-honoured-with-doctorate.htm |title=Vikram Honoured With Doctorate |publisher=cinema.pluz.in |date=3 June 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927081021/http://cinema.pluz.in/galleries/kollywood/9451/vikram-honoured-with-doctorate.htm |archivedate=27 September 2013 |df= }}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nVikram met Shailaja Balakrishnan in the late 1980s and married her in 1992 at [[Guruvayoor]] in a mass wedding alongside dozens of couples.<ref name=\"vikramkerala\"/> The pair then had a low-key wedding ceremony conducted at the church at [[Loyola College, Chennai]].<ref name=\"caravan\"/> She hails from [[Thalassery]], [[Kerala]] and now works as a psychology teacher at a leading Chennai school.<ref name=\"teacher\">{{cite web|author=Jha, Subhash K. |date=18 May 2010 |title='Aishwarya's a hero, Abhishek a brat' |publisher=[[CNN-IBN|IBN]] |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/aishwaryas-a-hero-abhishek-a-brat/115603-8-66.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100521092254/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/aishwaryas-a-hero-abhishek-a-brat/115603-8-66.html |archivedate=21 May 2010 |df= }}</ref> Shailaja also worked with the team of ''[[Deiva Thirumagal]]'' by giving professional advice on how people with special needs are treated and helping develop the character played by Vikram.<ref name=\"shailajadt\">{{cite web|author=Ramanujam, Srinivasa|date=19 April 2011|title=Vikram's wife helps Deiva Thirumagan!|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=31 July 2011|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-04-19/news-interviews/29446904_1_shailaja-actor-vikram-vijay}}</ref>\n\nThe couple has a daughter Akshita born in 1993 and a son Dhruv born in 1997.<ref name=\"sonvikram\"/><ref name=\"dhruv\">{{cite web |author=Vandhana |year=2014 |title=Vikram's son not debuting anytime soon |publisher=Silverscreen |accessdate=28 August 2014 |url=http://silverscreen.in/news/vikrams-son-debuting-anytime-soon/ |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140830134627/http://silverscreen.in/news/vikrams-son-debuting-anytime-soon/ |archivedate=30 August 2014 |df= }}</ref> His daughter married Manu Ranjith, the great-grandson of [[M. Karunanidhi]], on 30 October 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thenewsminute.com/article/akshita-manu-ranjith-wedding-vikram-s-daughter-gets-married-karunanidhi-s-great-grandson|title=Akshita-Manu Ranjith wedding: Vikram\u2019s daughter gets married to Karunanidhi\u2019s great grandson|date=1 November 2017|work=The News Minute|access-date=1 November 2017}}</ref> He lives near the beach in [[Besant Nagar]], Chennai and has stated that he would remain based in Chennai regardless of any offers in other regional films.<ref name=\"kanthaint\">{{cite web|author=Jyothsna |year=2009 |title=Vikram in a frank chat with behindwoods.com |publisher=Behindwoods |accessdate=31 July 2011 |url=http://www.videos.behindwoods.com/videos-q1-09/actor-actress-interview/vikram.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110807045813/http://www.videos.behindwoods.com/videos-q1-09/actor-actress-interview/vikram.html |archivedate= 7 August 2011 |df= }}</ref>\n\nDhruv made his debut with ''[[Adithya Varma]]'' in the year 2019 which was the Tamil remake of the Telugu film ''[[Arjun Reddy]]''.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/dhruv-vikram-to-head-to-portugal-for-aditya-varma-song-shoot/articleshow/68749205.cms |title=Dhruv Vikram to head to Portugal for 'Aditya Varma' song shoot |date=6 April 2019 |work=[[The Times of India]] |access-date=8 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography and awards==\n\n===Filmography===\n{{Main|Vikram filmography}}\n\n===Awards and nominations===\n{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Vikram}}\n\n== Discography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20%;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:5%;\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Language\n! Song(s)\n! Composer\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Co-singer(s)\n! class=\"unsortable\" | {{Tooltip|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Shree (2002 film)|Shree]]''\n| 2002\n| Tamil\n| \"Yaamirukka Bayamein\"\n| {{sortname|T. S.|Muralidharan|nolink=1}}\n| [[Shankar Mahadevan]], [[Tippu (singer)|Tippu]]\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref name=\"DTD\">{{cite news | url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/lf/2002/02/01/stories/2002020100410200.htm | title=Dhil to Dhool | work=The Hindu | date=1 February 2002 | accessdate=1 February 2015 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201154114/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/lf/2002/02/01/stories/2002020100410200.htm | archivedate=1 February 2015 | url-status=live}}</ref> <br/> <ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-cinemaplus/sing-on/article3021611.ece | title=Sing on... | work=The Hindu | date=26 June 2009 | accessdate=1 February 2015 | last=Rangarajan | first=Malathi | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201154658/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-cinemaplus/sing-on/article3021611.ece | archivedate=1 February 2015 | url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Gemini (2002 Tamil film)|Gemini]]''\n| 2002\n| Tamil\n| \"O Podu\"\n| [[Bharathwaj]]\n| {{sortname|Anuradha|Sriram}}\n| style=\"text-align: center;\