1||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||32||17\n|-\n|[[2017\u201318 Ligue 2|2017\u201318]]<ref name=\"SW\"/>\n|Ligue 2\n|33||10||6||6||2||2||colspan=2|\u2014||41||18\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!63!!26!!8!!7!!2!!2!!0!!0!!73!!35\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career total\n!271!!88!!13!!8!!5!!3!!1!!0!!290!!99\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Valencia B'''\n*[[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n]]: [[2010\u201311 Tercera Divisi\u00f3n|2010\u201311]]\n\n'''CFR Cluj'''\n*[[Cupa Rom\u00e2niei]]: [[2015\u201316 Cupa Rom\u00e2niei|2015\u201316]]<ref name=Final/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{BDFutbol|9292}}\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n*{{leqstat|61457}}\n\n{{UD Las Palmas squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lopez, Cristian}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Crevillent]]\n[[Category:Spanish footballers]]\n[[Category:Valencian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B players]]\n[[Category:Tercera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Alicante CF footballers]]\n[[Category:Real Madrid Castilla footballers]]\n[[Category:Valencia CF Mestalla footballers]]\n[[Category:CD Atl\u00e9tico Baleares footballers]]\n[[Category:Burgos CF footballers]]\n[[Category:UD Las Palmas players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Huddersfield Town A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Shrewsbury Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Northampton Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Liga I players]]\n[[Category:CFR Cluj players]]\n[[Category:Ligue 1 players]]\n[[Category:Ligue 2 players]]\n[[Category:RC Lens players]]\n[[Category:Angers SCO players]]\n[[Category:UAE Pro League players]]\n[[Category:Hatta Club players]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in England]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Romania]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in France]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in the United Arab Emirates]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate sportspeople in England]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate sportspeople in Romania]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate sportspeople in France]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate sportspeople in the United Arab Emirates]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|Christian Lopez (footballer)}}\n{{spanish name 2|L\u00f3pez|Santamar\u00eda}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Cristian\n| image = Cristian Lopez (Lens).jpg\n| caption = Cristian with [[RC Lens|Lens]] in 2016\n| fullname = Cristian L\u00f3pez Santamar\u00eda\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1989|4|27|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Crevillent]], Spain\n| height = 1.85 m\n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| currentclub = [[UD Las Palmas|Las Palmas]]\n| clubnumber = 17\n| youthyears1 = 1999\u20132002 | youthclubs1 = [[Crevillente Deportivo|Crevillente]]\n| youthyears2 = 2002\u20132003 | youthclubs2 = [[H\u00e9rcules CF|H\u00e9rcules]]\n| youthyears3 = 2003\u20132007 | youthclubs3 = [[Crevillente Deportivo|Crevillente]]\n| youthyears4 = 2007\u20132009 | youthclubs4 = [[Alicante CF|Alicante]]\n| years1 = 2008\u20132009 | clubs1 = [[Alicante CF|Alicante]] | caps1 = 8 | goals1 = 2\n| years2 = 2009\u20132011 | clubs2 = [[Real Madrid Castilla|Real Madrid B]] | caps2 = 44 | goals2 = 10\n| years3 = 2011 | clubs3 = \u2192 [[Valencia CF Mestalla|Valencia B]] (loan) | caps3 = 16 | goals3 = 11\n| years4 = 2011\u20132012 | clubs4 = [[Valencia CF Mestalla|Valencia B]] | caps4 = 31 | goals4 = 11\n| years5 = 2012\u20132013 | clubs5 = [[CD Atl\u00e9tico Baleares|Atl\u00e9tico Baleares]] | caps5 = 35 | goals5 = 9\n| years6 = 2013\u20132014 | clubs6 = [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] | caps6 = 2 | goals6 = 0\n| years7 = 2013 | clubs7 = \u2192 [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]] (loan) | caps7 = 5 | goals7 = 1\n| years8 = 2014 | clubs8 = \u2192 [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]] (loan) | caps8 = 3 | goals8 = 0\n| years9 = 2014\u20132015 | clubs9 = [[Burgos CF|Burgos]] | caps9 = 36 | goals9 = 13\n| years10 = 2015\u20132016 | clubs10 = [[CFR Cluj]] | caps10 = 44 | goals10 = 16\n| years11 = 2016\u20132018 | clubs11 = [[RC Lens|Lens]] | caps11 = 63 | goals11 = 26\n| years12 = 2018\u20132019 | clubs12 = [[Angers SCO|Angers]] | caps12 = 19 | goals12 = 2\n| years13 = 2019\u20132020 | clubs13 = [[Hatta Club|Hatta]] | caps13 = 12 | goals13 = 5\n| years14 = 2020\u2013 | clubs14 = [[UD Las Palmas|Las Palmas]] | caps14 = 1 | goals14 = 0\n| totalcaps = | totalgoals = \n| club-update = 8 March 2020\n}}\n'''Cristian L\u00f3pez Santamar\u00eda''' (born 27 April 1989), known simply as '''Cristian''', is a Spanish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[UD Las Palmas]].\n\n==Club career==\n===Alicante===\nBorn in [[Crevillent]], [[Province of Alicante|Alicante]], [[Valencian Community]], Cristian played for several clubs as a youth, including local [[Crevillente Deportivo]] and [[Alicante CF]]. He made his debut for the latter's first team during the [[2007\u201308 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|2007\u201308 season]], as they returned to [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]] after a 50-year absence.\n\nIn [[2008\u201309 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|the following campaign]], Cristian continued playing mostly with the reserves in [[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n]], with the main squad finally being relegated. He made his division two debut in a game against [[H\u00e9rcules CF]] on 6 June 2009, scoring in a 1\u20132 [[local derby]] home loss.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.laverdad.es/alicante/20090607/deportes_alicante/alicante/hercules-sigue-vida-20090607.html|title=El H\u00e9rcules sigue con vida (1\u20132)|trans-title=H\u00e9rcules still alive (1\u20132)|newspaper=[[La Verdad (Murcia)|La Verdad]]|first=Jos\u00e9 Manuel|last=Penad\u00e9s|language=es|date=7 June 2009|accessdate=15 January 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Castilla / Mestalla===\nL\u00f3pez signed for [[Real Madrid Castilla]] in the summer of 2009, with [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]]'s reserves in the third division. He finished [[2009\u201310 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|his first year]] with ten goals \u2013 second-best in the squad \u2013 as the team finished eighth in the league.\n\nIn January 2011, Cristian signed for [[Valencia CF]]'s [[Valencia CF Mestalla|B-team]] in the fourth level, in a [[2010\u201311 Tercera Divisi\u00f3n|season]]-long loan.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.superdeporte.es/valencia/2011/01/28/valencia-ficha-cristian-delantero-castilla/117998.html|title=El Valencia ficha a Cristian, delantero del Castilla|trans-title=Valencia sign Cristian, Castilla forward|newspaper=[[Super Deporte]]|first=Carlos|last=Bosch|language=es|date=28 January 2011|accessdate=6 November 2013}}</ref> He scored in double digits as the ''Che'' reserves returned to the third tier at the first attempt, and the move was made permanent in the summer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.defensacentral.com/la_fabrica/60706-cristian-santamaria-real-madrid-valencia-mestalla-valencia-promesa-delantero-ficahje-traspaso/|title=Cristian sigue los pasos de Canales|trans-title=Cristian in the footsteps of Canales|publisher=Defensa Central|language=es|date=11 August 2011|accessdate=6 November 2013}}</ref> He added a further 11 goals [[2011\u201312 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|the following campaign]], including all of his team's goals on 13 May 2012 as they won 4\u20132 at [[UE Sant Andreu]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uesantandreu.cat/2012/05/ue-sant-andreu-2-valencia-cf-mestalla-4/|title=UE Sant Andreu 2 \u2013 Val\u00e8ncia CF Mestalla 4|publisher=UE Sant Andreu|language=ca|date=13 May 2012|accessdate=13 November 2015}}</ref>\n\nCristian spent [[2012\u201313 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|2012\u201313]] still in division three, with [[CD Atl\u00e9tico Baleares]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.futbolbalear.es/2012/09/05/presentacion-oficial-de-jose-picon-cristian-lopez-y-roque-mesa-por-el-atco-baleares/|title=Presentaci\u00f3n oficial de Jos\u00e9 Pic\u00f3n, Cristian L\u00f3pez y Roque Mesa por el Atco. Baleares|trans-title=Official presentation of Jos\u00e9 Pic\u00f3n, Cristian L\u00f3pez and Roque Mesa by Atco. Baleares|publisher=F\u00fatbol Balear|language=es|date=5 September 2012|accessdate=10 October 2013}}</ref> He ranked top scorer for the [[Palma de Majorca]]-based side, scoring twice on 31 March 2013 in a 3\u20130 home win over city rivals [[RCD Mallorca B]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mallorcaesports.es/futbol/item/6599-atletico-baleares-mallorca-b-a-partir-de-las-12-horas|title=Final: Atco Baleares \u2013 Mallorca B (3\u20130)|trans-title=End: Atco Baleares \u2013 Mallorca B (3\u20130)|publisher=Mallorca Esports|language=es|date=31 March 2013|accessdate=13 November 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Huddersfield===\nOn 24 July 2013, trialist Cristian played for [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] against [[Real Betis]], in a 2\u20134 [[Exhibition game|friendly]] loss at the [[John Smith's Stadium]], and he scored in the next pre-season match with [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]] (2\u20133 defeat). The following week he signed a one-year deal with the Terriers, taking the number 19 shirt vacated by [[Alan Lee (footballer)|Alan Lee]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/23516824|title=Huddersfield Town sign striker Cristian Lopez|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=31 July 2013|accessdate=3 September 2013}}</ref>\n\nCristian made his [[Football League Championship]] on 3 August 2013, coming on as a [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in a 0\u20131 defeat at [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] \u2013 in the process, he became the club's first ever Spanish player in its 105-year history.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/23516824|title=Huddersfield Town sign striker Cristian Lopez|publisher=BBC Sport|date=31 July 2013|accessdate=3 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/23474913|title=Nottingham Forest 1\u20130 Huddersfield|publisher=BBC Sport|date=3 August 2013|accessdate=3 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.examinerlive.co.uk/sport/football/news/huddersfield-town-striker-cristian-lopez-6164262|title=Huddersfield Town striker Cristian Lopez joins Shrewsbury on loan|newspaper=[[Huddersfield Daily Examiner]]|first=Doug|last=Thomson|date=10 October 2013|accessdate=5 December 2019}}</ref> On 10 October, however, he joined [[Football League One]] side [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]] on a month's loan, becoming the first Spaniard to sign for the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/24451548|title=Cristian Lopez: Shrewsbury Town sign Huddersfield striker on loan|publisher=BBC Sport|date=10 October 2013|accessdate=10 October 2013}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the team and in [[Football in England|English football]] on the 22nd, in a 1\u20131 draw against [[Colchester United F.C.|Colchester United]] at the [[New Meadow]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/24529458|title=Shrewsbury Town 1\u20131 Colchester United|publisher=BBC Sport|date=22 October 2013|accessdate=23 October 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.htafc.com/news/2013/october/cristian-nets-first-goal/|title=Cristian nets first goal|publisher=Huddersfield Town A.F.C|first=Jack|last=Hoyle|date=28 October 2013|accessdate=5 December 2019}}</ref> but returned to Huddersfield on 5 November following an injury crisis to its attacking sector.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.shropshirestar.com/sport/football/shrewsbury-town-fc/2013/11/05/shrewsbury-town-after-new-striker-as-cristian-lopez-returns-to-huddersfield/|title=Shrewsbury Town after new striker as Cristian Lopez returns to Huddersfield|newspaper=[[Shropshire Star]]|date=5 November 2013|accessdate=4 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 14 March 2014, L\u00f3pez moved to [[Football League Two|League Two]]'s [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]], on loan for the rest of [[2013\u201314 in English football|the season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ntfc.co.uk/news/article/lopez-signs-1420404.aspx|title=Cristian Lopez joins Northampton Town|publisher=Northampton Town F.C|date=14 March 2014|accessdate=14 March 2014}}</ref> He was released by Huddersfield in May.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/27284802|title=Huddersfield Town captain Peter Clarke among eight released|publisher=BBC Sport|date=5 May 2014|accessdate=17 December 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Burgos / CFR Cluj===\nOn 17 July 2014, Cristian joined [[Burgos CF]] in the third tier,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.diariodeburgos.es/noticia/Z8FCD4684-A3B4-F19D-1643B7C742E28B3F/20140717/burgos/cf/cierra/fichaje/delantero/alicantino/cristian/lopez|title=El Burgos CF cierra el fichaje del delantero alicantino Cristian L\u00f3pez|trans-title=Burgos CF seal the signing of Alicante-born forward Cristian L\u00f3pez|newspaper=Diario de Burgos|language=es|date=17 July 2014|accessdate=18 February 2015}}</ref> eventually helping his team to a [[2014\u201315 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|mid-table finish]]. He received a straight [[Ejection (sports)|red card]] on 11 October 2014 in a goalless draw at [[CD Guijuelo]], for a 15th-minute high challenge on Juli Ferrer.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.diariodeburgos.es/noticia/Z3BCE2859-CF7B-1E9B-12E5CCB8A45E250E/20141013/burgos/cf/recurrira/expulsion/cristian/lopez/frente/guijuelo|title=El Burgos CF recurrir\u00e1 la expulsi\u00f3n de Cristian L\u00f3pez frente al Guijuelo|trans-title=Burgos CF will appeal the expulsion of Cristian L\u00f3pez against Guijuelo|newspaper=Diario de Burgos|first=Rom\u00e1n|last=Romero|language=es|date=13 October 2014|accessdate=13 November 2015}}</ref>\n\nCristian moved abroad for the second time in June 2015, signing with Romanian [[Liga I]] team [[CFR Cluj]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stiridesport.ro/competitii/liga-1/cfr-cluj-cristian-lopez-jakimovski-video.html|title=Atacantul spaniol de la Burgos este ultima achizi\u0163ie a celor de la CFR Cluj! Ardelenii negociaz\u0103 \u015fi cu un v\u00e2rf din Italia!|trans-title=Spanish forward from Burgos is CFR Cluj's latest acquisition! Transylvanians also in negotiations with an Italian giant!|publisher=Stiride Sport|language=ro|date=19 June 2015|accessdate=30 June 2015}}</ref> He made his top flight debut on 11 July, replacing [[Guima]] for the final 20 minutes of a 2\u20132 draw at [[FC Viitorul Constan\u021ba]] in the opening game of [[2015\u201316 Liga I|the season]]. A month later, he scored his first goal for the ''Feroviarii'', the game's only at the ''[[Stadionul Dr. Constantin R\u0103dulescu]]'' against [[FC Petrolul Ploie\u0219ti]], four minutes after coming on for [[Leo Beleck]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-intern/liga-1/arcasul-cfr-ului-cristian-lopez-isi-explica-gestul-de-dupa-golul-cu-petrolul-fost-la-real-madrid-spaniolul-promite-sa-fie-golgheter-voi-marca-multe-goluri-14672994|title=\"Arca\u015ful\" CFR-ului, Cristian Lopez, \u00ee\u015fi explic\u0103 gestul de dup\u0103 golul cu Petrolul. Fost la Real Madrid, spaniolul promite s\u0103 fie golgheter: \"Voi marca multe goluri\"|trans-title=CFR's \"archer\", Cristian L\u00f3pez, explains his gesture after goal against Petrolul. Formerly of Real Madrid, the Spaniard promises to be top scorer: \"I will score many goals\"|newspaper=[[ProSport]]|first=Vlad|last=M\u0103cic\u0103\u0219an|language=ro|date=12 August 2015|accessdate=13 November 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 August 2015, Cristian recorded a [[hat-trick]] in a 3\u20131 home win over [[FC Boto\u0219ani]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digisport.ro/Sport/FOTBAL/Competitii/Liga+1/VIDEO+Cristian+Lopez+a+marcat+de+trei+ori+cu+FC+Botosani+Primul+|title=Cristian Lopez a marcat de trei ori cu FC Boto\u015fani. Primul hat-trick al sezonului \u00een Liga 1|trans-title=Cristian L\u00f3pez scored three against FC Boto\u015fani. First hat-trick of the Liga I season|publisher=[[Digi Sport (Romania)|Digi Sport]]|language=ro|date=31 August 2015|accessdate=13 November 2015}}</ref> The following 17 May, in the final of the [[Cupa Rom\u00e2niei]], he came on at [[half-time]] for [[Tomislav Gomelt]] and headed a last-minute equaliser as CFR came from behind to draw 2\u20132 against [[FC Dinamo Bucure\u0219ti]] before [[2015\u201316 Cupa Rom\u00e2niei|winning]] in a [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shootout]].<ref name=Final>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36320965|title=Ekeng's Dinamo Bucharest lose Romanian Cup final|publisher=BBC Sport|date=18 May 2016|accessdate=19 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Lens===\nCristian switched countries again on 31 August 2016, when he joined [[Ligue 2]] club [[RC Lens]] on a one-year deal with the option for a second.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rclens.fr/infos_2016/08/31_contrat_lopez_c/index.php|title=Officiel: Cristian Lopez nouvel attaquant lensois!|trans-title=Official: Cristian L\u00f3pez new Lens forward!|publisher=RC Lens|language=fr|date=31 August 2016|accessdate=19 September 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160903144712/http://www.rclens.fr/infos_2016/08/31_contrat_lopez_c/index.php|archive-date=3 September 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> He made his debut nine days later, replacing [[K\u00e9vin Fortun\u00e9]] for the final ten minutes of a 1\u20131 home draw with [[FC Bourg-P\u00e9rronas]], and scored his first goal on 20 September in a 4\u20132 win over [[US Orl\u00e9ans]] also at the ''[[Stade Bollaert-Delelis]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lensois.com/2016/09/l2-j8-rc-lens-orleans-4-2-john-bostock-un-homme-dans-le-match/|title=John Bostock, un homme dans le match|trans-title=John Bostock, a man in the match|publisher=Lensois|language=fr|date=20 September 2016|accessdate=3 October 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161003193747/http://www.lensois.com/2016/09/l2-j8-rc-lens-orleans-4-2-john-bostock-un-homme-dans-le-match/|archive-date=3 October 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> The team [[2016\u201317 Ligue 2|finished in fourth]], one point off promotion, and he was joint-third amongst scorers with 16 goals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.footmali.com/malifoot/troyes-44-ans-que-le-club-navait-pas-connu-un-attaquant-comme-niane%20-%20footmali.com|title=[Troyes] \u2013 44 ans que le club n'avait pas connu un attaquant comme Niane|trans-title=[Troyes] \u2013 44 years that the club did not know a striker like Niane|publisher=Foot Mali|first=Youssouf|last=Kon\u00e9|language=fr|date=24 June 2017|accessdate=5 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nCristian scored eight times in the first half of the [[2017\u201318 Ligue 2|2017\u201318 season]]. He then embarked on a drought which lasted until the final two fixtures against [[Tours FC]] and [[AJ Auxerre]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lavoixdunord.fr/368037/article/2018-04-29/cristian-lopez-c-est-quoi-le-probleme|title=Ligue 2: Cristian Lopez, c\u2019est quoi le probl\u00e8me?|trans-title=Ligue 2: Cristian L\u00f3pez, what's the problem?|newspaper=[[La Voix du Nord (daily)|La Voix du Nord]]|first=S\u00e9bastien|last=No\u00e9|language=fr|date=29 April 2018|accessdate=5 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.madeinlens.com/actualite-rclens/saison-2017-2018/jour-de-match/43823-et-de-10-en-ligue-2-pour-cristian-lopez-avec-le-rc-lens.html|title=Et de 10 en Ligue 2 pour Cristian Lopez avec le RC Lens|trans-title=And 10 in Ligue 2 for Cristian L\u00f3pez with RC Lens|publisher=Made in Lens|language=fr|date=11 May 2018|accessdate=5 October 2019}}</ref> and fans petitioned for him to be given a new contract.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lavoixdunord.fr/375479/article/2018-05-12/des-supporters-lancent-une-petition-pour-voir-cristian-lopez-rester-lens|title=Foot \u2013 RC Lens: Des supporters lancent une p\u00e9tition pour voir Cristian Lopez rester \u00e0 Lens|trans-title=Football \u2013 RC Lens: Supporters launch a petition to see Cristian L\u00f3pez stay at Lens|newspaper=La Voix du Nord|language=fr|date=12 May 2018|accessdate=5 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Angers===\nOn 31 August 2018, the last day of the 2018 summer transfer window, [[free agent]] Cristian signed a one-year contract with [[Angers SCO]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/angers-sco/ligue-1-angers-sco-officialise-l-arrivee-de-cristian-lopez-5944257|title=Ligue 1. Angers Sco officialise l\u2019arriv\u00e9e de Cristian Lopez|trans-title=Ligue 1. Angers Sco make arrival of Cristian Lopez official|newspaper=[[Ouest-France]]|language=French|date=31 August 2018|accessdate=31 August 2018}}</ref> His maiden appearance in [[Ligue 1]] took place on 6 October, when he played the last eight minutes of a 2\u20132 home draw to [[RC Strasbourg Alsace]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football365.fr/l1-j9-angers-revient-de-loin-contre-strasbourg-7914358.html|title=L1 (J9): Angers revient de loin contre Strasbourg|trans-title=L1 (R9): Angers come from afar against Strasbourg|publisher=Football 365|first=Geoffrey|last=Steines|language=fr|date=6 October 2018|accessdate=4 October 2019}}</ref> He scored his first goal late in same month, but in a 1\u20132 loss against [[Olympique Lyonnais]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sport.francetvinfo.fr/football/ligue-1/ligue-1-suivez-angers-lyon-en-direct|title=Ligue 1: Revivez la douloureuse victoire de Lyon sur le terrain d'Angers|trans-title=Ligue 1: Relive Lyon's painful win at Angers|publisher=[[France T\u00e9l\u00e9visions]]|language=fr|date=27 October 2018|accessdate=4 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Hatta / Las Palmas===\nOn 19 August 2019, Cristian agreed to a one-year deal at [[UAE Pro-League]]'s [[Hatta Club]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.albayan.ae/sports/emirates/2019-08-19-1.3629483|title=\u0627\u0644\u0625\u0633\u0628\u0627\u0646\u064a \u0644\u0648\u0628\u064a\u0632 \u0631\u0627\u0628\u0639 \u0623\u062c\u0627\u0646\u0628 \u062d\u062a\u0627|trans-title=Spaniard L\u00f3pez the fourth Hatta foreigner|newspaper=[[Al Bayan (newspaper)|Al Bayan]]|language=ar|date=19 August 2019|accessdate=19 August 2019}}</ref> The following 1 March, he signed for Segunda Divisi\u00f3n team [[UD Las Palmas]] for the rest of the season with the option of one more.<ref>{{cite news |last1=P\u00e9rez Ben\u00edtez |first1=Juan |title=Las Palmas ficha a Cristian L\u00f3pez|trans-title=Las Palmas sign Cristian L\u00f3pez |url=https://www.canarias7.es/deportes/ud-las-palmas/las-palmas-ficha-a-cristian-lopez-HD8720081 |accessdate=9 April 2020 |publisher=[[Canarias 7]] |date=1 March 2020 |language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n==Club statistics==\n{{updated|match played 4 August 2018}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Alicante CF|Alicante]]\n|[[2007\u201308 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|2007\u201308]]<ref name=\"BD\">{{cite web|url=http://www.bdfutbol.com/en/j/j9292.html|title=Cristian: Cristian L\u00f3pez Santamar\u00eda|publisher=BDFutbol|accessdate=4 September 2015}}</ref>\n|[[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B]]\n|5||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||5||0\n|-\n|[[2008\u201309 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|2008\u201309]]<ref name=\"BD\"/>\n|[[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]]\n|3||2||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||3||2\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!8!!2!!0!!0!!colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014!!8!!2\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Real Madrid Castilla|Real Madrid B]]\n|[[2009\u201310 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|2009\u201310]]<ref name=\"BD\"/>\n|Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B\n|33||10||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||33||10\n|-\n|[[2010\u201311 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|2010\u201311]]<ref name=\"BD\"/>\n|Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B\n|11||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||11||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!44!!10!!colspan=\"2\"|\u2014!!col